title: karo pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add rest of ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 325° and bake until done (20 to 25 minutes).

title: apple dumplings
directions: Heat the water.
Roll biscuits to size of saucer.
Put apples on roll.
Fold together and crimp edges; put in baking dish.
Pour syrup over.
Sprinkle 1 cup sugar and 1 stick margarine.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and allspice over top.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, or until brown.

title: strawberry delight
directions: Mix cream cheese and sugar.
Add strawberries, pineapple and pecans.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into gelatin mold or casserole dish sprayed with a thin coating of cooking oil spray.
Freeze 3 to 4 hours before serving.

title: country chicken and biscuits
directions: Grease 9 x 13-inch pan.
Combine
first
four
ingredients. Add
1 cup cheese.	Blend soup and 1
cup
milk.
Pour over mixture and bake, covered, at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Put onions, chopped celery, garlic salt, Cajun seasoning and chicken in water.
Boil until chicken is done.
Place chicken in bottom of casserole dish.
Put mushroom soup over chicken and then peas.
Put spaghetti (cooked in broth that chicken was cooked in) over peas.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, peel and slice potatoes; set aside.
Cook bacon until crisp.
Remove from fat.
Measure 5 tablespoons bacon fat; put in large skillet.
Heat.
Add flour and make a paste.
Add water, vinegar, sugar and onions.
Stir until smooth.
Add 1 tablespoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper to taste.
Add potatoes and heat through.

title: garden pea salad
directions: Mix all together, except mayonnaise.
Add mayonnaise to suit taste.
Refrigerate until ready to eat.

title: apple crisp(diabetic recipe)
directions: Wash, peel and slice apples.
Place on bottom of 8-inch square baking dish.
Add water and vanilla.
Combine flour, sugar replacement, cinnamon and margarine in bowl or food processor. Work with pastry wire or steel blade into crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs evenly over top of apple slices.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: christina's orange cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to package directions, preheating oven according to directions for a 13 x 9 pan. Cool cake completely and then put in refrigerator for a few hours until nice and cold. Take cake out and poke holes all over the entire cake with a dinner fork.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute the onion in butter.
Mix all together.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch greased baking dish.
Bake approximately 1 hour at 350°.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until fluffy.
Beat in sugar and vanilla. Add peanut butter and milk; blend.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shells.
Freeze for 4 hours.
Sprinkle top with ground peanuts.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown beef and bacon with a little oil.
Mix well with all the remaining ingredients.
Place in large casserole dish and bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.
May also be put in a crock-pot and cooked for 4 to 5 hours.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix and store in refrigerator 2 days before using.
Can be refrigerated 2 to 3 weeks and used gradually.
Spray muffin tins with Pam.
Bake 15 minutes at 400°.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Beat eggs lightly.
Add oil, water, and 3/4 c. strawberries with juice.
Add cake mix and dry jello.
Mix well.
Bake in 9 x 13 inch pan or in layers for 25 minutes at 350 degrees.
Mix margarine, vanilla, confectioners sugar, and 1/3 c. strawberries with juice.
Spread over cooled cake after baking.

title: cheese potatoes
directions: Peel and boil potatoes until done. Drain the water off the potatoes and add the margarine, salt and pepper. Mash as you would for mashed potatoes. After they are mashed add all the cheeses except cheddar. Pour mixture in baking dish and sprinkle the cheddar cheese on top. Bake in preheated 400 degree oven long enough for
the potatoes to get bubbly and the cheese on top to melt.

title: ham party rolls
directions: Melt margarine.
Mix together margarine, poppy seed, mustard, onion and Worcestershire sauce and simmer.
Spread half inside open rolls.
Then put ham and cheese on rolls.
Top with other half of roll and spread remaining sauce over rolls.
Bake 30 minutes (if frozen) at 300°.
If not frozen, bake for 20 minutes.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Mix milk, butter and cheese and bring to a boil over low heat. Cook macaroni according to package and drain well.
Mix macaroni and add milk and cheese mixture together.
Bake in oven for 30 minutes.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder, salt and sugar into bowl. Add shortening, eggs and bananas.
Mix well.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased 5 x 9-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Yields 10 servings.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Use large casserole dish that has been sprayed good with Pam. Start with meat; add next four ingredients in layers.
Should have at least 2 layers of each.
On top of each layer, add margarine, salt and pepper.
Pour soup, mixed with water, over top of casserole and bake 1 hour at 375°.
Remove from oven and add cheese to top; return to oven and brown.
Let stand for 15 minutes before serving.
(For smaller dish, use half of all ingredients.)

title: mocha rum sauce
directions: Heat the butter in a 2 1/2-quart saucepan over medium heat. When melted, add the sugar, heavy cream, sifted cocoa, 2 tablespoons rum and salt.
Stir with a whisk to combine.
Bring to a boil, then adjust the heat and allow to simmer for 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Remove the saucepan from the heat.
Add the instant coffee, vanilla extract and the remaining tablespoon of rum; stir until smooth.
Allow to cool to room temperature before serving.

title: egg nog
directions: Beat egg whites until soft peaks form.
Add egg yolks.
Beat well.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add milk and flavoring. Beat well.
Whip the heavy cream. Fold gently into eggnog. Sprinkle with nutmeg.

title: saucy frichick and asparagus
directions: If desired, partially cook asparagus; drain.
Place the asparagus in a greased 9-inch square baking dish.
In a skillet over medium heat, brown frichick in oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Arrange frichick over asparagus.
In a bowl, mix soup, mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Pour over frichick, cover and bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese. Let stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken spaghetti casserole
directions: Saute celery and green peppers.
Add Greek or Italian seasoning to taste.
Mix soups, mushrooms and milk to celery and green peppers.
Add Velveeta and pimentos.
Mix all ingredients with chicken and spaghetti.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes and sprinkle with paprika.
Will make two 9 x 13-inch casseroles and serves 14 to 16.
Freezes well.

title: salmon cheddar pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Beat eggs in large bowl; add milk, 2 tablespoons of the parsley, butter, green onion, 1 tablespoon of the lemon juice, Worcestershire sauce and mustard; mix well.
Fold in cheese and salmon; pour into cooled pie shell.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until just set and crust is golden brown.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Combine sour cream, cucumber, remaining 1 tablespoon parsley, dill, remaining 1 teaspoon lemon juice and pepper.
Mix well.
Serve sour cream mixture over pie.

title: crab quiche
directions: Stir together cheeses and flour.
Beat together eggs, cream, mustard, salt and Worcestershire.
Set aside.
Line pastry shell with drained crab meat.
Combine egg and cheese mixtures.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes or until set. Let stand for 20 minutes before cutting.

title: johnny marzetti
directions: Brown beef and onions. Precook celery and green pepper with little water.
Precook noodles and drain.
Add rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Then sprinkle grated cheese on top and return to oven for 10 minutes more.
When the recipe is doubled, it makes enough for 9 x 12-inch deep cake pan and another 8 x 10-inch glass pan for the freezer!

title: broccoli bake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine all ingredients. Spoon into baking dish.
Bake about 1 hour.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix jello with water; partially set.
Add bananas, crushed pineapple and marshmallows; stir and set firm.
Cook and cool the egg, sugar, flour, oleo and pineapple juice.
Will cook thick. Add cream cheese.
Cool completely, then add small Cool Whip. Place on top of firm jello mixture.
Add nuts if desired.

title: lemon-baked steak
directions: Wash steak and place in large baking dish.
Rub with softened butter.
Season with salt and pepper.
Cover with lemon and onion slices.
Combine ketchup, Worcestershire sauce and water.
Pour over steak.
Cover tightly.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours or until tender.

title: sweet potato souffle
directions: Add ingredients, one at a time, to potatoes in Mixmaster bowl until well blended.
Spread on greased baking dish and bake at 350° about 20 minutes.
Top with marshmallows and brown.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Peel apples and cut in small pieces. Put in greased baking dish.
If apples are not juicy, put 1/4 cup water in them.

title: railroad pie
directions: Brown ground beef and onion in skillet; drain well.
Combine remaining ingredients with meat mixture and pour into a 2-quart greased casserole dish.

title: kielbasa soup
directions: Melt butter in Dutch oven.
Add kielbasa chunks, saute until lightly browned.
Add onions and garlic.
Saute briefly and add carrots, broth and rice.
Bring to a boil, reduce heat, cover and simmer 15 minutes.
Add spinach strips, zucchini, green beans and corn.
Cover and simmer 15 minutes or until carrots and beans are done.
Season to taste.
I usually like to make it a day before so it blends.

title: crock-pot pork chops
directions: Season pork chops with salt, pepper and Tony's as desired. Place in crock-pot and sprinkle each with onion soup mix.
Cook on high until dark brown.
May also be slow cooked on low.
It will make a gravy that may be served on rice.

title: caesar dressing
directions: Throw all in blender and whip.
Keep in jar in fridge.
Easy and good.

title: spread-a-burger
directions: In a large bowl, blend meat, soup, seasoning, onion and pepper until thoroughly mixed.
Spread 1/4 cup meat mixture on each roll half.
Spread to cover edges.
Place rolls, meat side up, on baking dish.
Broil 4 to 6 inches from the heat for 7 to 8 minutes. Sprinkle with cheese and continue until cheese is melted.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheese cake
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Put in graham cracker crust. Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
(I usually cook mine about 30 minutes.)
Cool 5 minutes.
Mix sour cream, remaining sugar and vanilla.
Put on top and bake 10 minutes more.

title: easy and delicious stewed beef
directions: Place in crock-pot and cook on high for 2 to 3 hours, until tender.

title: chocolate delight
directions: First Layer:
Mix flour, margarine and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Bake 25 minutes at 325°.

title: pork roast with sweet potatoes and apples
directions: You will need a Reynolds oven cooking bag.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine cheese until well blended.
Add all other ingredients; mix well.
Chill until hardened (1 hour or more).
Shape into a ball; roll in nuts or chipped beef.

title: layered salad
directions: Top with dressing of first 3 ingredients.
Sprinkle cheese and bacon on top of dressing.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix sugar, eggs, butter and flour.
Heat milk until warm.
Add milk and vanilla.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake for 350° to 375°, according to oven, for 35 minutes.

title: blt toss salad
directions: Combine tomatoes, celery, salad dressing, green peppers and onion.
Toss lightly.
Chill 1 hour.
Add bacon; toss lightly. Spoon vegetable mixture over shredded lettuce.
Garnish with additional cherry tomato halves and bacon crumbs if desired. Yields 6 servings.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and set aside.
Prepare pudding with electric mixer.
Blend in cream cheese.
Add Cool Whip.
Mix well.
Layer in flowerpot the cookies, filling and cookies again.
Make last layer of cookies thick on top.
Use silk or live flowers with stem wrapped in plastic wrap.
You can use lemon cookies and lemon pudding mix also.
Surprise your guests.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Bring to boil; simmer 10 minutes.

title: chocolate chip cookies(diet)
directions: Combine butter, egg, vanilla, extract, milk, Sugar Twin and water.
Beat for 1 minute at medium speed.
Add flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend for 2 minutes at low speed.
Fold in chocolate chips and drop by teaspoons on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: crispy cookie logs
directions: **Chocolate chips, raisins, chopped walnuts, other nuts, or a combination may also be used.

title: chocolate caramel bars
directions: Blend all ingredients, except caramels and chocolate chips, until crumbly.
Put 2/3 of mixture in a 9 x 13-inch baking dish, greased.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Remove from oven and pour chocolate chips over.
Set aside.
Melt the 64 caramels and 1/2 cup plus 2 tablespoons of milk until creamy.
Pour over the chocolate chips.
Sprinkle the remaining crumb mixture over the top.
Bake 15 minutes or until the top is lightly browned.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Stir together; pour in greased pie dish (deep).
Pour fruit on top.
Save some dough for top.
Cook 15 minutes at 425°.
Reduce heat and continue to cook until light brown.

title: company veggie bake
directions: Cook vegetables, covered in 1/2 cup boiling water for 5 minutes.
Drain, reserving liquid.
Add water to liquid to measure 1/4 cup.
Combine vegetables, pepper and 3/4 cup cheese.
Add liquid and turn into a 1-quart casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese; bake, uncovered, 2 minutes more.
Serves 4.

title: fruit cake
directions: Prepare first five ingredients together in large container. Set aside.
In a large mixing bowl, cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Set aside.
Sift together flour (one cup is correct) and nutmeg and mix with fruit and nuts.
Add butter, sugar, egg mixture to fruit and nuts alternately with wine.
Mix well using hands if necessary.
The batter is very stiff.
Press mixture into two medium sized tube pans, greased and wax paper lined.
Bake in 250° preheated oven on high rack for one hour.
Reduce heat to 200° and continue baking for approximately 3 hours.
Yield:
Approximately 10 pounds.

title: no guilt brownies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Over very low heat, melt chocolate; cool slightly.
In food processor, puree all ingredients except chocolate and powdered sugar until smooth.
Add melted chocolate. Blend well.
Pour into lightly buttered 8-inch square pan.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.
Makes 16 brownies, each with 107 calories, 3 grams fat, 1 mg cholesterol, 69 mg potassium and 3 grams protein.

title: cream of persian soup
directions: Cook vegetables in water until tender. Set aside. Melt butter and margarine in large pot. Saut celery and onion in butter until tender. Add flour to butter mixture and stir until smooth. Add bouillon cubes (crushed) and milk. Stir until smooth. Stir in vegetables and liquid. Add ham, pepper, Accent and salt. Stir and let thicken.

title: annie craver's sugar cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Cut in shortening.
Add eggs and milk; mix together.
Put in refrigerator for 2 hours.
On a floured board, roll out dough very thin.
Cut into desired shapes and decorate.
Place on an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until golden brown at 350°.

title: knudsen icebox cottage cheese cake(no baking)
directions: Drain cottage cheese and beat until smooth.
Mix gelatin, sugar and salt in top of double boiler.
Beat egg yolks and milk and add to gelatin mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, about 10 minutes until gelatin is dissolved and mixture thickens.
Remove from heat.
Stir in lemon rind and cool.
Add cottage cheese, lemon juice and vanilla and cool, stirring occasionally, until mixture mounds slightly when dropped from a spoon.
Fold stiffly beaten egg whites and whipped cream into chilled cottage cheese mixture.
Turn into an 8-inch spring-form pan.

title: rhubarb pudding
directions: Sift together dry ingredients.
Mix in milk.
Stir in the rhubarb.
Place in buttered baking dish and pour over it the sauce made by boiling together a few minutes the brown sugar, water and butter.
Bake in a 375° oven for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine cake mix, beaten egg and melted butter in bowl; mix well.
Press into a 9 x 13-inch baking pan sprayed with nonstick cooking spray.
Combine cream cheese, remaining 2 eggs, lemon juice and confectioners sugar in bowl; mix well.
Spread into prepared pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes; cool.
Cut into squares.
Garnish with additional confectioners sugar.
Yield:
15 servings.

title: firecracker wings
directions: In a large bowl, combine hot sauce, dressing mix, margarine, Worcestershire sauce and honey. Set aside.
Cut off and discard bony wing tip from wings.
In a Dutch oven, heat oil for deep fat frying to 350°.
Fry wings until crispy. Dip wings in sauce and serve.

title: crustless egg custard
directions: Beat eggs.
Mix sugar and flour and add to beaten eggs. Slowly add milk and vanilla.
Mix well and add melted butter. Pour into a greased pie plate and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until firm.

title: grasshopper pie(serves 8)
directions: Mix cookies and butter.
Press into bottom and sides of a 9-inch pie pan.
Place marshmallows and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat until melted.
Cool.
Stir in creme de menthe and creme de cacao.
Chill over ice water until partially thickened. Fold in whipping cream.

title: oven baked finnish pancakes
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in 9-inch round pan in 425° oven.
Meanwhile, beat eggs with honey, salt and milk.
Add remaining 2 tablespoons butter, softened, and flour to egg mixture, blending until smooth.

title: rabbit sauce piquante
directions: Fry each piece of rabbit until golden brown in deep fat. Remove rabbit and set aside. Retain 6 to 8 tablespoons oil.
Into oil, add chopped onions and fry until onions begin to curl. Add tomatoes and garlic; cook until fat floats on top.
Add fried rabbit, salt, Tony's Creole seasoning to taste and pepper.
Cover with hot water. Cook slowly for 2 hours or until rabbit is tender, adding water as needed.
Cook sauce until thick.
Just before serving, add minced parsley and onion tops and cook 10 minutes longer. Serve with steamed rice.

title: puffy fish topping
directions: Whisk ingredients together.
Place on fish last 5 to 10 minutes of broiling.

title: grandma's sweet potato pudding
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grate sweet potatoes.
Put in casserole dish the margarine, sugar, cinnamon, nutmeg, egg and milk. Gradually mix in the flour.

title: campfire potato casserole
directions: Slice all vegetables into a piece of heavy-duty foil that has been sprayed with cooking spray.
Dot with margarine.
Place foil packet in coals.
Cook slowly so that potatoes get cooked thoroughly.

title: rice and chicken
directions: Use 2 to 3 tablespoons liquid from mushrooms.
Cook chicken; chop meat.
Cook rice as directed.
Saute onions in butter; blend flour, soup and milk.
Add mushrooms and salt and pepper to taste. Alternate layers in an 11 x 7-inch casserole.
Layer rice, chicken, sauce and cheese.
Bake at 300° for 30 to
40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: crispy kraut salad
directions: Drain kraut well.
Meanwhile chop onion, celery and green pepper.
Mix the dressing from vinegar, oil and sugar.
Blend all ingredients together and marinate for an hour or longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken rollantini with pesto
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut pocket in each chicken breast; roll a piece of ham around each piece of Mozzarella cheese.
Smear inside of chicken pocket with 1 1/2 teaspoons Pesto.
Place ham and cheese roll in pocket and press together.
Dredge chicken in flour; shake off excess.
Dip in egg; dredge in bread crumbs.

title: gingerbread
directions: Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: swiss meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat egg in a large bowl.
Add evaporated milk, sage, salt and pepper and mix.
Add beef and crumbs, 1/2 cup of the cheese and the onion; blend.
Form into a loaf and place in 2-quart rectangular baking dish.
Arrange bacon pieces on top.
Bake for 40 minutes.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup of cheese on top and bake 10 minutes longer.

title: mom's spanish rice
directions: Fry bacon; drain most of grease.
Saute onions in bacon grease; throw in peppers (saute peppers short time only) and celery.
Add can of tomatoes and water; bring to boil.
Add chili powder first.
Add rice, cover and let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese; cover until melted.

title: dorito chicken
directions: Stew chicken with celery; cool, bone and cube.
In large bowl, mix crushed Doritos, grated cheese, onion, both soups, bell pepper and tomatoes.
Add diced chicken; mix well.
Put into casserole dish; top with grated cheese.
Put into oven and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: poppy seed muffins
directions: Cream butter.
Gradually add sugar; beat well with electric mixer.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each.
Add sour cream and vanilla.
Combine flour, soda, salt and poppy seed; add to creamed mixture.
Spoon into greased muffin pans, filling 2/3 full.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes, or until golden.
Remove from pans immediately.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown hamburger; drain.
Add taco seasoning (reserve 1 tablespoon for dressing).
Use large bowl and layer salad ingredients in bowl, starting with lettuce and ending with cheese. Cover and refrigerate.
At serving time, toss with dressing and chips.

title: yippee yogurt pops
directions: You will need ten 3 ounce cold drink cups* and 10 wooden sticks.

title: fresh fruit pie
directions: Bake pie shell; fill 1/2 full of fruit.
Cook until clear the sugar, water and cornstarch, then add jello.
Stir and cool.
Pour over fruit and chill.
May garnish with Cool Whip.

title: brownies
directions: Melt butter in mixing bowl.
Stir in cocoa until dissolved. Add sugar and beaten eggs.
Mix well.
Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Add flour mixture to cocoa mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla and nuts.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan, greased and dusted with flour.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter; add beef stock, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Cover and simmer 45 minutes.

title: fantastic bars
directions: Melt margarine and mix in flour and nuts.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish and bake at 375° for 15 minutes; cool.
Mix confectioners sugar, cream cheese and 1 cup Cool Whip.
Spread on cooled crust.
Mix pudding and milk.
Spread on cream cheese mixture.
Let stand until firm.
Cover with Cool Whip and garnish with finely chopped nuts.

title: cooked crawdads
directions: Wash crawdads and pinch off their tails.
Discard everything but the tails.
Pull the mud veins out of the tails.
Put a large cooker of water on to boil.
Add onions, seasoning salt and hot sauce to taste.
When water comes to a boil, add crawdad tails. Boil for about 10 minutes and eat.
All you do is tear the meat out of the shells.
This is a tried and true recipe.
We were all at Donald Lee's and Darlene's and Muggsy wanted to have a turtle fry.
The fellers caught turtles and we went to Indian Creek to get the crawdads. Muggsy fried the turtle.
We all guessed at what to do with the crawdads.
They tasted delicious.
Muggsy said that Justin Wilson couldn't have done better.

title: puffy corn
directions: Boil butter, sugar and Karo for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove syrup from heat and add vanilla and baking soda.
Pour mixture over Puffin Corn and stir.
Bake corn for 1 hour at 225°, stirring every 15 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.

title: fudge
directions: Cook the sugar and milk for 5 minutes in a 3-quart saucepan .
Add the remaining ingredients.
Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Combine butter and potatoes while hot.
Then add sugar and eggs.
Mix and add cocoa.
Combine flour and spices.
Then add it to cocoa mixture.
Add vanilla, nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Grease and flour 3 pans.

title: portuguese sausage soup
directions: Remove casings from sausages.
Crumble meat into Dutch oven or heavy kettle and saute until browned.
Drain off fat.
Add all remaining ingredients to sausage.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and simmer, covered, for 30 minutes or until all vegetables are tender.
Serves 8.

title: leek soup
directions: Clean leeks by cutting off tops almost down to the white. Slice down in 1/4-inch slices. Saute in a large saucepan in the butter until just soft. Add the chicken broth and the potatoes. Begin simmering. Cut up the kielbasa into bite-sized pieces. Roll the sausage into tiny balls and simmer in water until cooked. Add both meats to the soup. Chop spinach and add to mixture along with the caraway and cumin. Simmer until potatoes are soft. Just before serving, add the cream.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Mix Jello per directions on boxes.
Stir in package of mini-marshmallows.	Cool, but do not let set.
Mix drained pineapple with softened cream cheese.
Stir in nuts, and add this mixture to the jello mixture. Stir to mix.	Pour into a 2 inch deep dish.	Let set.
Cut into squares to serve.

title: best ever lemon pie
directions: In double boiler, combine cornstarch, sugar and water.
cook, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Add salt, lemon juice and rind.
Continue cooking and stirring until mixture is blended.
Beat eggs (yolks) until lemon color.
Pour mixture over egg yolks, stirring constantly.
Return to hot water.
Cook 4 minutes.
Add butter.
Blend well.
Remove and let cool, then pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites and 6 tablespoons sugar until peaks.
Spread over pie; bake 15 minutes at 325°.

title: cinnamon tortillas and fruit salsa
directions: Tortillas:
Spray tortillas with water; sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Cut tortillas into 8 triangular pieces.
Bake until brown.

title: cheese bread
directions: Mix milk, egg and biscuit mix.
Add parsley, onion and 1/2 cup of cheese.
Pour into greased 8 or 9-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/2 cup cheese on batter.
Pour melted butter over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Serve with ham, chili and Mexican dishes.

title: heavenly fruit salad
directions: Dissolve pudding in pineapple and peach juice.
Add pineapple, peaches, apricots and bananas.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes in skin (not too well done).
Peel and grate coarsely.
Season with salt, pepper, onions and sour cream.
Add cheese and melted butter; mix lightly.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: triple flavored big batch cookies
directions: In bowl, stir together the flour, oats, unsweetened cocoa powder, baking soda and salt.
In a mixing bowl, beat the butter and peanut butter with an electric mixer.
Add the sugar and brown sugar; beat until combined.
Add the eggs and vanilla.
Beat the mixture well.
Add the dry ingredients and stir until combined. Stir in the semi-sweet chocolate pieces.
Drop by generous teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake in a 350° oven 12 to 14 minutes or until done.
Let cool for 1 minute on cookie sheet before removing to wire rack.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions and add a small amount of salt.
Drain.
Add mayonnaise, soup, onion and eggs. Mix well.
Pour into a greased 2-quart casserole and top with crumbs and grated cheese.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: seven seas casserole
directions: Combine soup, onion, water, lemon juice, salt and pepper in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil over medium heat.
Pour half of the soup mixture into a greased 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
In layers, add rice (right from box), peas and tuna.
Add remaining soup.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Cover and bake at 375°.

title: christmas salad
directions: Mix all ingredients and refrigerate until being served.
May also be frozen until needed.

title: congo bars
directions: Cream shortening and sugar; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Sift dry ingredients together and add.
Add nuts and chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes in a pan, 10 1/4 x 15 1/4-inch or bake for 35 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan. The smaller pan will make thicker bars.

title: peach delight
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in saucepan.
When it comes to a boil remove from heat and beat in flour until smooth. Add nuts.
Spread in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake in oven for 12 minutes at 350°.
Cool completely.

title: sweet potato raisin patties
directions: Mash the potatoes and beat in egg.
Mix in raisins.
Drop from tablespoon into a heated greased frypan.
Brown slowly on both sides.
Makes 12 patties.

title: cookies for santa
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients at medium speed.
Shape dough into a ball and refrigerate for 2 hours or more.
Roll dough approximately 1/4-inch apart.
Glaze with egg white and water mixture.
Sprinkle with your choice toppings.

title: fruit sherbet
directions: Boil sugar and water.
Add the juices and the bananas.

title: p. j.'s lemon pie
directions: Mix all in a bowl (mixer optional).
Spoon into crust.
Place in freezer for 30 minutes, minimum.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Mix together sugar, water and Karo syrup.
Bring to soft boil. Beat 2 egg whites while syrup is boiling.
When egg whites are well beaten, add 1/2 of the sugar mixture.
Continue to beat egg whites and syrup while rest of the syrup is boiling to a hard crack stage.
Add to the egg whites and beat well.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Drop on wax paper when mixture begins to thicken.

title: pear pineapple jelly
directions: Boil pears, pineapple and sugar for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and add 1 large box of orange jello.
Pour into jelly jars.

title: popcorn cake
directions: In large bowl combine the popcorn, peanuts, pecans and candy. In a double boiler melt oil, butter and marshmallows until smooth. Pour this mixture over popcorn mixture and stir until coated. Press mixture into pan. Cover with plastic wrap and let set overnight. Turn out and eat.

title: ted's fruit cake
directions: Put Brazil nuts, dates and cherries into large bowl.
Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt over nuts and fruit.
Mix until nuts and fruit are coated.
Beat eggs until foamy.
Add vanilla.
Stir into nut-fruit mixture until well mixed.
Turn into greased and wax paper lined pan, 9 1/4 x 5 1/2 x 2 1/2-inch. Spread evenly in pan.
Bake in slow oven, 300°, for 1 hour and 45 minutes.
Cake must be cooled before slicing.
If desired, cut in half and wrap as two separate gift cakes.
Makes one 3 pound cake. This recipe is over 30 years old; very good.

title: cream sauce
directions: Melt butter.
Remove from heat and add flour and salt.
Blend well.
Slowly add milk.
Return to fire and bring to a boil for 1 minute.
(If milk does not "mix-in", place pan on very low heat, stirring constantly until butter melts and flour mixes with liquids.)
Add more milk to make a thinner sauce.
Add more flour and butter to make a thicker sauce.

title: mexican casserole(serves 6 to 8)
directions: In a large skillet, cook beef, celery and onion until meat is browned; drain.
Stir in taco mix, water, beans and green chilies if desired; mix well.
Pour into a 2 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 30 minutes or until heated through.
Top with cheese, green onions, tomatoes, olives and chips.

title: japanese fried pork chops
directions: Remove fat from pork chops; score each piece, making diamond-shaped cuts.
Pound pieces to about 1/8-inch thick. Place in a shallow baking dish.

title: fruit nut nibbles
directions: Mix cereal, peanuts and banana chips in 3-quart casserole dish or bowl.
Mix margarine, honey, cinnamon and salt; pour over cereal mixture, tossing until evenly coated.
Microwave on High for 3 to 4 minutes, stirring after 2 minutes until toasted.
Watch carefully so mixture does not burn.

title: peachy delight
directions: Mix all ingredients for first layer and spread in 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake 350 for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: sausage and pepper sandwiches
directions: Cook sausage in a large skillet with 3/4 cup water, 10 to 15 minutes, until browned.
Remove and cut into 1/2-inch pieces. Discard liquid.

title: eggy thingys
directions: Heat 8-inch skillet on medium heat.
Lay bread on cutting board.
With 12 ounce glass, place on center of bread and twist until donut hole appears.
Now eat donut hole.
Butter bread (both sides).
Place in pan, crack 1 egg to pour into center of hole.

title: sweet-sour potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes in their jackets.
When tender, peel and dice. Add celery, hard-cooked eggs, onion, pickle and parsley.
Fry bacon until crisp and brown.

title: oyster cracker nibbles
directions: Combine oil, dressing mix, garlic salt, dill weed and lemon pepper.
Stir well until dry mix is dissolved.
Add crackers and toss to mix well.
Toss several times at intervals until oil is absorbed.
Store in airtight container.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together (it will be soupy).
Pour into a large, ungreased roaster pan.
Bake uncovered at 350 for 1 hour or until brown.

title: cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Divide dough in half.
Make into 2 rolls.
Wrap in waxed paper and freeze.
Slice and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until light brown.

title: mock chop suey
directions: Brown ground beef.
Prepare rice according to normal directions.
Combine ground beef, rice, can of cream of mushroom soup, onion and celery in a 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle chow mein noodles over the top.
Bake in a 350° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: mustard dip
directions: Mix
dry
ingredients
and
then
eggs and the liquids. Cook over low heat to thicken.
Stir constantly and let cool; then serve.

title: margaret's red velvet cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar, eggs and coloring together.
Add dry ingredients alternately with buttermilk.
Add vanilla.
Bake in 3 layers at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: one step lasagne(microwave)
directions: You will need a 12 x 7-inch micro-proof baking dish.

title: meal-in-a-minute
directions: Brown beef in butter; pour off grease. Season with salt and pepper; add vegetable soup and string beans. Pour into casserole and top with creamed potatoes. Brown in oven and serve immediately.

title: mississippi pecan pie
directions: Beat together first 6 ingredients.
Mix in pecans.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Cook in preheated 350° oven for 40 minutes or until a thin knife, when inserted, comes out clean.

title: blueberry cobbler
directions: Cover
bottom of an 8-inch square pan with blueberries. Mix 3/4
cup
of sugar, butter, baking powder, salt, milk and flour together
until
crumbly.
Pour
over blueberries.
Mix remaining sugar
and cornstarch; sprinkle over flour mixture. Pour
cup boiling
water
over top.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yields 9 servings.

title: whoopie pies
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: cream cheese danish
directions: Cream together all ingredients. Set aside.
Roll out one can of rolls and place in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place mixture on top of rolls and cover with the second can of rolls.
You may want to press out the second can of rolls so you can cover complete top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: do bake cookies
directions: Bring sugar, buttermilk and cocoa to a full boil.
Boil for 2 minutes, remove from heat and add peanut butter, oats, vanilla. Spoon on wax paper to cool.

title: mexican meat
directions: Combine all ingredients in a pressure cooker and cook for about 1 hour. Or, cook in a large pot, covered until meat falls apart. After this mixture is cooked, shred the meat. If too much liquid remains, simmer uncovered until liquid cooks away. Taste to test seasoning and add desired additional seasonings before simmering away the liquid. This meat can be used for anything-enchiladas, tacos, nachos, tostados, huevos, etc.

title: chicken cheese balls
directions: Combine cream cheese, steak sauce and curry powder in bowl. Mix well.
Add chicken, celery and parsley.
Mix well.
Shape into balls.
Roll in a mixture of pecans and parsley.
Chill until firm.
Serve with crackers.

title: spicy meat loaf americana
directions: About 2 hours before serving, in 10-inch skillet over medium-high heat, in hot salad oil, cook onion, pepper, celery and garlic until vegetables are tender and lightly browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove 2 tablespoons vegetable mixture; reserve for garnish.
Into vegetables remaining in skillet, stir nutmeg and 1 1/2 teaspoons salt.
Cook 1 minute.
Remove skillet from heat.

title: patsy's walnut bran muffins
directions: Combine eggs and milk in a large, wide bowl.
Beat vigorously. Add cinnamon and beat again to absorb most of the cinnamon. Place a little cooking oil on a hot griddle at medium heat.
Dip a slice of bread at a time in the egg mixture, covering both sides. With fork and thumb, remove each slice from mixture and place on the hot griddle.
Cook each side until it is a golden brown. Remove to a platter.

title: oven roasted potatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 450.
In 13 x 9 baking pan combine all ingredients until all potatoes are evenly coated.
Bake uncovered, stirring occasionally 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender and golden brown.
4 servings.

title: crescent palmiers
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Sprinkle 1 1/2 tablespoons sugar on a cutting board; separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Press perforations to seal.
Lightly press dough into sugar and brush top of rectangles with the melted oleo, then sprinkle with remaining sugar.
Using two rectangles, place one on top of the other. Starting with the shortest sides, roll up both ends jelly roll fashion to meet in the center.
Cut into 8 slices.
Repeat with the remaining two rectangles, making 16 slices in all.
Place, cut side down, on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Brush with remaining oleo. Bake for 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown.
Remove immediately from cookie sheet and allow to cool completely.

title: easy lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs.
Mix egg yolks, lemon juice and milk.
Pour into graham cracker crust.
Beat egg whites until fluffy.
Add 3 tablespoons sugar and 1/4 teaspoon cream of tartar.
Beat a few more minutes.
Put on pie and brown at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: country style chicken kiev
directions: Heat oven to 375°.
Melt margarine.
Combine bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, basil, oregano, garlic salt and salt.
Dip chicken in melted margarine; coat with crumb mixture.
Reserve the remaining margarine.
Place chicken on ungreased baking pan.
Bake for 50 to 60 minutes or until fork-tender.

title: sunday morning casserole
directions: Beat eggs, milk, dry mustard and oil in mixing bowl. Butter a 9 x 13 glass dish. Layer bread, cheese, sausage, green onion and pour egg mixture on top. Refrigerate overnight. Remove 10 minutes prior to baking. Bake, uncovered at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until eggs are done.

title: old fashioned chocolate frosting
directions: Melt cocoa and butter, adding all other ingredients slowly. Boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute.
Will frost a 2-layer cake.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until fluffy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla.
Stir in zucchini.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into 2 floured and greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° about 45 minutes.

title: tasty broiled hamburgers
directions: Combine meat, seasonings, grated onion and milk thoroughly. Split buns and spread each half with meat mixture, spreading well to the edge.
Arrange buns on broiler rack.
Insert broiler pan and rack so the meat is 2 or 3 inches from heat.
Broil 10 minutes.
Serve with tomato slices and lettuce.
Serves 6.

title: chicken almond casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except Cheddar cheese and potato chips. Put in casserole.
Cover with cheese and chips.
Bake, uncovered, at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: old-fashioned maple pie
directions: Place the flour and salt into a bowl; stir in sugar.
Cut in half the butter or margarine with the lard until the mixture resembles fine cornmeal.
Add enough iced water to mix to a firm dough.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables.
Mix together oil, vinegar, sugar, salt and pepper.
Bring this mixture to a boil, then cool in refrigerator.
Pour over vegetables; stir and refrigerate overnight.
Will keep for 2 weeks!

title: mexican cornbread with ground meat
directions: Mix corn meal, eggs, milk, soda, salt, corn and drippings and set aside.
Saute ground meat and put on absorbent paper to drain. Prepare onion, cheese and peppers in separate mounds.
Grease a large iron skillet and heat.
Sprinkle a very thin layer of corn meal in the skillet and let brown slightly.
Pour half the batter in skillet; sprinkle the grated cheese evenly over the batter, then the meat, next the chopped onions and finely the jalapeno peppers. Pour remaining batter on top.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: peanut butter icebox pie
directions: Blend and pour into graham cracker pie crust; top with Cool Whip.

title: chinese barbecued pork
directions: Combine all ingredients in Ziploc bag.
Add pork; mix well and refrigerate 3 to 10 hours (or overnight), turning occasionally. Drain pork, reserving marinade.
Place pork on wire rack over baking pan.
Bake in preheated oven (350°), turning and basting often until cooked through, approximately 45 to 60 minutes.
Slice into thin diagonal slices.

title: foolproof fudge
directions: Combine chips, salt, condensed milk and vanilla in large microwave-safe bowl.
Cook on High
for up to 3 minutes.
Stir to melt any whole chips.
Add nuts if desired.
Spread evenly into wax paper lined 8-inch square pan.
Chill 2 hours or more.
Turn onto board; peel off paper.
Cut in 1-inch squares.

title: mints for showers and weddings
directions: Mash cream cheese and add flavoring and coloring.
Mix in powdered sugar and then knead with hands until the consistency of pie dough.
Roll into marble size balls and dip into granulated sugar.
Press sugared side into candy molds and unmold onto waxed paper.
Makes about 25 roses and 25 leaves.

title: next best thing to magnum p.i.  cake
directions: Bottom Layer:
Blend first 4 ingredients.
Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch or larger pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes (less time in glass pan).

title: tamale bake
directions: Saute ground beef with onions, pepper and celery in skillet until crumbly.
Combine corn meal and tomatoes in saucepan.
Cook 5 to 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Add to ground beef mixture. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Mix well.
Pour into greased casserole.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: seafood delight
directions: Butter large shallow casserole.
Line with asparagus.
Sprinkle some cheese over top.
Cover with crab and shrimp.
Sprinkle with cheese.
Cover with drained mushrooms and mushroom soup to which lemon juice and dry mustard have been added.
Also add salt, pepper and sherry.
Scatter almonds and bread crumbs on top.
Add the rest of cheese and paprika.
Cover tightly with foil and bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Brown under broiler until brown.
Can make day ahead and store in refrigerator.

title: tender beef pot roast
directions: Place beef in a shallow roasting pan. Sprinkle beef with lemon juice; pierce with a fork. Cover and refrigerate until ready to roast.

title: hamburger and corn casserole
directions: Brown first 3 ingredients together and drain.
Cook noodles, but don't overcook.
Drain.
Mix everything together.
Top with buttered bread crumbs if desired.
Bake for 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: buttermilk biscuits(best)
directions: Combine dry ingredients and cut in shortening. Add buttermilk and mix with fork just until holds shape.
Mix lightly with hands about 10 times.
Pat dough down to about 1/2-inch thickness.
Cut out in rounds.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet in a 450° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: * We use all or half butter Crisco.

title: corn pudding
directions: Combine corn, sour cream, butter and eggs. Mix well. Then fold in corn mix.
Pour into 9 x 13 casserole dish. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: monkey cake
directions: Cut biscuits into quarters and shake a few at a time in a bag with cinnamon and sugar.
Place in a well-greased tube pan.
Bring to boil 1 cup sugar and 1 1/2 sticks butter.
Pour over biscuits. Bake for 35 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Remove from pan immediately. Cool; pick apart with fingers.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli in broth about 3 minutes.
Add soup.
Add drained carrots.
Cut Velveeta up in cubes.
Add to soup mixture, stirring until melted.
Add chicken near end.

title: chess squares
directions: Spread cake mix, butter and 1 egg in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix cream cheese, eggs and sugar and spread over cake mixture. Bake at 325° for 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: quick candied yams
directions: Place yams in shallow dish.
Combine syrup, sugar and butter in a saucepan, stirring to a boil.
Pour over yams.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, basting frequently.

title: "dip"
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill before serving.

title: tuna casserole
directions: Cook and drain noodles.
Put 1 layer of noodles and 1 can of tuna in bottom of baking dish.
Cover with 1/2 can of cream of celery soup, another layer of noodles and tuna with rest of celery soup on top.
Put crushed chips on top and put tomato soup, mixed and heated with 1 can water, on top of all.
Bake at 375° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: chewy squares
directions: Set oven to 350°.
Cream 1/2 cup margarine in a bowl; add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Mix.
Melt remaining 1/2 cup margarine and chocolate in a saucepan over low heat.
When melted, add to first mixture; mix well.
Add sifted flour and salt to mixture; mix well. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Sprinkle coconut and cinnamon evenly over top.
Bake about 45 minutes; cool in pan.
Cut in 1 1/2-inch squares.
Makes about 60 pieces.

title: scalloped cabbage
directions: Cook cabbage for seven minutes.
Mix all ingredients and put buttered bread crumbs over top.
Bake about 1/2 hour.

title: blender pancakes or waffles
directions: Add ingredients one at a time to blender; blend at high speed. Use
a spatula to scrape sides; blend more.
Set aside for a few minutes.
Use a hot griddle or waffle iron.

title: peanut butter crispies
directions: Combine butter, sugar and
corn
syrup
in
a saucepan. Bring to a rolling boil.
Remove
from heat and stir in peanut butter, cereal
and
vanilla.
Drop by teaspoonful onto waxed paper, or can be spread in buttered pan and cut in squares.

title: ice cream cake 2
directions: Mix Oreos with 1/2 stick melted butter.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add ice cream.
Freeze.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Blend soup, milk, salt and pepper.
In buttered 1 1/2-quart casserole, alternate layers of potatoes and sauce.
Dot top with butter and cover.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Uncover; bake 15 minutes more or until potatoes are done.

title: chipped ham barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients except ham and rolls, then add ham.
Cook on high for 1 hour, then 1 hour to all day on low.
Ham can be added throughout day.
Can easily be doubled.

title: crab soup
directions: In soup pot, combine water, tomatoes, bouillon cubes, Old Bay and pepper.
Bring to a boil.
Add onion, celery and cabbage and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes.
Add crabmeat and continue cooking for 10 minutes more.
Can be made a day ahead and refrigerated overnight.
Better flavor when reheated.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: broccoli-corn bake
directions: Mix broccoli and corn in casserole dish.
Stir in eggs and onion.
Melt the 4 tablespoons margarine and stir in stuffing mix. Spread stuffing mix over top of casserole and bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: fruity-cherry punch
directions: Combine strawberries, bananas, orange juice and lemonade in container of electric blender; blend until smooth.
Combine soft drink mix, sugar and water, stirring until sugar is dissolved. Add fruit mixture, stirring well.
Just before serving, add ginger ale.
Yields about 6 quarts.

title: lemon poppy seed bread
directions: Cream softened butter, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, baking powder, milk, lemon juice and poppy seed.
Spray loaf pan with nonstick spray.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.
Let cool.
Stick top all over with toothpick if glazing.

title: fabulous cherry coke salad
directions: Drain fruit juices in pot.
Add Cherry Coke, bring to boil. Dissolve Jell-O in boiling liquid.
Mix well.
Set aside to cool. Cut cream cheese into small pieces.
Pour Jell-O mixture into a casserole dish or large mold.
Add nuts, fruit, and cream cheese pieces.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: best ever hickory nut cake
directions: Cream together the sugar and butter.
Add eggs.
Beat on medium speed of mixer for 2 minutes.
Mix dry ingredients together lightly.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk; mix well. Stir in vanilla and nuts.
Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool.
Frost with Penuche Frosting.

title: maryland crab cakes
directions: In a bowl, mix bread crumbs, egg, mayonnaise and seasonings. Add crabmeat and mix gently but thoroughly.
Shape into 6 cakes. Fry in hot oil (350°) until browned.

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon. Set aside. Mix eggs and sugar.
Add oil.
Mix in carrots and nuts. Add dry ingredients, blending well.
Bake at 350° in greased 10 x 14-inch pan until golden brown (50 minutes).

title: jam cake
directions: Mix all dry ingredients together.
Add other ingredients with beaten eggs.
Bake in layers or loaf.
Bake at 350° until toothpick comes out clean.

title: mincemeat pie(makes 2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs slightly; add sugar and Karo.
Then mix in mincemeat, raisins, nuts, vanilla and juices.
Pour in 2 unbaked pie shells and put crusts on top; bake at 350° until done.
Makes 2 pies.

title: italian salad dressing
directions: Blend in food processor, blender or in a shaker.
If using processor, garlic is minced with a metal blade.
Makes 8 servings.

title: irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees. Mix together melted margarine, eggs and milk. Then mix in dry ingredients. Grease and flour 13 inch loaf pan. Bake 45 - 60 minutes.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Combine in bowl of electric mixer flour, soda, salt, baking powder, sugar and margarine.
Beat at medium speed until mixture is of a mealy consistency.
Slowly add the buttermilk, vanilla and mashed banana.
Mix 4 minutes or until light and fluffy.
Add the slightly beaten eggs in two parts, beating after each addition; fold in nuts.
Place in two greased and floured 9-inch pans.
Bake at 350° until cake is brown and springs back when touched lightly, about 25 minutes.
Remove cake from pan as soon as taken from oven. Cool, top side up, on a wire rack or towel.

title: phillipine egg rolls
directions: Fry onion until limp.
Add meat, celery, carrot, garlic salt and soy sauce.
Brown; drain off grease.
Add bean sprouts; mix well.
Taste and add more seasonings if desired.
Spoon a small amount of filling on each egg roll wrapper.
Fold 2 opposite sides over and about 3/4 inch each.
Then roll up according to illustration on package.
Seal edge with water.
(Dip your finger in water, then run along edge of wrapper and seal.)
Heat 1/2 inch of oil in frying pan on medium high.
Add 4 egg rolls and brown on both sides lightly.
Repeat until all are cooked.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve with duck sauce.

title: death by chocolate
directions: In glass bowl, layer 1/2 brownies, 1/2 pudding, 1/2 whipped topping and 3 crushed Heath bars.
Repeat layers.
Keep refrigerated until ready to serve.

title: taco dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and serve with warm chips.

title: sandies
directions: Cream together first 4 ingredients.
Add flour until dough doesn't stick to your hands and is easy to roll into 3/4-inch bars. Work in chopped pecans and shape into crescents.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° approximately 30 minutes, or until lightly golden.
After cookies are cooled, roll in powdered sugar gently because they break easily.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix and serve. Very easy and quick.

title: salade nicoise
directions: Place the potato in a small heavy saucepan.
Add enough unsalted water to
cover
and
bring to a boil over moderately high heat.	Cover
and
cook until the potato is tender, about 20 minutes; drain.
Let
stand
until	cool
enough to handle. Peel the potato, cut
it into 1/2-inch cubes and place it in a large bowl.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Bake the crescent rolls at 350° for 12 minutes; let cool.
Mix the cream cheese dressing, Miracle Whip and milk together and spread mixture onto crust.
Top the pizza with the chopped vegetables and shredded cheese.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Grease a 9 x 12-inch oven dish.
Spread rice over bottom.
Add mushroom soup.
Add legs or thighs.
Sprinkle onion soup over. Add orange juice over all.
Cover and bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: zucchini stew
directions: In 5-quart kettle combine tomatoes, onions, celery, peppers and spices.
Cook on medium heat 35 minutes.
Cut bacon into small pieces.
Fry to brown and crispy.
Add drained bacon and 2 tablespoons grease to stew.

title: angela's tortellini salad *
directions: Cook tortellini.
Add all ingredients except seasonings. Season to taste with salt, pepper, Italian seasoning and garlic powder.

title: real texas chili
directions: Cut beef in bite size chunks.
Brown in oil.
Add garlic, spices and flour.
Stir in beef broth last.
Simmer about 3 hours, stirring occasionally and tasting for seasoning.
If desired, 1 can of chili beans and 1 cup of sour cream can be added.

title: mrs. lewis' rum cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Beat at medium speed until well creamed (about 5 to 10 minutes).
Add one egg yolk at a time, beating only until yolk is broken.
Sift dry ingredients together and stir into batter along with rum extract.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into cake mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup chopped nuts on bottom of a well-greased and floured tube pan, then pour in the cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Sift together all dry ingredients.
Make a well in center. Add eggs and oil, stirring just until evenly moistened.
Stir in strawberries and nuts.
Pour into 2 greased 8-inch loaf pans. Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Let stand overnight before slicing.

title: warm cider
directions: Mix juices in percolator.
Mix other ingredients in basket of percolator.
Perk; when it stops, remove basket.
Makes 22 cups.

title: gazpacho
directions: Put oil, lemon juice, onion, celery, Tabasco, salt, peppers and chilies in blender or food processor.
Add beef broth and process.
Put tomato juice in a gallon container.
Add mixture from blender and stir.
Put chopped cucumber and tomatoes on top. Refrigerate.
Stir before ladling into bowls.
Serve with croutons on top.
Makes a delicious summer meal.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Combine 1 cup butter, 3 teaspoons vanilla, 1/4 cup cocoa, 1 cup nuts and next 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Mix well.
Pour into a large greased and floured baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until cake is done.

title: coconut pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour a tube pan.
Cream together the butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add flour and eggs alternately, mixing well.
Beat in remaining ingredients. Pour into prepared pan and bake for about 1 hour.
Cool on rack 5 minutes and turn onto serving platter.
Yields 16 slices.

title: cherry surprise
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Add eggs one at a time and lemon juice.
Add flour and baking powder.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread with cherry pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: sawdust salad
directions: First, dissolve box of lemon jello and box of orange jello in hot boiling water, then add cold water and bananas (chopped up). Add pineapple (drained) and add miniature marshmallows.
Second, cook until thickens, sugar, flour, egg and pineapple juice.
Let cool.
Spread over jello.
Third, mix Dream Whip and cream cheese; beat together and spread over mixture.
Cheese on top.

title: ann's peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in milk.
Cook to soft ball stage (234° on candy thermometer) in cold water.
Remove from heat. Stir in vanilla and peanut butter.
Beat until mixture loses its gloss.
Pour quickly into greased pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: veal florentine
directions: Pound or flatten veal.
Dredge in flour.
Make egg batter with eggs, grated cheese and parsley.
Dip cutlets in egg batter and panfry.
Remove meat from pan. Add white wine and juice of lemons. Add precooked spinach.

title: laham mishwee (lamb shish-kabob)
directions: Pierce lamb and wedged onions alternately on skewer.
Place over charcoal fire, gas flames or under oven broiler until done.

title: icebox cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla and nuts alternately in layers.
First layer crumbs, then mixture and last crumbs.
Press firmly in pan and let stand in refrigerator 24 hours.
Serve with whipped cream.
Makes 8 servings.

title: christmas cheese ball
directions: Mix; refrigerate 24 hours.
Mold into ball.
Roll in parsley. Decorate with maraschino cherries.

title: chester sauce
directions: Process vegetables.
Sprinkle on salt.
Let stand 1 hour and drain.
Add vinegar and spices; cook until tender.
Put into hot sterile jars or process in hot water bath 10 to 15 minutes and seal.

title: cheesy meatloaf
directions: Preheat oven to 325 degrees; Mix all ingredients together except cheese and mushrooms in a large bowl.

Pat out into rectangle shape onto a piece of wax paper, similar to 13 x 9. Sprinkle cheese and mushrooms over this, holding one end of the wax paper, slowly rolling the cheese covered meat into a roll patting the ends to close and hold the cheese and mushrooms in as you roll. Put into a greased loaf pan and bake at 325 degrees for about 40 to 60 minutes.

title: sweet and sour sauce
directions: Mix pineapple preserves and mustard to taste.
Makes a great sweet and sour sauce for chicken or anything you want to eat it with.

title: swiss steak
directions: Combine flour, salt and pepper; pound into meat.
In Dutch oven or large skillet, melt butter over medium heat.
Add meat and brown on both sides, about 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients. Reduce heat, cover and simmer, stirring occasionally until beef is tender, about 1 hour.

title: 4 bean soup
directions: Put all beans, onions and Ro-Tel in large pot.
Bring to a boil with 3 cups water.
Turn down heat to simmer for 30 to 45 minutes. Add ground beef, all cut up hot dogs and smoked sausage.
Add to pot and cook on low heat for 30 more minutes.
Salt and pepper to taste.
I don't add salt and pepper until it's done for the dogs and sausage are already salty.

title: carrot casserole
directions: Cook carrots until soft (10 to 15 minutes); strain carrots. Mix with other ingredients.
Place in casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mollie's super dip
directions: Mix together cream cheese, sour cream, beans, enchilada mix and hot sauce.
Spread this mixture in 2 (8-inch) pie pans and cover with remaining cheeses.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°. Serves 8 to 12.
Serve with corn chips.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions.
Drain.
Put soup and cheese in separate pan and cook until cheese is melted.
Add broccoli and stir until covered in sauce.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Prepare stuffing according to directions and sprinkle on casserole.
Cook at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad supreme
directions: Dissolve raspberry gelatin in 1 cup boiling water.
Stir in pie filling. Turn into 9 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Chill until partially set.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream the sugar, Crisco and margarine.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla.
Add sifted flour, cocoa and baking powder. Add milk.
Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chow chow pickle
directions: Cut vegetables and mix together. Mix all the seasoning and add enough vinegar to make a smooth paste. Bring rest of vinegar to a boil and add the paste mixture to it. Cook slowly until it thickens. Add vegetables and cook until thoroughly heated. Boil for a few minutes. Add a few red peppers for color, and hot pepper to taste. Seal in pint jars.

title: russian tea
directions: Mix all ingredients together.

title: pistachio salad
directions: Stir pudding (dry) into undrained pineapple.
Add Cool Whip and marshmallows, then nuts.
Stir well and chill.

title: cranberry relish
directions: Mix together and let set
out on counter over night. Stir and put in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: cheese and egg biscuit wiches
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Prepare biscuits according to package directions.
In medium bowl, combine eggs, milk, green pepper and pepper.
Beat well.
In large skillet, melt margarine; stir in egg mixture.
Cook until set but moist, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat.
Cut cheese into 20 triangles.

title: sugared walnuts
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Melt butter in a 15-1/2 inch x 10-1/2 inch pan with sides (a jelly roll pan or cookie sheet).
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold sugar and salt into whites.
Fold in walnuts making sure they are all coated with the meringue.
Spread mixture over butter in pan.
Bake at 325° for about an hour, stirring every 10 minutes, until meringue is brown and all the butter is gone.
Cool and serve.

title: old-fashioned strawberry shortcake
directions: Set aside a few strawberries for garnishing.
In bowl, crush half of the remaining strawberries with a fork.
Slice remaining berries and stir into crushed berries with the 1/2 cup of sugar. Set aside.

title: buttermilk salad
directions: Cut up marshmallows, then pour buttermilk over marshmallows and let set overnight.
Make sauce of oleo, flour and pineapple juice.
Cool sauce and pour over marshmallows.
Add pineapple chunks cut in half and drained.
Add pecans and Cool Whip.
Fold all ingredients together.
Chill and serve.

title: cheesy california blend
directions: Boil the California Blend 8 to 10 minutes.
Put in casserole dish.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo with Velveeta cheese.
Pour over vegetables.
Melt 1/2 stick oleo and mix with crushed Ritz crackers.
Put on top of vegetables.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. This can be made the day before.

title: peanut butter whirler
directions: Place all ingredients in blender.
Blend until well mixed and smooth.
Serve in tall glass.

title: banana bread
directions: Mash bananas.
Save in 1 bowl.
Mix flour, salt, soda and wheat germ in another bowl; save.
Melt butter in a large bowl. Add eggs and one cup applesauce, then fold in flour mixture and bananas.
Lastly, bake in greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ann's crescent roll appetizers
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in 10-inch skillet and cook over medium heat until brown.
Drain off any excess fat.
Add cheese; stir until melted, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Preheat oven to 345°.
Separate dough into triangles.
Cut in half.
Spoon ingredients into triangles.
Fold edges well.
Bake on ungreased pan until golden brown, about 15 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen appetizers.

title: beef roast with mushroom onion gravy
directions: Place roast in slow cooker.
Sprinkle onion soup mix over roast.
Add both cans of mushroom soup.
Cover and cook on low for 8 hours.

title: dolly's icebox cake
directions: Place layer of graham crackers on bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Then spread cooked vanilla pudding over graham crackers. Put layer of sliced bananas over pudding.
Place another layer of graham crackers over bananas.
Spread cooked chocolate pudding over bananas.
Put layer of sliced bananas over pudding.
For topping, place a layer of crushed graham crackers.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Serve and enjoy.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Saute hamburger and onions.
Combine hamburger and onions with other ingredients in a large pot.
Bring to a boil; let simmer about 2 hours.
Cool and put in containers; freeze.
Makes about 5 quarts.

title: j. daniel's barbecue sauce
directions: Combine onion, garlic and J. Daniels in a 3-quart saucepan. Simmer about 10 minutes over low flame, then carefully light mixture to burn off liquid alcohol (about 20 seconds).
Add remaining ingredients.
Bring to boil.
Simmer 20 minutes, stirring constantly.
Strain to remove onion and garlic pieces, if you prefer a smoother sauce.
Refrigerating sauce for 1 to 2 days will increase tastiness.

title: monkey bread
directions: Put 1/2 cup sugar and 2 teaspoons cinnamon in a bag.
Cut biscuits into quarters.
Place in bag.
Shake pieces until all are coated.
Place dough into well-greased Bundt pan.
Melt butter, 1 teaspoon cinnamon and brown sugar in a saucepan.
Bring to a full boil for 1 minute.
Add nuts.
Pour sauce over dough.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Turn upside down on plate immediately. Don't cut apart, just break off in pieces to eat.

title: scotcheroos
directions: Cook sugar and Karo syrup in 3-quart pan, until sugar is dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and Rice Krispies.
Mix well and spread on greased 13 x 9-inch sheet.
Melt chocolate bits and the few butterscotch bits.
Pour over top.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Trim a thin slice from top and bottom of each tomato.
Cut tomatoes crosswise into 1/2-inch thick slices.
On large sheet of waxed paper, combine flour with 1/2 teaspoon salt.
In small bowl, beat eggs with sugar and remaining salt.
Dip tomato slices, coating completely.
Dip into egg mixture, then bread crumbs, coating completely.
Heat 1/4 cup oil in large skillet.
Add tomato slices; saute about 3 minutes on each side or until nicely browned. Add oil as needed.

title: taffel's salad
directions: Drain pineapple.
Use enough juice and water to make 1 1/2 cups.
Let the mixture boil and add to the jello.
Drop in marshmallows and dissolve.
Add pineapple, cottage cheese and nuts.
Do not add Cool Whip until mixture is completely cooled. Let stand in refrigerator 12 hours before serving.

title: party pumpkin popcorn
directions: Preheat oven to 250°.
Combine sugar, pumpkin, butter and corn syrup in medium saucepan; bring to boil, stirring constantly. Continue boiling 15 minutes over medium-low heat, stirring frequently.
Remove from heat; add salt, soda and cream of tartar, stirring until well-blended and foamy.
Stir in peanuts.
Pour over popcorn; toss until well coated.
Spread on two greased cookie sheets.
Bake 50 to 60 minutes or until golden brown, stirring every 15 minutes.
Remove immediately from cookie sheets.
Spread on foil, breaking popcorn into pieces.
Cool.
Coating will harden on cooling.
Yields 3 quarts.

title: auntie "a's" not so famous cucumber salad
directions: Make Jell-O mixture.
Add vinegar and onion.
Chill until syrupy.

title: pork tofu
directions: Place pork in a 3-quart microwave baking dish.
Cover and microwave on High power for 3 minutes.
Stir well, cover and microwave 3 more minutes or until pork is cooked.
Place tofu, chop suey vegetables, onions, mushrooms and ginger on pork.
In a small bowl, combine remaining ingredients and pour over tofu mixture.
Cover and microwave on High power for 6 more minutes. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: bark candy
directions: Line cookie sheet with foil and grease with oil or oleo (1-inch sides on cookie sheet).
Place crackers all over bottom of pan (to cover).
Melt oleo and brown sugar in small pan.
Cook for 3 minutes.
Pour mixture over crackers and bake at 400° for 6 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with chocolate chips; let melt, then spread around to cover top.
Let cool.
Then refrigerate until cold.
Break apart and store in container in refrigerator.

title: rum balls
directions: Measure all ingredients into a bowl; mix well.
By teaspoonful shape into balls.
Roll in confectioners sugar, instant coffee or dry cocoa.
Store in a tightly covered container.
Makes 50. Store at least a week to develop the best flavor.

title: snowballs
directions: Toast Rice Krispies in oven at 300° for a few minutes. Microwave almond bark, a few pieces at a time, until completely melted.
Stir all ingredients together; drop onto wax paper by teaspoon.

title: grandmother's cherry cobbler
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Cream butter and 1/2 cup sugar.
Add dry ingredients and milk.
Beat.
Pour batter into greased baking dish.
Put drained cherries on top.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup sugar.
Pour cherry juice over all and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
May microwave for 13 minutes instead of baking in oven.

title: pumpkin raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Lightly oil a 5 x 9-inch loaf pan. Combine both types of flour, baking powder, baking soda and spices.
Mix well.
Add raisins.
In small bowl, combine remaining ingredients.
Beat with fork; add flour mixture.
Mix all ingredients until moistened.
(Dough will be stiff.)
Place dough in prepared pan.
Smooth the top with the back of spoon.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes.
Cool on wire rack 5 minutes.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Mix together and make small meatballs.
Brown until slightly gray and not done completely.

title: carrot salad
directions: Dice carrots and cook until tender.
Cool.
Add onion, green pepper and cauliflower.
Mix in blender tomato soup, sugar, oil, mustard, vinegar, salt and pepper and pour over carrots.
Let set overnight.

title: chicken 'n biscuits
directions: Baking Temperature: 350°.
Baking Time: 20 minutes.

title: wild blueberry nut bread
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Grate the rind of the orange and lemon. Squeeze juice, adding enough boiling water to make 3/4 cup.
Add rind and butter; stir to melt the butter.
Beat the egg separately.
Add sugar gradually, beating well.
Add all other ingredients and juice.
Blend well.
Spoon into a greased loaf pan and bake 1 hour.
Remove and cool.

title: cheesy scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
I use my Salad Shooter.
Potatoes should be sliced thin.
In a mixing bowl, combine all other ingredients except the chopped green onions.
Beat with a mixer until smooth.

title: pumpkin custard cake
directions: Mix large can of pumpkin pie mix, following directions on can for 2 pies.
Pour into 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle yellow cake mix (dry) over pumpkin mix.
Pour melted butter over cake mix. Sprinkle 2 cups chopped walnuts over cake.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour and 20 minutes.
Start checking after 1 hour.
Cook until done.

title: breakfast souffle
directions: Brown sausage over medium heat in skillet, stirring until crumbly.
Drain well on paper towels.
Combine with remaining ingredients in a large bowl, mixing well.
Pour into greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Chill, covered, in refrigerator overnight. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Yields 8 servings, 445 calories each.

title: crescent wrapped gouda
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cut cheese round in half crosswise to form 2 circles.
Remove wax.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles. Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place one rectangle on top of a second; repeat with remaining rectangles, making two double thick rectangles.
Press each into a 6-inch square.
Place cheese circle in center of each.
Pull corners of dough to top center of cheese.
Press dough tightly against cheese.
Twist dough in center to seal, twisting off excess dough.
Press seams to seal. Repeat to make second Gouda wrap.
Press out excess dough with canape cutter or paring knife.
Cut out decorative shapes.
Place on top of each Gouda wrap.
Brush with beaten egg.
Place 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 18 to 22 minutes or until golden brown.
Cool for 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheddar and squash
directions: Cook squash in small amount of water until tender; drain. Sprinkle with salt.
Mix sour cream, egg yolks and flour.
Fold in egg whites.

title: tea cakes
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Mix flour, one cup at a time.
Roll in balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Flatten balls with the bottom of a glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: apple bake bars
directions: Mix cake mix with margarine.
Press on bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
While still warm, spread on pie filling.
Mix sour cream with egg and drizzle over apples. Bake 20 minutes more.
Let cool about 15 minutes, then cut into bars.

title: appetizers
directions: Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing.
Spread crescent rolls out on cookie sheet. Bake and cool.
Spread cream cheese mixture on baked rolls.
Top with chopped veggies and shredded cheese.

title: honeycomb coffee cake
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 9-inch or 8-inch round cake pan.
In small bowl, combine brown sugar, cinnamon and mace; mix well.
In second small bowl, blend margarine and lemon juice.
Separate dough into 10 biscuits; cut each into 4 pieces.
Place biscuit pieces and graham cracker crumbs in bag; toss gently to coat.
Arrange coated pieces evenly in greased pan.
With a small wooden spoon handle poke a deep hole in each biscuit.
Sprinkle brown sugar mixture over pieces.
Drizzle with margarine mixture.
Sprinkle with nuts. Bake at 400° for 12 to 18 minutes or until golden brown.
Turn onto wire rack; invert to serving plate.
Fill holes with honey.
Serve warm.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter with sugar.
Add eggs one at a time and beat well.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk, ending with flour.
Add vanilla and floured walnuts.
Bake in a greased and floured tube pan at 350° for 45 minutes or until toothpick tests done.
Cool on a rack for 20 minutes before removing from pan to cool.

title: chocolate chess pie
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in unbaked pie shell at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: cracker jacks
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Stir in brown sugar, corn syrup, water, vinegar and vanilla. Bring to boil for 5 minutes.
Do not scorch.
Pour over popped corn. Bake in oven for 15 minutes at 250°.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix ingredients together and top with chips.
Bake 60 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian cauliflower
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Spray a large baking sheet with nonstick cooking spray.

title: corzine chocolate cake
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into ungreased pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: stuffed cabbage rolls
directions: In boiling water to cover, cook cabbage for about 5 minutes, or until leaves become pliable.
Remove 6 large leaves and set aside.

title: beef roast(marinated)
directions: Mix dry ingredients and rub into meat on both sides.
Place in baking dish and dribble the lemon juice, vinegar and salad oil over meat.
Cover dish and turn meat occasionally for 4 hours or more.
(I let meat marinate overnight.)
Cover meat with sliced onions.
Add water and bake at 300° for 2 hours.

title: texas barbecue spareribs
directions: Put ribs in a roast pan.
Mix ingredients with 1 1/2 cups water in a bowl.
Pour over ribs.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.
Bake uncovered for 30 minutes more.
Baste and turn ribs several times during baking.

title: sugar-free apple pie
directions: Plump raisins by adding 1/4 cup water to raisins and cook on High heat in microwave for 2 minutes.
Cool (juice will help sweeten pie).
Peel and thinly slice apples.
Add all remaining ingredients to apples and mix thoroughly.
Pour into lower crust. Dot with butter.
Add top crust.
Crimp edges.
Bake at 425° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: garlic pepper parmesan crisp
directions: Combine ingredients in bowl.
Sprinkle cheese mixture on a non stick cookie sheet into 1 1/2 inch rounds.
16 circles on a sheet.
Bake in 350 degree oven for 9 to 10 minutes until golden. Cool on rack. Makes 96 rounds. Store in air tight container.

title: coconut buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: jello cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour into a greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: dill chive sauce(appetizer)
directions: Combine all ingredients in the work bowl of a food processor and blend.
Chill.
To serve, place the sauce in a hollowed red cabbage and arrange in a wicker basket or platter and surround by a variety of raw and or blanched vegetables.

title: california quiche
directions: Melt margarine in skillet and saute onion until tender.
Add mushrooms and cook over medium heat until tender, about 3 minutes. Stir in lemon juice. Cover and simmer 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and cook, stirring constantly, until mushroom liquid has thickened.
Set aside.

title: oatmeal bran muffins
directions: Combine milk and bran in medium size mixing bowl.
Add combined oats and dry ingredients to bran mixture, mixing just until dry ingredients are moistened.
Fill 12 greased medium size muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake in preheated hot oven at 400° for 15 minutes. Makes 1 dozen.

title: fried banana peppers(as "hall's on the river")
directions: Clean, seed and cut in half lengthwise the peppers.
Dip in sweet milk; roll in flour and roll in cracker crumbs.
Allow to dry, then again dip in sweet milk; roll in flour and roll in cracker crumbs.
Fry in canola oil.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot.

title: garlic french dressing
directions: Cover; shake vigorously.
Let stand overnight for flavor. Shake before using on salad.

title: louisiana chicken
directions: Mix together soups, mushrooms and sour cream.
Pour over the cut up chicken.
Take 1 stack of Ritz crackers and crumble over chicken.
Melt butter.
Pour over the top of chicken.
Place in oven at 375° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in baking dish.
Cook 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Drain off fat 1 or 2 times during cooking.

title: quick rice pudding
directions: Beat milk with pudding; add rice and pineapple and mix well. Add Cool Whip and mix well again.
Chill and serve.

title: brownie alaska
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Line 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with foil. Prepare, bake and cool brownie mix following package directions. Invert brownie onto cookie sheet.
Remove foil and cut in half crosswise so each half measures 8 1/2 x 6 1/2-inches.
Cut brick ice cream in half lengthwise.
Place each half on brownie half. Chill in freezer.

title: cauliflower salad
directions: Mix mayonnaise and Parmesan cheese; mix into other ingredients.
Best to serve right away.

title: cheddar potato casserole
directions: Prepare mashed potatoes.
Beat in egg yolks and mix well. Stir in cheese, onion and pepper.
Salt to taste.
Whip egg whites and fold into potato mixture.
Spoon into buttered casserole dish. Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: white cheese dip
directions: Melt cheese, milk and
1/8 c. jalapeno juice or a little more. Cook until
