melted stirring often. Add more milk or jalapeno juice if you want a thinner dip.

title: banana trifle
directions: Cover the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan with crumbled vanilla wafers (may not take whole box).
Mix the milk, pudding, sour cream and 1/2 the Cool Whip together.
Pour a layer over vanilla wafer crust.
Top with sliced bananas, then another layer of pudding and then sliced bananas.
Top with remaining Cool Whip and sprinkle with vanilla wafer crumbs.
Cool and serve.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Tear the angel food cake into pieces and place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Mix the strawberry jello according to the directions on the package, using 3 cups of water.
Pour over the angel food cake pieces.
Add strawberries and pecans on top of this.

title: barbecue deer roast
directions: Place meat in crock-pot, covered.
Add onion with water to cover.
Cook until tender.
Salt and pepper as desired.
Drain meat and pull apart.
Place in a casserole dish and add barbecue sauce.
Simmer in oven about 30 minutes.

title: caramel fruit dip
directions: Mix ingredients together.
If chunky, you may have to use an electric mixer to blend together.
Serve with fruit.
Also, a dish of chopped peanuts may be served along with dip.

title: cheese-mushroom strata
directions: In large bowl, beat together eggs, broth, sour cream and mustard.
Stir in bread cubes, cheese and mushrooms.
Pour into greased 2-quart oval baking dish.
Cover; refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: texas potatoes
directions: Combine the ingredients.
Mix and put in 9 x 13-inch buttered dish.
Sprinkle topping on top and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift the cocoa in with the flour.
Mix ingredients together in order.
Bake at 350° in cake pan for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: holiday salad
directions: Blend cranberries, orange and apples through chopper; cover with sugar.
Let set in refrigerator.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Pare and slice cucumbers and onions thin.
Separate onion slices into rings.
Add salt, let stand 1/2 hour.
Then squeeze out liquid and place cucumbers in bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients, pour over cucumbers.
Refrigerate until served. Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: angel flake biscuits
directions: Mix warm water and yeast and set aside.
Then in a large mixing bowl, mix flour, sugar, salt, soda, baking powder and shortening.
Add buttermilk.
Add yeast mixture and mix well. When dough is mixed well, place in a greased covered container. Put in refrigerator until needed.
Take out what's needed and roll out 1/2-inch thick.
Let rise about 45 minutes before baking. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400° until golden brown.
This dough will keep several days in refrigerator.

title: bootlegger beans
directions: Fry bacon.
When it is about half done, add chopped onion. When the onion starts to brown, pour off most of the grease and add the beans, brown sugar and ketchup.
Stir well.
Cover the pan and simmer slowly for a few minutes.
Or beans can be put in a baking dish and bake in a
300° oven for about 1 hour.

title: taco soup
directions: Brown ground beef, drain.
Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Simmer 30 minutes.

title: saucy skillet potatoes
directions: In a large skillet, melt margarine over medium heat.
Add onions; cook 2 to 3 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in the next five ingredients.
Add potatoes; cook, stirring constantly, for 2 minutes or until hot (do not boil).
Garnish with parsley and bacon.
Makes four to six servings.

title: oven chicken salad
directions: Toss above ingredients together (lightly).
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Remove from oven and cover with Cheez Whiz.
Return to oven about 5 minutes or until cheese is melted.
Remove from oven and cover with a can of French onion rings.
Return to oven about 2 minutes.
(Bake in casserole dish.)

title: oreo cookie dessert
directions: Mix crushed Oreos and butter (save some crumbs for top). Spread in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.
Spread softened ice cream on cooled crust.
Freeze.
Pour on fudge. Refreeze.

title: fruit cocktail cake
directions: Mix by hand, sugar, flour, soda, salt and egg.
Add drained fruit cocktail and mix until moistened.
Put half of nuts in greased 8-inch pan.
Add mixture and spread evenly.
Mix brown sugar and rest of nuts.
Spread on top.
Bake 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: banana split cake
directions: Beat butter, eggs and sugar for 15 minutes.
Pour into crust. Cover with sliced bananas and pineapple.
Top with Cool Whip. Garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: banana muffins(low-fat and low cholesterol)
directions: Beat egg, oil and milk.
Stir in mashed bananas.
Mix dry ingredients and stir into banana mixture until flour is moistened. Fill tins 1/2 to 2/3 full.
Bake about 23 minutes for large or 15 to 18 minutes for small muffins.
Let cool about 15 minutes before removing from pans to let texture firm up.
Bake at 400°.
Makes 12 servings.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Simmer chicken slowly in 2 quarts or more of salted water. Cook slowly so water doesn't cook away.
Debone and save liquid. Saute onion and celery.
Use liquid to cook spaghetti. Cook slowly so it won't get dry.
When spaghetti is done, add chicken, onion and celery.
Stir up then pour in long baking dish.
Grate cheese on top and melt in oven.

title: guamanian chicken estufao
directions: Cut chicken into small pieces.
Place chicken, garlic, onion, vinegar, salt and pepper into a bowl.
Mix well.
Drain liquid and reserve.

title: corn flake peanut butter cookies
directions: In a 4-quart Teflon-coated pan, heat sugar and Karo and add peanut butter.
Stir until mixed.
Add corn flakes and drop by teaspoonful onto wax paper.
Cool until hard.

title: greek butter cookies
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Beat in egg yolk and vanilla.
Blend in dry ingredients and nuts.
Work dough with hands until pliable.
Shape into crescents or fingers, using rounded teaspoonfuls of dough.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
After removing cookies from oven and cookie sheet, sift powdered sugar over warm cookies. Makes about 6 dozen.

title: 3 layer pie
directions: Mix together until consistency of dough, then place in the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan; press evenly in bottom of pan.
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: e z stroganoff
directions: Cut flank steak into 1/3's lengthwise, then slice each 1/3 across grain into very thin slices.
Brown meat in large skillet with small amount of margarine.
Move meat aside or remove.

title: krullers(large batter)
directions: Put together dry ingredients.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add dry ingredients, a little at
a time, with milk until a dough forms.
Place dough on board.
Knead until smooth and batter does not stick to your hands.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Combine soups, chicken broth and tomatoes and set aside.
Oil a 3-quart casserole.
Layer 1/2 of the tortilla pieces, 1/2 of the chicken, 1/2 of the onion and 1/2 of cheese in the casserole. Pour half of the chicken broth mixture over layers.
Repeat layers and then add remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes. (Can be frozen and reheated.)

title: chalet ham dip
directions: Thoroughly combine first 4 ingredients; add milk gradually, stirring until smooth.
Serve with Swiss cheese crackers.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: gingersnaps
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add molasses and egg.
Beat well. Add sifted dry ingredients.
Roll in small balls and roll in extra sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on greased cookie sheet (350° oven for about 5 minutes each shelf).
Makes 4 dozen.

title: chicken simon and garfunkle
directions: Cut chicken in half.
Flatten chicken between waxed paper. Salt and pepper the chicken.
Roll up chicken with 1 slice of cheese (you can use shredded cheese if easier).
*Important to tuck in sides.
Dip in egg; roll in flour, then bread crumbs.
Place in pan.
Melt butter and add spices.
Pour this over chicken.
Bake 30 minutes.
Pour 1/2 cup wine over chicken and bake additional 20 minutes.

title: georgia peach pound cake
directions: Grease 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar. Cream remaining butter.
Gradually add remaining butter, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well. Combine 2 3/4 cup flour, baking powder and salt. Gradually add to creamed mixing, beating well until well blended. Dredge dry peaches with 1/4 cup flour.
Fold peaches in batter.
Pour in prepared tube pan and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
(Can dust with powdered sugar, if desired.)

title: shrimp-n-macaroni salad
directions: Cook macaroni; rinse in cold water.
Mix sour cream, dressing, salts, seasoning and pepper.
Add to macaroni.
Fold in remaining ingredients and chill.

title: spinach rice cheese bake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Place in a greased casserole.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: blueberry dessert
directions: Break angel food cake into pieces.
Cover bottom of cake pan with pieces.
Spread blueberries over cake, then spread Cool Whip. Put the rest of the cake pieces on top and refrigerate.
Can also be used with cherries substituted for the blueberries.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix tomato, onion, kidney beans, cheese and dressing with hamburger and refrigerate.
Toss with lettuce and chips just before serving.

title: crisco chocolate chip cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Combine shortening, brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl.
Add egg and blend until creamy. Combine flour, salt and baking soda.
Gradually add to creamed mixture.
Stir in chocolate chips and nuts.
Drop by tablespoonful (about 2 tablespoons of dough) 3 inches apart on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 8 to 10 minutes for chewy style.
Chewy style tend to look moist and gooey but don't overbake.
For crispy style, bake a few minutes longer.
Makes about 3 dozen.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar, oil, salt and pepper to boil.
Let cool. Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour sauce over vegetables.

title: english cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add the eggs.
Mix the soda, baking powder, spices and flour together and mix into egg. Mix alternately with cold coffee and vanilla.
When mixed, stir in the raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° about 8 to 10 minutes.
Cookies will be firm and light brown on bottom.
Makes 80 cookies.

title: baked chicken breasts
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Arrange chicken breasts on it.
Put one slice of Swiss cheese on each breast.
Pour soup over breasts, then the stuffing mix.
Pour melted butter or margarine over it. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: baked corn casserole(microwave)
directions: Mix ingredients thoroughly.
Grease 3-quart Tupperware roaster (or any microwave-safe container) and pour mixture into it. Microwave about 20 minutes in a 700 watt microwave
(will be firm in the center when done).
Serves 8 to 10 people.

title: easter egg bread
directions: Wash 12 eggs; tint shells with coloring.
Set aside.
Scald milk; add sugar, salt, shortening and lemon peel.
Cool to lukewarm.
Sprinkle yeast on warm water; stir to dissolve.
Add to milk mixture with the 2 eggs and 2 1/2 cups flour.
Beat until smooth.
Stir in enough flour to make stiff dough.
Turn onto a lightly floured board.
Knead until smooth.
Place in a lightly greased bowl.
Grease top and cover bowl.
Let rise about 1 hour in a warm place; punch down and let rise until double or about 30 minutes.
Make 2 large braided rings or 12 small ones.
Make 4 ropes; twist until 36 inches long.
Braid 2 at a time loosely; insert 6 eggs.
Bake 20 minutes at 375°.

title: hamburger rice casserole
directions: Brown meat, onions and pepper together.
Drain.
Add to Ragu sauce.
Layer dish with rice; top with cheese.
Add meat mixture. Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: hawaiian chops
directions: Trim excess fat from pork chops.
In a bowl, combine flour, salt & pepper.
Roll chops in flour mixture to coat.
Arrange chops in a baking dish.
Bake at 375 degrees for 30 minutes.
Lay a slice of pineapple on each chop; return to 350 degree oven for 15 minutes.

title: mushroom and rice casserole
directions: Melt butter in skillet.
Add rice and brown. Add mushrooms. Pour in casserole dish and add broths and almonds.
Cook 1 hour at 350° or until liquid is absorbed.

title: party mix
directions: Combine last 3 ingredients in a large glass bowl.
In small glass bowl, combine first 5 ingredients; microwave until melted. Pour over cereal and nut mixture; stir.
Microwave on High for 2 minutes; stir.
Microwave another 2 minutes on High; stir.
Put on paper towels to cool.

title: jello salad
directions: Mix first five ingredients well.
Chill for two hours before serving.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Cake:
Mix
all of ingredients together.
Put
on
wax paper lined 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 375°
for
minutes. Turn out on dish towel covered with granulated sugar.
Roll up in
a
roll in the towel.
Cool 30
minutes.
Unroll;
spread filling and roll up. Refrigerate overnight or 10 hours.

title: baked chicken 'n dumplings
directions: Cut chicken in quarters. Boil in large pot, covering chicken with water. Add salt and pepper. Boil until tender and well cooked. Remove chicken to cool on large cookie sheet. Place broth in large roaster pan and continue to simmer while chicken cools. Add margarine, soup and enough water to fill roaster pan about half full. Taste to see if seasoned enough. Add chicken (picked off bone). Add evaporated milk just before you begin to add dumplings.

title: no-bake fudge cookies
directions: Dissolve first 3 ingredients in saucepan; add butter.
Heat to full boil and boil for 1 minute.
Have measured and ready to add the peanut butter, quick oats and vanilla.
Add to cocoa mixture.
Mix well and drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper. Cool and enjoy!

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add flour.
Blend and form.
Roll out; then cut with a small round cutter.
(I use a shot glass.) Place pecan half on each biscuit.
Bake slowly at 325° until golden.
Take up and sprinkle with powdered sugar.

title: dutch oven dinner
directions: In hot fat in Dutch oven, cook chuck, stirring about 10 minutes.
Stir in salt.
Add black pepper, onions, green pepper, whole kernel corn and mushrooms.
Top with uncooked noodles; sprinkle with 1 cup grated cheese.
Pour tomatoes over all. Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Serve with grated Parmesan.
Makes 8 servings.

title: joggin-in-a-jug health drink
directions: Mix together and take 2 ounces a day.

title: corn bread salad
directions: Make corn bread; crumble in separate bowl.
Combine vegetable ingredients with mayonnaise and 2 Tbsp. sour cream.
Layer corn bread and vegetable mixture; then sprinkle on a little cheddar cheese and bacon bits.
Continue layering until ingredients are gone.
Spread
8 oz. sour cream on top layer; cover with 2 cups shredded cheddar cheese and some bacon bits.
Refrigerate overnight, if possible.

title: easy yogurt fruit dip
directions: Blend yogurt into Cool Whip until well mixed and dip consistency. Cool in refrigerator. Serve in center of fruit tray with assorted fruits. Garnish with strawberries or pineapple slices.

title: potato chip cookies
directions: Cream together shortening and sugars.
Add eggs and vanilla. Blend well.
Add flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Fold in crushed potato chips and nuts.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes.

title: preacher cookies
directions: Boil together margarine, sugar and milk for 3 1/2 minutes. Take from stove and add remaining ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonfuls on wax paper immediately.
Let cool.

title: chicken sausage casserole
directions: Boil chicken and dice.
Brown sausage.
Prepare rice according to instructions on box.
In 13 x 9-inch casserole line bottom with diced chicken.
Mix sausage, soup, mushrooms and rice and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for about 45 minutes.

title: pickled eggs
directions: Blend mustard with small amount of vinegar in saucepan. Add remaining ingredients, except onions and eggs. Heat juice to boiling. Simmer for 10 minutes. Cool. Pour over eggs and onions. Cover and refrigerate. Eggs will keep at least 2 weeks.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Place ground beef in skillet and add taco seasoning mix.
Add 1/4 cup of water and simmer 10 to 15 minutes.
Let cool.
Chop and mix together lettuce, pepper, onion and tomatoes; toss well.
Rinse and drain kidney beans and add to salad.
Add 3/4 bag cheese and crush up chips and add to salad. Now toss well.
In separate bowl mix taco sauce and stir until blended.
Pour this over salad and toss again until well coated. Sprinkle remaining cheese on top.

title: fiery grilled shrimp on sesame spinach
directions: Prepare the grill.
In a small bowl, combine the red pepper flakes, garlic, ginger, oil, salt and pepper; mix together well. Coat the shrimp generously with the rub and refrigerate for at least 15 minutes.

title: crab cakes
directions: Soak bread in milk.
Mix with all remaining ingredients except crab meat.
Add crab meat and mix well but lightly.
Form into cakes and cook in melted butter or Crisco until both sides are brown.

title: speedy vegetable soup
directions: Brown beef and drain well.
Put into 3-quart microwavable bowl.
Stir after adding each of these:
vegetables, onion, sauce, tomatoes and paste.
Add salt, pepper, garlic, and water and stir again.
Microwave at 100% power for 20 minutes, covered with waxed paper.
Prepare macaroni or rice according to package. (Microwavable rice, such as "Success" does not need to be prepared separately.)
Stir soup and microwave on 70% power for 15 more minutes, adding cooked macaroni or rice during the last few minutes, or stirring in microwavable rice for the full 15 minutes. Let stand 10 minutes.
Makes 8 to 10 bowlfuls and freezes well.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all ingredients except egg whites.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold in last.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes.
Let stand 5 minutes before pouring glaze over cake in pan.
Then let it cool before taking it out of pan.

title: simple yellow cake
directions: Put all ingredients in at once and mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Good for shortcake or top with favorite frosting.

title: salmon braised with fennel and apple
directions: Season the flour with salt and pepper; dredge the salmon in it. In a deep skillet, heat half the olive oil and the butter until bubbling.
Brown the salmon pieces on both sides over high heat. Remove to a plate and keep warm.
Add the onion and remaining oil to the pan and cook over moderate heat until lightly browned, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Add the beef broth and cider and heat to a simmer. Return the salmon to the pan along with any juice collected on plate.
Cover and simmer for 8 to 10 minutes until the salmon flakes when lightly pressed.
Lift fish with slotted spatula; place on platter.
Surround with the apples and fennel.
If sauce is thin, reduce for several minutes to thicken.
Add lemon juice and pour over all.
Makes 4 servings.

title: quick and easy cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Drop with teaspoon onto baking sheet, 1/2-inch apart. Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.

title: orange salad supreme
directions: Mix jello by directions (less 1/4 cup water).
Pour into 9 x 12-inch dish.
Chill until jello begins to thicken; add pineapple and let congeal.

title: divinity candy(this can be made even on a rainy day.)
directions: Empty marshmallow cream into a nonplastic bowl. Do this first! Mix sugar and water in a saucepan and boil for 3 minutes. Pour over marshmallow cream and beat until candy loses gloss. Add desired amount of chopped nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper. Does not keep well in tightly closed container.

title: banana nut drop cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In a medium bowl, combine mix, oil and water.
Stir vigorously with a spoon until well blended, about 1 to 2 minutes.
Drop from a teaspoon onto an ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cookie sheet for about 1 minute, then remove to cooling racks to finish cooling.

title: fire and ice tomatoes
directions: Place tomatoes, pepper and onion into shallow dish.
Combine remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Boil 1 minute and pour immediately over vegetables.
Cover tightly and chill.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Boil sugar and milk until soft ball forms in cold water. Remove from heat and add peanut butter and marshmallow cream. Pour into a greased pan and cool.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Soak cucumbers in 1 cup of salt to 1 gallon of water for 1 week.
Then wash and cut in rings.
Soak in 1 cup lime to 1 gallon of water for 23 hours.
Wash well and make syrup of sugar and vinegar (enough to cover cucumbers) and soak overnight.
Drain off syrup and boil 10 minutes.
Cover cucumbers again and let set 2 hours.
Put on stove and cook 12 minutes.
Put mixed spices in jar.
Fill with cucumbers and syrup and seal.

title: sfinge
directions: Sift flour, baking powder, salt and nutmeg together.
Cream sugar with butter, then add eggs and beat smooth.
Add two mixtures together and blend to form dough.

title: baked custard
directions: Beat all ingredients well and pour into individual custard cups or a baking pan.
Place in a pan of hot water that comes almost to the top of the cups and bake in an oven preheated to 350° for 40 to 50 minutes until the custard is set.
Serve hot or cold and garnish with fresh berries.

title: peanut butter clusters
directions: Combine cocoa, sugar and salt in a saucepan.
Add syrup and milk.
Cook over slow heat until mixture forms soft ball when dropped in cold water.
Remove from heat and stir in peanuts, oatmeal and coconut.

title: veal scaloppini
directions: Dry scaloppine thoroughly.
Place butter and oil in the frying pan over moderate heat.
Dust meat with flour.
When the butter is foamy, fry the scaloppine for 2 minutes, then turn and fry 1 minute more.	Remove from pan.
Add chopped onion, garlic, parsley and sliced mushrooms.
Last add white wine, cream, salt and pepper to taste. Bon Appetit.
Serves 6.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Dip chicken in egg and small amount of water mixture; dredge in flour, flour/cornmeal mix or cracker crumbs.
Fry in shortening and place in casserole.
Add onion and celery to remaining shortening.
Cook over low heat until soft and lightly brown. Stir in flour; slowly add milk and stir until thick and smooth. Add seasonings.
Pour gravy over chicken; cover and bake at 325° for about an hour or until chicken is tender.

title: hamburger and bean casserole
directions: Fry the bacon and hamburger, then add the rest of the ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Grease and flour loaf pan.
Mix and stir all the ingredients together.
Bake 55 minutes in 350° oven until toothpick comes out clean.
Can be also made with chopped dates.

title: confetti pasta salad
directions: Better if mixed and left to set in refrigerator 3 hours before serving.
If you wish for more color, add 2 tablespoons chopped pimentos.

title: peach cream cake
directions: Cut cake into 1/4-inch slices.
Arrange half the slices on bottom of 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin walnut cake
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, cinnamon and salt on waxed paper. Beat eggs in large bowl with electric beater on high until well mixed. Add sugar gradually, beating until thick and lemon colored. Beating constantly, pour in corn oil. At low speed, blend in dry ingredients alternately with pumpkin to egg mix. Begin and end with dry ingredients. Beat until smooth; add walnuts. Turn into well-greased angel food or tube pan (10 x 4). Bake at 350° approximately 1 hour and 10 minutes. Add glaze (Cream Cheese Frosting) and drizzle down sides.

title: bacon and avocado dip
directions: In a medium skillet, cook bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels.
Crumble and set aside to cool.
In a medium bowl, use a fork to mash avocados.
Stir in lemon juice, onions, salt, tomato, chili peppers and crumbled bacon.
Cover and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.

title: sauteed mushrooms quincy style(appetizer)
directions: Saute all ingredients together in a skillet for about 2 to 3 minutes.

title: miss green's punch
directions: Mix all together, except ginger ale.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale.

title: chutney cheese canape
directions: Blend the ingredients well.
Chill for at least 4 hours. Scoop out a pineapple half and fill with mixture.
Top with toasted almonds.
Serve with crackers.
This is a quick and festive recipe and may be made the day before serving.

title: strawberry-pretzel jello
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and press into 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake 7 minutes at 400° (glass pan 375°).
Cool.

title: kadiah crab
directions: Grease 16-inch dish.
Dice four slices of bread.
Put in bottom of dish.
Mix crab, mayonnaise, onions and peppers.
Put on top of diced bread.
Trim crust from other 6 slices and place on top of crab mixture.
Put beaten egg and milk mixture over bread.
Let stand overnight or for a few hours.
Pour soup over egg mix.
Add cheese and butter.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar together.
Sift dry ingredients. Combine milk, water and syrup and add alternately with dry ingredients.
Add vanilla and fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Pour into paper-lined layer-cake pans and bake in a 350° oven for 35 minutes.

title: meringues
directions: Lightly spray cookie sheet. Beat egg white, sugar and vanilla. Beat until peaks form. Cover pecan halves. Bake at 250° for 30 minutes. Cut oven off and let set in oven for 30 minutes.

title: strawberry rhubarb crisp
directions: In bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan, mix strawberries and rhubarb. In small bowl, stir cornstarch and 1/2 cup brown sugar.
Add this to rhubarb mixture and stir well.
Stir remaining brown sugar, oats, flour and cinnamon.
Stir in margarine.
Sprinkle over mixture.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: layer salad
directions: Chicken salad with capers.

title: easter cookies(koulourakia)
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, one at a time, alternating
with
orange
juice.
Add
flour, which has been sifted
with
baking
powder
and baking soda, gradually. This makes
a
soft dough.
Shape into desired forms; place on buttered cookie
sheets.
Brush with beaten egg-milk mixture; sprinkle sesame seed.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese-potato delight
directions: Preboil potatoes.
Combine all ingredients in a casserole dish.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: fabulous fudge dip
directions: Combine all ingredients except vanilla in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook over medium heat, stirring occasionally until mixture comes to a full boil (18 to 20 minutes).
Boil 3 minutes, stir in vanilla.
Serve with fresh fruit.

title: cream puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Add butter to water and return to a boil.
Add flour; cook 3 minutes.
Remove from heat; break eggs, one at a time into mixture, beating well after each egg.
Before adding fourth egg, add baking powder.
Drop dough from a tablespoon onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 425° for 20 minutes, then reduce heat to 300° and bake 20 minutes longer.
This will make 6 large puffs or about 10 small ones.
May be served with any filling desired, packaged pudding mix is fine.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Make a sauce of the margarine, flour and milk.
When it thickens, add sour cream, cheese and mushrooms.
Mix and add chicken.
Pour mixture over the cooked spaghetti that has been put in a casserole dish.
Top with round cracker crumbs or buttered bread crumbs.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake covered 45 minutes or less.
Uncover and bake until crumbs are light brown.

title: double chocolate oatmeal cookies(similar to a mrs. fields cookie)
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Cream together butter and sugars.
Add eggs.
Whirl oatmeal in blender until it becomes partly oat flour. Add salt, baking powder and soda to oat mixture.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture gradually.
Fold in chocolate chips, chopped nuts and grated milk chocolate.
Batter will be very stiff. Drop by rounded tablespoonfuls onto ungreased air-cushioned cookie sheet.
(Do not use regular cookie sheet, cookies will burn.)
Bake 11 minutes or until edge of cookies begin to brown.
Makes 150 large cookies.

title: tennessee river catfish
directions: Begin heating 2-inches of oil over medium-high heat in a deep, heavy pot to 375°.

title: spanish okra
directions: Saute okra, tomatoes, onion and salt in butter for 5 minutes. Add chili powder, Tabasco sauce and water; mix well.
Simmer, covered, on low heat until vegetables are tender and mix has thickened.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: butternut pound cake
directions: Cream sugar, butter, Crisco and salt.
Add the 5 eggs, one at a time, beating well.
Mix milk, water and cake flour.
Start adding flour and milk alternately, mixing well.
Fold in the butternut vanilla flavoring.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour and 45 minutes. Start in cold oven.

title: crispy chicken
directions: Cut chicken into pieces and skin.
Mix mayonnaise and ketchup together.
Dip chicken into mixture and
roll in corn flakes. Place in baking pan. Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 60 minutes. Remove foil and bake 10 to 15 minutes until crispy.

title: egg custard
directions: Mix all the ingredients in blender together.
Pour into well-greased pie dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add carrots, salad oil and eggs.
Beat until well mixed.
Add other ingredients and stir.
Put batter in two large or three small loaf pans or two 9-inch cake pans which have been oiled and floured.

title: chicken apricot
directions: Mix together and pour over 2 chickens (cut up) or chicken pieces.
Bake uncovered about 1 hour at 375°.

title: skipper's dock poppy seed salad dressing
directions: Mix sugar, mustard, paprika, salt and vinegar until sugar is dissolved.
Add the honey, lemon juice and shallots.
Gradually beat in oil and add tarragon and poppy seed.
Chill.
Yields 1 1/2 cups.

title: amish shoo-fly pie(makes one 9-inch pie)
directions: Mix flour, lard and sugar.
Mix 1 cup crumbs in molasses mixture and pour in shell.
Put remaining crumbs on top.

title: ann's chewy cake
directions: Mix first three ingredients well and pour in greased 13 x 9 x 2 inch baking dish.
Mix last three ingredients well and pour over the above mixture.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes on 350 or until done.

title: baked chicken breasts supreme
directions: Wipe chicken well with damp paper towels.
Remove meat from bones. Be sure to take out gristle.

title: hamburger gravy
directions: Fry hamburger until crumbly in oil and margarine; put 2 tablespoons flour and brown lightly.
Pour milk over and cook until it thickens.
Add salt and pepper.
Pour it over toast or biscuits.
(Same as for sausage gravy.)

title: aunt dot's pie crust
directions: Mix shortening into flour and salt with pastry blender.
Add liquid with egg beaten in.
Mixture will be soft but will stiffen up.

title: chicken breasts piquant
directions: Combine soy sauce, oil, water, garlic, oregano and brown sugar.
Arrange chicken breasts in baking dish.
Pour wine mixture over breasts. Cover. Bake at 375° for
1 hour and 30 minutes. Makes 6 servings.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients; beat until light and fluffy.
Add 7-Up gradually and beat well.
Pour into greased 9 x 12 x 2-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Flake salmon; blend in egg.
Stir in liquid from salmon and milk.
Add remaining ingredients.
Spoon lightly into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: monte cristo dinner
directions: In skillet, cook bacon until crisp.
Remove bacon; crumble. Discard all but 2 tablespoons drippings.
Cook pepper and onion in drippings until tender.
Prepare dinner as directed on package. Add bacon, pepper and onion; heat thoroughly.
Gently stir in chicken.

title: icing(with flour)
directions: Cook flour and milk, stirring carefully until very thick (burns easily).
Allow to cool, then beat until creamy.
Mix butter, sugar and vanilla in separate bowl until fluffy.
Add to cool mixture.

title: ham loaf
directions: Mix together fresh ham, smoked ham, milk, bread crumbs and egg like a meat loaf.
Mix brown sugar, water, vinegar and brown sugar. Bake at 350° for 1 hour, basting frequently during baking.

title: wacky cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients in bowl.
Make 3 wells in mixture: large one for oil, medium one for vinegar and small one for vanilla. Pour water over all and mix thoroughly with a fork.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Put in ungreased 8-inch square pan.
For oblong pan, double recipe.

title: punch
directions: Mix and put in freezer for later use.
When taken out, add two 28 ounce cans ginger ale.
Makes 40 (4 ounce) servings.

title: tomato soup
directions: If you have fresh tomatoes, cook them well and beat them up with a mixer.
Do not puree them, however.
If you use the canned tomatoes, beat them in the same manner.
Leave some of the chunkies.
Cook the tomato mixture and spices for 16 minutes. Cool the mixture down and pour in the milk.
Fold the cream cheese in; stir it until it is the consistency you want.
Do not leave the chunks of cheese floating around.
Mix until it is homogeneous.
Watch out for the tarragon.
It will overwhelm you.

title: chicken and ham dish
directions: Melt butter and blend in flour.
Add milk and broth gradually stirring constantly.
Bring to a boil.
Keep stirring, cook until thickened.
Lower heat.
Stir in remaining ingredients, one at a time.
Simmer 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until heated through.
Serve over rice, toast or patty shells.
Serves 6.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Dip vegetables of choice.

title: pigs-in-a-blanket
directions: Slice crescent rolls into triangles.
Spread mustard on dough. Roll wieners in dough.
Bake at 400° until brown.

title: baked potato wedges
directions: Mix all ingredients in a shaker bag.
Wash potatoes and cut into wedges.
Place several wedges at a time into shaker bag and turn to coat well.
Place potatoes in a single layer in a large baking dish.
Melt 1 stick margarine and drizzle over potatoes. Bake in 400° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli, ham, noodle casserole
directions: Mix butter, soup and milk in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Add cooked noodles, ham and broccoli.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with grated cheese.
Return to oven until the cheese is melted.

title: paper bag apple pie
directions: Pare, core and quarter apples, then halve each quarter crosswise to make chunks (approximately 7 cups) or use pie sliced apples. Place in large bowl. Combine sugar, flour, and nutmeg in cup. Sprinkle over apples; toss to coat well; spoon into pastry shell, drizzle with lemon juice.

title: aunt georgie's cornbread(fat-free)
directions: Mix and bake in iron skillet that is well-greased and hot at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brown.

title: robert (mustard) sauce
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Add scallions and flour.
Stir for 3 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and simmer.
Great over various meats (especially chicken).

title: pineapple cream pie
directions: Combine ingredients in saucepan and cook until thick.
Remove from heat and fold in 1 cup crushed pineapple.
Pour into baked pie shell.

title: quick salmon patties
directions: Drain liquid off salmon; save.
Combine salmon, egg, onion and flour.
Add 2 tablespoons salmon liquid.
Form into small patties and shallow fry in hot oil until golden brown (about 5 minutes). Serve with tartar sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: chocolate pudding or pie
directions: Heat sugar, flour, salt and milk
Add egg yolks and mix.
Add butter and chocolate; mix well.
Add vanilla when thickened.
Top with meringue.

title: deep dish apple pie
directions: Peel apples.
Slice and fill a 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Mix remaining ingredients except butter and pastry and sprinkle over apples.
Dot with butter.
Cover with pastry and bake in a moderate oven (350°) for 45 minutes.

title: toad-in-the-hole
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
In a large mixing bowl, combine eggs, salt and milk.
Blend in flour.
Set aside for 15 minutes.
In a heavy skillet over medium-high heat, saute sausage.
Distribute drippings among eight 3-inch pie tins.
Pour a thin layer (about 1/4-inch) of batter into each tin.
Bake for 5 minutes or until set.
Add sausage; top with remaining batter.
Bake for about 25 minutes or until puffed up and brown; serve at once.

title: toads in the hole
directions: Place sausage and water in a 10-inch skillet.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 minutes.
Remove cover; increase heat to medium and cook until brown and water is evaporated.
Prepare batter.
Beat eggs with whisk; add milk and blend well.
Add remaining ingredients and blend well.
Pour 1/4 cup sausage drippings in an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking dish.
Arrange sausage links on bottom of dish.
Pour batter over all.
Bake in a 425° oven for 30 minutes.

title: adam's pizza pockets
directions: Roll out dough and cut into approximately 4-inch squares. Place 1 tablespoon pizza sauce in center of each square.
Add toppings and cheese as desired.
Fold square to form triangle; moisten edges of dough and press to seal.
Fry in oil over medium to medium-high heat approximately 3 minutes each side or until golden brown.

title: cinnamon bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar, egg yolk, vanilla and dry ingredients together.
Pat thin into a well-greased baking pan.
Pour egg white over and pat in finely chopped nuts.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Combine all ingredients except Jiffy mix and stir.
Add Jiffy mix last.
Stir.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.

title: blender cheesecake
directions: Place all ingredients in a blender container.
Blend for 7 minutes.
Butter a 10-inch pie plate (clear glass ovenproof is best).
Pour mixture into pie plate and sprinkle top with cinnamon. Bake at 325° for 1 hour or longer (bottom should be nicely browned).
Cool and refrigerate.
If strawberry, cherry or blueberry topping is desired, eliminate cinnamon and pour topping over cool pie.

title: fudge cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt 1 stick butter in a 9x13 inch baking dish.
Mix ingredients with spoon in a large bowl.
Pour over melted butter but do not stir.

title: banana split cake
directions: Blend first 3 ingredients and add pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.
Cool thoroughly.

title: mae dee's squash casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients, except crackers, and place in a baking (greased) casserole dish.
Sprinkle top with crushed cracker crumbs.
Bake in preheated 350° oven for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: vegetable cutlets
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Cook potatoes in boiling salted water until tender.
Peel and mash.
In skillet, heat butter. Saute onions and mushrooms until tender.
Add to potatoes. Stir in carrots, green beans, peas and 2 eggs.
Blend. Add enough matzoh meal so mixture
can be shaped into large patties.
Season to taste. Shape into 12 patties. Beat well 1 egg. Brush on both sides of patties.
Place on greased cookie sheet and bake 45 minutes or until lightly browned. Serve with Vegetable Gravy.

title: my favorite chicken vegetable soup
directions: *Two or three large, fresh, chopped tomatoes are best.

title: hot chipped beef dip
directions: Blend cream cheese and milk in a bowl.
Add sour cream and pepper; mix well.
Stir in dried beef, onion and green pepper. Spoon into ungreased casserole.
Bake for 15 minutes or until bubbly.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Place in warming server.
Serve with vegetables or crackers.

title: jalapeno cheese squares
directions: Alternate layers of cheeses and jalapenos in greased baking pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together in bowl.
Pour over cheese.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: black bread soup
directions: In a large saucepan, combine broth, lemon peel, cinnamon, nutmeg, brown sugar and beer.
Bring to a boil, then lower heat and let simmer for 10 minutes.
Line a warmed soup tureen with the slices of bread.
Pour in the soup.
Serve with sour cream on the side.
Serves 4.

title: wonder marshmallows
directions: In top	of
double
boiler
soften
gelatine in 1/3 cup water. Place
over
boiling
water and stir until gelatine is dissolved. Add
sugar
and stir until dissolved.
Remove from heat.
Pour Karo
into	large
bowl
of
electric mixer.
Add vanilla and
the gelatine and sugar mixture.
Beat on highest speed until
mixture becomes thick and of marshmallow consistency, about
15 minutes. Brown coconut in 350° to 375° oven. Sprinkle bottom
of
pan with coconut; pour in marshmallow and sprinkle top.
Put
in
cool place 1 hour; cut in squares and roll edges in coconut.

title: fettuccine alfredo
directions: Cook fettuccine in unsalted water.
Drain well.
Place in a large bowl, add remaining ingredients.
Toss and serve.
Serves 6.

title: norwegian puff pastry
directions: Cut

1/2 cup butter into flour, add 2 Tbsp. water. Round into 2 balls. Pat out dough into 2 long strips 3 x 12 on ungreased cookie sheet. Bring 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to a boil. Add almond flavoring. Remove from heat. Add flour. Add eggs, one at a time, mixing well by hand. Place this evenly over strips and bake 60 minutes at 350°. After cooled, frost.

title: lime jello and cottage cheese salad
directions: Dissolve jello in hot water (then cool).
Blend in mayonnaise and milk.
Add pineapple, salt and lemon juice.
Add cottage cheese and pecans.
Pour into large mold and put in refrigerator until firm.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix dry ingredients; add diced onions.
Beat eggs; add to buttermilk.
Add all ingredients together.
You may have to add a little more buttermilk to form and roll into balls, about the size of walnuts.
Drop into medium-hot oil.
Cook until golden brown. They will float when done.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Roll into balls and coat with dipping chocolate.
Makes about 40 centers.

title: hollywood chicken
directions: Brown hamburger well; add flour and brown.
Add milk and cook until thick.
Add soup; mix well.
Put layer of cracker crumbs in casserole.
Pour in mixture.
Add a top layer of crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 30 minutes or until bubbly and brown. Children and husbands love this.

title: french onion soup
directions: Saute onions in butter in saucepan until limp.
Add flour, salt, pepper, sugar and garlic.
Cook over medium heat, stirring until mixture is golden brown.
Add parsley and thyme; stir.
Add chicken stock and wine.
Simmer 45 minutes.
Serve with croutons and grated Swiss cheese.

title: frozen avocado salad
directions: Dice avocado into a bowl.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon lemon juice.
Blend cheese with remaning lemon juice, sugar, mayonnaise and salt.
Add fruit.
Fold in whipped cream.
Put in freezing tray and freeze 6-8 hours.
Let stand a few minutes before cutting.
Cut in squares to serve.
Pretty and good!

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream sugar, eggs and butter well.
Mix until light and fluffy.
Add pineapple and cherries.
Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Add nuts, flavorings, coconut and pineapple juice.
Mix well.
Bake at 275° in 2 to 3 loaf pans for 1 1/2 hours or until toothpick comes out clean.
Cool well.
Store to develop flavor.

title: old fashion macaroni and cheese
directions: Make a white sauce with margarine, flour, milk and salt.
Add 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Stir until melted.
In 1 1/2-quart casserole, layer half of macaroni and cheese sauce; repeat layers.
Top with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: oven-braised pork chops
directions: Microwave browning dish on High for 5 to 6 minutes.
Add pork chops.
Season with salt and pepper.
Microwave on High for 4 to 6 minutes or until meat is golden.
Turn over halfway through cooking.
Add water.
Cover with tight fitting lid.
Microwave on Medium for 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Allow to stand for 5 minutes before serving.

title: pizza burger
directions: Brown beef and drain off fat.
Add onion, pepper, soup, catsup, Parmesan cheese, salt, oregano and garlic.
Simmer 3 to 5 minutes.
Spread mixture on French bread and top with Cheddar cheese.
Place under broiler until cheese bubbles.

title: split pea soup
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients in large kettle and bring to a boil.
Then set back to simmer and cover, cooking for 1 hour.
At this time, add all the vegetables and spices up to the optional cayenne.
Cook until tender.
Put soup through a blender using puree to coarse setting then return to kettle.
You may have to add some broth or water.
Finally, to bind and thicken soup, mix butter which is melted with flour and a little soup.
Return all this to the rest of the soup and stir until thickened.
Serve with cornbread or just crackers.
Keeps well after cooling in the refrigerator.
Take out what you want; add a little water; heat and eat.

title: parker house rolls
directions: Mix 1 1/2 cups flour with all other dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Melt margarine, then cool it down with cold milk, then add to the dry ingredients.
Add the eggs and beat with mixer until it is well mixed.
Stir remaining flour into the mixture with a spoon.

title: cashew clusters
directions: In a 1 1/2-quart saucepan combine sugar, water and cream of tartar.
Cook and stir until sugar dissolves.
Bring to boiling; boil until syrup reaches hard crack stage (300°).
Remove from heat; stir in cashews and vanilla.
Set pan in larger pan of hot water to keep soft.
Drop by tablespoonfuls onto greased baking sheet to form clusters of 5 or 6 nuts.
Makes about 1 pound of candy.

title: apple-sausage roll
directions: Roll out sausage between two sheets of heavy waxed paper into a 12-inch square.
Mix together diced apples, chopped onion, bread crumbs, egg and seasonings.

title: old fashion lemon pie
directions: Cook in double boiler.
Mix real well. Cook until thick.
Put grated rind in mix, then lemon juice.
Cook crust before putting pie filling in.
Let cool, then put on Cool Whip or egg whites over after beaten real stiff.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Makes 3 big pies.

title: velveeta fudge
directions: Melt butter and cheese in saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Mix in vanilla.
Pour over mixture of confectioners sugar and cocoa in bowl; mix quickly until well blended.
Spread in buttered 9 x 13-inch dish.
Pat pecans over top.
Let stand until set.
Cut into squares.
Yields 3 pounds.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Cook noodles per instructions and drain. Use the flavor packet in dressing.

title: easy rolls
directions: Stir all ingredients together to form a smooth mixture.
Spoon onto a greased baking pan.
Bake in a preheated 450° oven until golden brown.

title: pot roast dinner
directions: Put meat in pan and add soup and soup mix.
Cover and bake at 350° for 3 hours.
Add peeled carrots and potatoes.
Cover and continue to bake for 1 hour until veggies are cooked.

title: east india cheese ball
directions: Combine all ingredients, except coconut; mix well.
Roll into ball.
Roll ball in the shredded coconut.
Serve with crackers. May be stored in refrigerator for several weeks.

title: ground beef potato supreme casserole
directions: Thaw potatoes.
Combine all ingredients, except cornflakes and margarine.
Stir well.
Melt margarine in 1 large or 2 medium casseroles.
Pour in potato-ground beef mixture.
Sprinkle crushed cornflakes on top.
Dot with 1/4 cup margarine.
Bake 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
You may have to put a piece of foil on top toward the last 1/2 hour to keep the cornflakes from getting too brown.

title: southern style tomatoes
directions: Empty cans of tomatoes including juice into a large heavy pot.
Boil uncovered over medium heat for an hour or more, stirring occasionally to prevent scorching on bottom.
Season with salt, pepper and oregano to taste.
When most of the liquid is gone and tomatoes are mostly broken up, add brown sugar, adjusting amount for taste.
Finally, crumble a slice of bread (with crusts cut off) into the mixture.
This should thicken the puree sufficiently; if not, add more bread crumbs.
Don't add bread chunks as in scalloped tomatoes.

title: fritter fried okra
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and salt in a mixing bowl.
Add eggs and milk, beating until smooth.
Add okra, stirring until coated.
Spoon okra into hot oil in a large skillet.
Cook, stirring occasionally, until golden brown.
Can be deep fried. Yield:
About 6 servings.

title: five flavor pound cake
directions: When you take out of oven, boil this glaze and pour over cake while hot. Just let it come to a boil.

title: tomato sauce (diabetic)
directions: Peel, core
and chop tomatoes.
Chop peppers and onions fine. Combine
all
ingredients. Boil slowly 4 hours or until thick. Fill boiling
hot
to
within
1/2 inch of top of jar. Process 10 minutes in boiling water bath.

title: vegetable marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients and use as a marinade/dressing for a vegetable medley.

title: caramel pie
directions: Brown 1/2 cup sugar in a heavy skillet.
Beat egg yolks slightly then combine with one cup sugar, milk and flour.
Add the egg-milk mixture to the caramelized sugar very slowly.
Cook over medium heat until the sugar dissolves.
The mixture will thicken as it cooks.
Add butter and vanilla.
Pour into a 9 inch baked pie shell.
Top with meringue.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: Wash and slice thin.
Soak in mixture of ingredients.
Add all together in big pan; don't boil.
Let them get to where they are almost ready to boil, then start putting them in jars.
Have lids real hot.

title: quick taco salad
directions: In a small skillet, heat chili con carne.
Prepare lettuce, cheese, onions and tomatoes.
In medium serving bowl, layer ingredients as follows:
chips, lettuce, chili, cheese, onions and tomatoes.
Toss together.
Top with either green chili salsa or Thousand Island dressing.
Makes 2 servings.

title: cheese hash browns
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Mix cornbread according to package directions.
Bake well done and let cool.
Crumble and add taco seasoning.
Add the other ingredients and fold together well.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Cover bottom of a greased casserole with potato slices. Sprinkle with 1/2 flour, salt and pepper.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over potatoes.
Drizzle evenly with melted butter.
Cover and bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Uncover and cook for 30 minutes longer.

title: ground beef and noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles as directed on the package, then drain well.
In a skillet, brown ground beef and onions, drain.
Combine noodles, ground beef and all other ingredients, mix well.
Pour mixture into a casserole dish and sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: stuffed hot dog buns
directions: In a large bowl, mix all of the ingredients together.
Spoon mixture equally into the buns.
Place in a 9 x 13 pan and cover with foil.
Place into a 350 degree oven and bake for 20-30 minutes.

title: fresh berry freezer jam
directions: In large bowl, combine berries and sugar; mix well.
Let stand 10 minutes.
In small bowl, combine pectin and lemon juice.
Pour over berries.
Stir thoroughly 3 minutes (a few sugar crystals will remain).

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs about 3 minutes until foamy.
Beat in flour and sugars until well blended.
Beat in margarine.
Stir in morsels and nuts.
Bake at 325° for 55-60 minutes.
Cool completely. Serve with whipped cream or ice cream.
If using frozen pie shell, use deep dish style and thaw completely.

title: super mexican cornbread(fried)
directions: Mix well and drop by tablespoon in hot grease. Makes wonderful small patties.

title: susan's beef enchiladas
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning mix according to package directions.
In large saucepan, add meat mixture to enchilada sauce along with 1/2 of chopped onion and olives and simmer on low heat.
In a small skillet, mix Mexene chili powder with water over low heat.
In a large skillet, add 1/2 oil over medium heat and heat each tortilla shell.
Transfer shell to the Mexene mixture and turn, then transfer into 9 x 13-inch glass baking dish sprayed with Pam.
Lay tortilla flat in dish.
Using slotted spoon, spoon 1 to 2 tablespoons meat mixture into center of shell.
Sprinkle with chopped onion, olives and cheese.
Fold sides of shell to center overlapping.
Line up in dish beginning at one end.
Continue with remaining shells as preceding.
When finished filling shells, pour Mexene mixture into enchilada sauce; pour remaining sauce over enchiladas.
Sprinkle with remaining onions, olives and lastly with cheese.
Ready to serve or cover with foil.
Heat in oven at 250° until ready to serve.
Serves
4 to 6.

title: easy chocolate cookies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by teaspoonful on cookie sheet. Bake 350 degrees for 10 minutes.

title: banana pie
directions: Dough:
Mix flour, butter, pecans and sugar with hands until well blended; pat out into greased pie pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Put layers into shell (when cooled).

title: baked eggs with cheese
directions: Stand 5 small round ovenproof dishes in a bain-marie.
Butter the dishes well and lay 2 slices of cheese in the bottom of each. Break the eggs into the dishes and season well.
Add 1 tablespoon of cream and dust with paprika.
Cover with a lid of foil and cook very slowly in the oven for 7 to 8 minutes.

title: cherry berry salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries, pineapple and juice and bananas.
Pour half of the mixture in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch dish.
Chill 1 hour or until firm.

title: impossible coconut pie
directions: Beat eggs well.
Blend sugar, flour and baking powder.
Add to eggs.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Pour into two (9-inch) well-greased pie pans.
Bake at 400° for 35 or 40 minutes until brown.
Pie will be firm.

title: sour cream coffee cake
directions: Mix cake mix, sugar, sour cream and oil; add eggs, one at a time.
Beat thoroughly.
Grease Bundt pan with soft butter or margarine.
Sprinkle with brown sugar and nuts.
Pour in batter. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: hot artichoke heart dip
directions: Drain and chop the artichoke hearts in food processor. In mixing bowl, mix the artichoke hearts with all the remaining ingredients and transfer the mixture to a casserole dish. Bake the mixture of artichoke heart sin preheated oven at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Serve with crackers and sliced baguettes.

title: sweet fried ham steak
directions: Grease skillet with butter. Put ham steak in skillet and sprinkle with brown sugar evenly.
Let cook. Turn over and sprinkle other side evenly and cook.
make sure there is enough butter in pan.
Cook to satisfaction.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Sift dry ingredients together.
Beat the eggs; mix in buttermilk.
Add to dry ingredients, along with raisins, and mix for 5 minutes.
Bake in a greased and floured round pan in a 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: curried fruit
directions: Drain fruit cans and place contents in a crock-pot.
Mix together the melted butter, brown sugar and curry powder.
Pour on top of fruit mixture.
Cook on low in crock-pot for 2 hours or until fruit appears to be soft.
Serve warm.

title: garlic mashed potatoes
directions: Scrub potatoes and rub evenly with vegetable oil.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour or until done.
Cut potatoes in half.
Scoop out pulp, discarding skin.
Combine the potato pulp, butter and remaining ingredients in a mixing bowl and beat at medium speed with an electric mixer until fluffy.
Makes 3 cups.

title: breakfast burritos
directions: Brown sausage and remove from pan.
Brown potatoes in 2 teaspoons oil and drain.
Combine sausage and potatoes in pan. Beat eggs with 1 teaspoon of water and salt and pepper to taste. Add to sausage mixture and cook on a low temperature.
When eggs are scrambled, fold in the cheese and stir until melted.
Place egg mixture in warm tortillas and top with salsa.

title: crispy sugar cookies
directions: Cream together first five ingredients.
Mix and sift together remaining ingredients, then add to first mixture.
Chill dough. Form into balls the size of walnut.
Flatten on cookie sheet with glass dipped in sugar.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes.

title: upside-down macadamia nut cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch oblong baking dish, pour in pineapple with juice. Spread evenly.
Pour cake mix over pineapple.
Sprinkle margarine as evenly as possible over mix.
Bake according to cake mix instructions.
Halfway through baking, sprinkle nuts over cake. Best served warm with vanilla ice cream.

title: golden bars
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add vanilla, flour, baking powder and salt.
Fold in walnuts.
Spread into 11 x 7-inch glass pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Cut into squares while hot.

title: simple dessert
directions: Whip heavy cream.
Slice some fresh peaches and chill together.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon-sugar.
Serves 6.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix together 100% Bran and boiling water and soak.
Cream Crisco, sugar, eggs and buttermilk.
Add dry ingredients alternately, then add the 100% Bran/water mixture.
You can add raisins, dates, pineapple, etc.
Keeps covered in airtight container in refrigerator for 6 weeks or freeze.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs.
Mix in the remaining ingredients. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased cake pan.
Bake at 375° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: onion roasted potatoes
directions: Wash and scrub potatoes; cut in chunks.
In large plastic bag, add all ingredients.
Shake until all potatoes are coated.
Empty potatoes in shallow baking pan.
Bake at 400°
about 40 minutes or until potatoes are tender.
Garnish with chopped parsley.

title: easy party cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients.
Sift together dry ingredients. Add to cream mixture.
Stir in 1/2 cup M&M's.
Drop on ungreased cookie sheet.
Decorate with remaining M&M's.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: walnut zucchini bread
directions: Beat sugar into eggs or Egg Beaters.
Then beat in oil (or applesauce).
Combine dry ingredients; add to first mixture.
As you add the dry ingredients, add it one at a time and add a little bit of zucchini in between each one.
Stir in raisins, walnuts and vanilla.
Put into 2 greased and floured loaf pans (9 x 5 x 2 3/4-inch).
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes (may take longer in certain ovens).
Let stand for 10 minutes.
Remove and let cool. The loaves freeze well.

title: 1 hour buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water; add to buttermilk. Beat in remaining ingredients. Beat well; let rest 10 minutes. Form into rolls; let rise. Bake at 400° for 20 to 25 minutes. Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: cheese puffs
directions: Mix all ingredients, except pineapple or olives, together with fork or fingers.
Cut pineapple chunks in half, or use olives and roll in cheese mixture into balls.
Or, make plain cheese balls. Freeze on an ungreased cookie sheet until hard.
Can be put into containers and kept frozen.
Bake, frozen, on ungreased pan in a preheated 400° oven for 15 minutes.

title: home style granola(vegan recipe)
directions: Follow cooking directions for rice.
When finished, combine raisins and applesauce.
Stir.
Pour 3 cups of boiled hot water over flakes.
Bake in oven on cookie sheet for 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
Substitute any fruit you wish.
This is a vegan recipe, no eggs or milk.

title: german chocolate cookies
directions: Add melted butter and eggs to dry cake mix.
Mix well.
Add nuts and coconut.
Drop by tablespoon onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 11 to 12 minutes.

title: pineapple pies
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 4 egg whites, and cook over low heat until thick.
Pour into 2 unbaked pie shells.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, blend brownie mix, 1 egg and water at low speed until crumbly.
Spread mix into ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Blend cream cheese, 3/4 cup sugar, 2 teaspoons vanilla and 2 eggs.
Beat until fluffy.
Spread over brownie mix. Bake for 25 minutes.

title: orange dip
directions: Use spoon until soft, then mix.
Let it set in refrigerator overnight.

title: meringue cookies
directions: Beat egg whites until foamy.
Beat in sugar, one tablespoon at a time.
Continue beating until very stiff and glossy.
Fold in cereal.
Drop by teaspoon on lightly greased cookie sheet, 2-inches apart.
Bake 14 to 16 minutes at 350°.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: brisket
directions: Trim as much fat from brisket as possible.
Slice 2 onions into rings and lay in large roaster.
Put brisket in.
Top with 2 more sliced onions.
Pour bottle of figaro liquid smoke over brisket.
Cover closely.
Bake at 325° for 6 to 8 hours (overnight).
Let sit for 1 to 2 hours, then remove from juice. Throw onions and juice away.
Slice thinly.
Serve with barbecue sauce.

title: corn salad
directions: Combine vegetables.
In a small bowl, add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour over vegetables.
Cover and chill overnight.

title: seafood spaghetti
directions: Heat olive oil in pan.
Add garlic, onion and tuna and brown over moderate heat for about 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Add tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, salt, pepper and sugar and bring to boil.
Allow sauce to simmer, in a covered saucepan, for 3 hours.

title: pretzels (flavored)
directions: Mix together.
Pour over bag (1 pound) of broken pretzels. Bake in oven 10 minutes at 250° on cookie sheet.
Stir.
Bake another 10 minutes.
Cool.

title: mary's lima bean and chicken stew
directions: In a large pot, add 3 quarts of water.
Bring to a boil and add roux.
When roux is dissolved, put in chicken pieces and potatoes.
Let cook on medium heat for 30 minutes and add lima beans.
Cover and simmer for 1 1/2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: beet cake
directions: Mix oil and sugar.
Add
drained and mashed beets.
Mix dry ingredients.
Add eggs.
Mix well.
Bake in sheet cake pan at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: chili(15 to 20 servings)
directions: Brown the ground beef until it is no longer red.
Pour off excess fat.
Add the onion, parsley, garlic, green pepper and chili brick.
Let simmer for about 20 minutes, stirring often. Add powdered chili mix.
Let simmer for about 10 minutes more, stirring often.
Add tomato sauce and cook slowly for an additional 30 to 40 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: In large saucepan, melt margarine.
Add onion and frozen broccoli and saute until tender.
Mix in rice, Cheez Whiz and soup. Put in buttered casserole dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: five cup salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and chill at least one hour before serving.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: fiesta corn casserole
directions: Combine corn, olives, pimento, onions and green pepper with eggs and seasonings.
Add cracker crumbs. Mix thoroughly. Pour into 2-quart baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes. Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: raggedy ann's magical jello cake
directions: Combine all of the ingredients.
Mix until blended.
Pour into greased Bundt pan or 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.

title: coconut cream pie
directions: Mix flour and sugar together until well blended.
Add 2 cups milk to this mixture.
Add coconut and beat well.
Beat 1/4 cup milk and 3 egg yolks together and add to mixture and heat, adding 1 tablespoon coconut flavoring when mixture has thickened.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Use the egg whites for the meringue and brown in oven.
You may want to sprinkle some coconut on top of meringue before browning.

title: fruit cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in baking dish, then pour back into mixing bowl. Add dry ingredients.
Add milk; mix well.
Pour batter into baking dish.
Empty 2 cans cherries or peaches over batter.
Pour sugar and hot water over fruit.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Try it. You will like it.

title: morning glorious muffins
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
In another bowl, combine carrots, apple, dates and pecans.
Stir in eggs, oil and vanilla.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir until moistened.
Stir in coconut.
Grease or line muffin pans with paper baking cups.
Spoon batter into muffin pans.
Bake at 375° for 18 to 20 minutes.
Makes approximately 18 muffins.

title: taco salad
directions: Mix sour cream, Miracle Whip salad dressing and taco flavoring.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Shred carrots, celery, green pepper and onion; sprinkle over taco mixture.
Cut tomatoes and put over shredded vegetables.
Cut lettuce in small pieces and put over tomatoes.
Add Cheddar cheese.
Chill and serve with taco chips.

title: floating fruit parfaits(low calorie)
directions: Divide fruit among 6 dessert glasses.
Stir boiling water into gelatin in bowl until completely dissolved.
Stir in cold water and ice cubes until ice is completely melted.
Pout 3/4 c. of the gelatin over fruit in each of the glasses.
Refrigerate 20 minutes until set, but not firm.

title: swedish apple pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
Add to apples, nuts, beaten egg and vanilla. Spread in oiled 9-inch pie pan. Bake 25 minutes at 350°.

title: barb's coconut pie(this is a cake)
directions: Bake cake mix as directed.
While cake is still warm, punch holes in top and pour over evaporated milk and water and powdered sugar.
When refrigerator-cooled, ice with Cool Whip and coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: oriental carrot souffle
directions: Saute peas and bean sprouts slightly, just to soften.
Season with marjoram, parsley flakes, salt, pepper, butter and soy sauce; set aside.

title: evelyn's top ground potato pie
directions: Peel and quarter top ground potato.
Cook in water approximately 1 hour.
(Add water as needed.)
Drain.
Put in bowl and add all other ingredients.
Stir until well blended.
Put in greased pan and bake at 350° until brown on top.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook spaghetti 5 minutes maximum.
Rinse and drain.
Pour salad dressing over spaghetti and add chopped vegetables.
Chill overnight.

title: french silk  pie
directions: Beat sugar and oleo until creamy.
Add cooled chocolate and salt.
Add 1 egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add the other egg and beat 5 minutes.
Add vanilla.
This mixture will be thin.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill 2 or 3 hours.
Serve with whipped topping or whipped cream.
This is very rich!
The success of this pie is in beating of the egg!

title: brioches (rolls)(makes 24 rolls)
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: brownies
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake at 350°.

title: quick apple cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Butter an 8-inch baking pan.
Beat eggs well; add milk.
Combine dry ingredients (not cinnamon) and beat into egg mixture; beat in oil.
Dough is quite firm and thick. Spread dough in pan.
Stand the apple slices on edge over entire surface of dough.
Bake 15 minutes.
Remove from oven; pour cream over surface and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Return to oven for another 25 minutes.

title: creamy sweet potato crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Beat potatoes, mayonnaise, 1/4 cup packed brown sugar and cinnamon in a large mixing bowl at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Spoon into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with combined apples, cranberries, oatmeal and remaining 1/4 cup packed brown sugar.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes.

title: olive's sweet cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan. Bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except dressing.
Put in a 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Be sure it is sprayed with Pam.
Top with dressing that has been mixed according to the directions on box. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 10.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: Layer corned beef and sauerkraut in microwave-safe dish.
Mix mayonnaise and salad dressing in bowl.
Spread over layers.
Top with tomato slices; sprinkle with cheese.
Microwave on High for 15 minutes.

title: chocolate fluff
directions: Mix together flour, pecans and butter. Press into an oblong pan; bake for about 18 minutes. Cool. Mix together half of a large container of Cool Whip, cream cheese and confectioners sugar and add to first layer. Take a little piece at a time so it won't tear up. Mix pudding mix as directed on package, then add to second layer. Set for a while, then add remaining Cool Whip to top.

title: rice casserole
directions: Bake in a two-quart casserole dish at 350° for about 45 minutes to 1 hour.
Last 15 minutes, top with pecan halves.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: In large bowl combine broccoli, chicken and rice.
Mix together soups, Cheez Whiz and chicken broth; combine with broccoli and chicken mixture.
Place in three-quart casserole and bake in 325° oven for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: red velvet cake(waldorf-astoria recipe)
directions: Cream the Crisco and sugar; add eggs and beat well.
Mix cocoa in a large measuring cup with food coloring.
Fill 1 food coloring bottle almost full of water; pour from bottle to bottle in order to get all the coloring out of the bottles.
Add to the food coloring and cocoa mixture.
Add this to the Crisco, sugar and egg mixture.
Mix well and add vanilla.

title: upside-down german chocolate cake
directions: Mix nuts and coconut together.
Pour into greased 10 x 13-inch pan.
Mix cake mix according to package directions.
Pour over nuts and coconut mixture.
Mix melted margarine, powdered sugar and cream cheese.
Spoon on top of cake batter.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes.
Cool.

title: creamy coleslaw for crowd
directions: Combine first six ingredients in large bowl.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and chill overnight.
Makes 12 generous servings.

title: beef skillet fiesta
directions: Brown meat in oil over high heat in skillet, leaving meat in coarse chunks.
Add onion; reduce heat to medium and cook until onion is tender.
Add seasonings, tomatoes, corn and bouillon. Bring to boil.
Stir in rice.
Remove from heat.
Cover and let stand 5 minutes.

title: deluxe tuna casserole
directions: Combine ingredients (except milk, soup, cheese and nuts). Heat milk and soup.
Add the cheese.
Stir until melted.
Add to mixture.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan and top with nuts.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: curry chicken
directions: Mix yogurt, soup, lemon juice and curry.
Layer the bottom of pan with broccoli, then chicken.
Pour sauce over chicken; sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts, about 30 minutes. Yield:
6 servings.
Carbohydrate 6 g, protein 37 g, fat 20 g, calories 352.
One serving = 1 vegetable exchange, 5 meat low-fat exchange.

title: lemon sponge pie
directions: Combine sugar and flour.
Add beaten egg yolks and milk.
Add lemon juice, rind and butter.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into mixture carefully.
Pour in unbaked pastry shell and bake for 60 minutes in a slow oven.

title: rhesa's easy cornbread
directions: Mix cornmeal with milk and let it stand for 10 minutes.
Stir in rest of ingredients.
Pour batter into an 8-inch pan that has been greased.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in a 425° oven.
Cut into wedges.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Brush pie shell with egg white and prick it well.
Chop bacon into 1-inch lengths.
Cook bacon in heavy skillet, stirring constantly, until the fat is almost rendered out but the bacon is not yet crisp.
Drain on paper towels.
Scald milk or cream, cool slightly then beat together with eggs, salt, pepper, nutmeg and chives.
Sprinkle the bacon and cheese in the bottom of the pie shell.
Pour the custard mixture over it.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until the top is golden brown.
For doneness, you may test as for custard (put a knife in the center of pie, if it comes out clean, it is done).

title: cheese cake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Press 1/2 of this mixture in an 8-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat sugar and cream cheese until smooth; add other ingredients and beat.
Pour this mixture on baked crust.
Top with the other 1/2 of the crumb mixture.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool, then cut in squares. Refrigerate.

title: chili-style roast
directions: Coat Dutch oven with cooking spray.
Place over medium-high heat until hot.
Add roast and cook until browned on all sides. Sprinkle with salt and red pepper.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix soups and water together.
Cover bottom of greased 9 x 12-inch cake pan or roaster with thin layer of soup mix.
Place chicken pieces, single layer, on top.
Cover with dry onion soup mix.
Sprinkle rice over this, then pour the rest of the soup mixture over the top.
Cover pan and bake at 300° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
If mixture gets dry cooking, add more milk or water.

title: fritos bandito chili
directions: In large skillet, preheat 1 tablespoon vegetable oil.
Brown ground chuck (drain off fat).
Set aside.
Now in same skillet, with 1 tablespoon vegetable oil, cook onion and garlic until onion is tender.

title: lazy day lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain.
Combine oregano with spaghetti sauce.
Ground beef may added.

title: tortilla pinwheels
directions: Mix sour cream and cream cheese until smooth.
Add rest of ingredients and mix until smooth.
Spread on approximately 6 large soft flour tortillas.
Roll tortillas and wrap in plastic wrap. Refrigerate several hours before slicing.
Serve with salsa.

title: dean's pralines
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook over medium heat to 236° (soft ball stage) on a candy thermometer.
Stir constantly.
Cool slightly. Beat until mixture begins to thicken.
Drop candy rapidly from tablespoon onto waxed paper or buttered baking sheet.
If too stiff, add hot water.

title: fried green tomatoes
directions: Slice tomatoes into thick slices.
Season tomatoes with salt and pepper.
Mix in tomatoes into meal and flour.
Mix well.
Take tomatoes out of mixture.
Put into oil.
Cook until golden brown. Serve warm.

title: pull apart vegetable bread
directions: Saute pepper, onion and chives in butter.
Quarter biscuits. Combine all ingredients (be sure biscuits are well coated with butter).
Pour into ungreased Bundt pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°. To serve, simply pull apart and eat.
Serves 12.

title: five cup salad
directions: Drain oranges and pineapple. Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Chill before serving.

title: individual pot roast
directions: In Dutch oven, brown beef chuck slowly in cooking oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add water.
Cover and simmer for 1 hour. Add water, if necessary.
Add carrots, onions and potatoes to meat.
Simmer 45 minutes or until tender.
Serve with skimmed juice.

title: chicken getti
directions: Combine all ingredients except Velveeta; mix thoroughly.
Add 1/2 cup Velveeta cheese and mix.
Pour into 9 x 13-inch baking pan or large casserole dish.
Add remaining Velveeta cheese on top. Bake at 350° for about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: yankee doodle beef(main-dish soup)
directions: Mix thoroughly beef and onion salt; shape into 24 meatballs. In large saucepan, brown meatballs in shortening; pour off fat. Add remaining ingredients, except cheese.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Simmer 10 minutes or until done; stir occasionally.
Serve with cheese.
Makes about 6 cups.

title: chicken with rice
directions: Butter bottom and sides of casserole dish (9 x 13-inch). Spread evenly 1/2 package dried onion soup mix.
Spread evenly 1 can cream of mushroom soup (do not dilute).
Sprinkle instant rice as next layer.
Spread remainder of dried soup mix.
Spread another can of cream of mushroom soup.
Pour 1/2 can water over last layer.

title: spiced tea
directions: Mix and store in a tight container until needed.
Mix 2 tablespoons to 1 cup of hot water.

title: date and nut bars
directions: Mix and bake in 9-inch square pan for 30 minutes in 350° oven. Cool and cut into squares.
Dust with confectioners sugar.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water until frothy.
Add and mix pecans. Mix sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Add nuts and mix well.
Place on buttered cookie sheet.
Bake at 225° for 1 hour; stir every 15 minutes.

title: daryl's peach cobbler(serves 10)
directions: Pour peaches into 11 x 13-inch pan, juice and all.
Slice 8 to 10 butter pats over peaches.
Sprinkle with sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook and stir in a 450° oven for 20 to 25 minutes.
Blend flour, sugar, milk and vanilla for 2 minutes.
Pour batter over peaches and return to oven at 350° until golden brown.
Mmmm....

title: creamy rice dessert
directions: Mix first five ingredients.
Mix last three ingredients together.
Fold into rice and fruit mixture.
Chill for 1 hour.

title: spaghetti with artichoke hearts
directions: In saucepan, add oil and pieces of garlic and artichoke hearts; saute for a few minutes.
Add juice and let simmer another few minutes.
Cook spaghetti and drain.
Add artichoke sauce and mix. Serve with grated cheese.
Serves 4.

title: dried spice mix
directions: Place orange slices on a greased wire rack.
Place rack on baking sheet.
Bake at 200° for 5 to 6 hours, removing slices as they dry.
Cut slices into eighths with shears.
Place 1/4 cup orange pieces, 1 teaspoon cloves, 1 teaspoon allspice and 1 cinnamon stick in 7 to 8 Ziploc plastic bags.

title: ground beef
directions: Brown ground beef, bell pepper and tomato soup.
Put corn chips in a bowl.
Pour meat onto the chips.
Pour cheese over this.

title: raisin cake
directions: Simmer raisins and water 10 to 15 minutes; allow to cool. Cream shortening and sugar.
Add cooled raisins and mix.
Add dry ingredients alternating with coffee; mix well.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour or until tester comes out clean.
Cool in pan about 10 minutes, then invert to plate or rack.
When cooled, sprinkle with powdered sugar or drizzle with thin icing or serve plain.

title: salmon with fresh papaya relish
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Beat eggs and add milk.
Beat until bubbly.
Place Ricotta cheese in a small bowl and add the chives to it.
Blend well, then set aside.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix shortening and sugar together.
Sift the cream of tartar, soda and flour together and add.
Add vanilla.
Roll into balls, roll in powdered sugar and flatten.
Bake at about 350° for about 10 minutes.

title: shrimp cutlets
directions: Lightly beat eggs and water in one bowl.
Combine bread crumbs, red pepper, black pepper, cheese and parsley in another bowl.
Devein and butterfly shrimp.
Dip shrimp in egg and then in bread crumbs.
Repeat.
Refrigerate 1/2 to 1 hour.

title: suzie q cake
directions: Bake devil's food cake as directed on package or any chocolate cake.
Partially freeze.
Slice lengthwise.
Remove top.
Spread filling on bottom.
Replace top.

title: chicken-egg-lemon soup(kotosoupa avgolemono)
directions: Cover chicken and vegetables with water; bring to a boil.
Skin off scum.
Reduce heat and cook partially covered 1 1/2 to 2 hours until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth.
Set aside for later use as desired.
