Strain broth into a kettle, discarding vegetables.
Bring broth to a boil, add rice; stir and salt to taste.
Reduce heat and cook covered until rice is tender.
Add white meat from chicken that you set aside.
Blend hot soup with Avgolemono sauce.

title: old hats
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients.
Add salt and baking powder.
Add just enough flour to make soft dough to roll out.
Cut in thin strips and fry in hot fat until brown.
Serve with maple syrup for breakfast.

title: cherry-almond bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, butter and eggs until fluffy.
In a separate bowl, sift together flour, baking soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture with buttermilk.
Stir in almonds, cherries and almond extract.
Pour batter into a greased and floured 9 x 5 x 3 in. loaf pan and bake 55 to 60 minutes, testing for doneness with a toothpick.
Remove from pan and cool on a wire rack.
Yields:
1 loaf of bread.

title: candied sweet potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes until tender. Drain. In a small pan, cook sugar, syrup, salt and butter until butter melts. Add cinnamon to taste. Pour over potato chunks and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: quick chocolate mousse with raspberries
directions: Heat 1/3 cup of the cream just to a boil in a small saucepan over high heat. Pour the cream over the chocolate in a medium bowl and whisk until the chocolate is melted and smooth. Let cool and whisk in the vanilla and salt.

title: chris' hamburger stroganoff
directions: Brown meat and drain.
Mix meat together with all other ingredients except noodles or rice.
Stir well and heat through. If it appears a little thick, add more milk.
Serve over rice or noodles.
This is particularly easy for fathers left to care for twins for the evening.

title: pineapple cheese casserole
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients.
Crush crackers on top.
Pour butter over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lasagna
directions: Season meat with salt.
Cook and drain grease.
Add garlic, onions and pepper.
Simmer slowly for 10 minutes.
Stir in tomatoes, tomato sauce and spaghetti sauce mix.
Cover and simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour 1/3 of sauce into 12 x 8 baking dish.
Cover with strips of lasagna noodles and slices of cheese, then spoons of cottage cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with meat sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: sweet potato pudding
directions: Peel and slice sweet potatoes to approximately 1 1/4-inches. Dampen and roll in combined 1/2 white sugar with 1/2 flour. Grease lightly a small or oblong Pyrex dish and place potatoes in. Bake at 325° for approximately 3/4 hour.
Around 1/2 hour or browned, turn potatoes over and bake approximately 15 minutes or when lightly browned.
(This recipe is over 100 years old.)

title: mississippi fudge cake
directions: Add ingredients, except marshmallows and icing, together. Bake at 350° for exactly 25 minutes.
While still hot, spread marshmallows over cake.
Put a towel over the cake until cool. When the cake is cool, frost with icing.

title: baked lasagna casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, brown ground beef in oil with onion and garlic.
Drain; add spaghetti sauce and simmer 20 to 30 minutes over low heat.
Cook lasagna as directed on package.
Mix egg and Ricotta cheese.

title: garlic chicken
directions: Cut chicken into 1/2-inch pieces.

title: french fries
directions: Pare potatoes and cut into 3/8-inch strips.
Rinse or soak in cold water.
Dry potatoes well on paper towels.
Deep fry half of the potatoes at a time in Crisco heated to 365°.
Cook until tender and golden brown (5 to 7 minutes).
Drain on paper towels. Keep hot in oven set on low temperature.
Sprinkle with salt. Serve hot.

title: chicken divan
directions: Boil chicken; remove from bones (save broth).
Layer the following in a greased 9 x 13-inch baking dish:

1/2 bag of dressing moistened with chicken broth, chicken, cut into small pieces, broccoli, mixture of cream of mushroom soup and mayonnaise, 8 ounces cheese and 1/2 bag of dressing, moistened with chicken broth.
Preheat oven to 350° and bake for 1 hour.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion until tender.
Drain.
Add all soups together.
Add milk, cheese, broccoli and onion.
Simmer until cheese melts, stirring frequently.

title: meat loaf magnifique
directions: Beat egg in a deep mixing bowl.
Break up hamburger in a bowl and add salt and pepper to taste.
Add 1/4 cup catsup, onions, pickle, cracker crumbs and milk.
Mix all ingredients and form into a loaf.
Put in a roasting pan and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
The pan should be covered with tinfoil.
If loaf seems too dry, just add a little more milk.
If too wet, add more crumbs.
Remove the tinfoil the last 5 minutes and cover with catsup.

title: rookie cookies uncooked fudge
directions: Melt butter in a saucepan.
Stir in milk and vanilla. Gradually add mixture of sugar, cocoa and salt.
Mix until creamy. Press in buttered pan.
Chill and cut in squares.
(It is soft.)

title: texas brag cake
directions: Spread pie filling in the bottom of a greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Spoon pineapple over pie filling.
Sprinkle cake mix over the cherry/pineapple mixture and pat down.
Spread coconut and nuts evenly over the cake mix.
Spoon the melted margarine over the top and bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: corn casserole
directions: Bake in greased casserole at 350° with lid on for 1 hour. Remove lid and bake 15 to 20 minutes longer.

title: black walnut cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add beaten eggs.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Sift flour once before measuring and twice after.
Add baking powder and salt before last sifting.
Add vanilla to milk. Alternately add the sifted dry ingredients and milk to the creamed mixture, beginning and ending with the flour.
Fold in nuts.
Pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until cake tests done.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes and then turn out on rack to cool completely.
Serve plain, dusted with confectioners sugar or with cream cheese frosting.

title: carrot cake
directions: Boil carrots, sugar, raisins, water, butter, cinnamon and cloves for 5 minutes only.
Cool thoroughly.

title: tuna dogs
directions: Mix together.
Spread into hot dog buns.
Heat in microwave about 30 seconds or in 350° oven.
If heating in oven, wrap in tinfoil.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Mix the first 4 ingredients.
Let cool.
Lay crescent rolls flat and bake.
Spread with cream cheese mixture.
Chop vegetables and sprinkle on top.
Top with grated cheese.
Any of these vegetables may be used:
Broccoli, mushrooms, red and green peppers and cauliflower.
Delicious and different!!

title: nutty fingers
directions: Bake at 300° for 30 minutes.
Roll in powdered sugar while hot and again when cool.

title: frozen fruit salad
directions: Mash bananas and add all other ingredients.
Stir and place in loaf pan, mold or individual paper-lined muffin tins.
Freeze. To serve, take out of the freezer a few minutes and put on lettuce.

title: monkey bread
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt and cut in shortening with two knives or pastry blender until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Add enough water to make a soft dough. Knead on lightly floured board until smooth and elastic.
Pinch off enough dough to make 1 1/2-inch balls.
Roll or slap back and forth from hand to hand until each ball is flat 4-inch round.
Fry in skillet in 1/4-inch deep hot fat at 400° until lightly brown on both sides, turning once.
Bread becomes puffy as it fries.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve hot, plain or with jam, honey or favorite tortilla topping.

title: candy bar cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on box. Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan. When the cake is baked, remove from oven and use a fork to poke holes all over the top of the cake. Then pour the jar of caramel syrup all over the top of the cake. Allow the cake to cool. After the cake has cooled, ice it with the Cool Whip. Sprinkle the top with the crushed candy bars.

title: *chocolate fudge
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients and bring to a boil; turn heat on low and cook for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add the chocolate, marshmallow cream, vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased, flat pan to harden.
Cut into squares and remove.

title: quiche crust
directions: Place flour in mixing bowl. Combine oil and milk and add to flour, all at once.
Mix quickly with a fork until mixture forms into a ball. Roll dough out between sheets of waxed paper to a 12-inch circle.
Line an 8 or 9-inch pie plate with the pastry and crimp the edges.
Pierce dough in several places with fork. Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until golden brown. Cool before filling.

title: rhubarb cake
directions: Sprinkle the 1/2 cup sugar over rhubarb. Set aside. Sift together flour and cinnamon. Add shortening, sugar and eggs. Add vanilla and nuts. Add rhubarb. Mix well. Pour into 9 1/2 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° for about 45 to 50 minutes, depending on oven.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: Mix well. Roll in small balls. Place on baking pan and cook at 450° for 12 minutes.

title: quick spanish rice
directions: In medium saucepan, combine all ingredients. Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 25 minutes or until rice is done. Garnish with green onions.

title: pork chops
directions: Brown pork chops.
Put chops in casserole dish and place onions on top.
Mix catsup, soup and Worcestershire sauce.
Pour over chips and onions.
Bake at 375° for 45 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: First Layer:
Mix graham crackers with melted butter and press into bottom of pan.

title: refrigerator salad
directions: Drain pineapple and orange sections thoroughly.
Combine all ingredients and refrigerate for at least 24 hours.

title: mexican hominy
directions: Fry bacon until crisp; remove from pan and drain, reserving 2 tablespoons drippings.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add hominy, tomatoes, chili powder, salt and pepper; cook until slightly thickened.
Pour half of hominy mixture into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Top with half of grated cheese.
Fill with rest of hominy mixture and top with remaining cheese.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes or until cheese is melted.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add onion and green chilies.
Dip 3 tortillas in enchilada sauce and put in bottom of greased casserole.
Add 1/4 cup meat mixture, 1/4 cup shredded cheese and 1/4 of diluted soup.
Continue layers of tortillas, meat, cheese and soup until all ingredients are gone.
Pour remaining enchilada sauce over top.
Bake at 450° for 20 minutes.
Makes 8 servings.

title: hot dutch dressing
directions: Fry bacon until crisp, drain and crumble.
Beat sugar into egg.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Add to bacon drippings in skillet.
Cook until slightly thickened, stirring constantly. Remove from heat and add bacon.
Cool slightly before serving. Great for spinach salad.
Yields 1/2 to 3/4 cup.

title: nuts and chips pie
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix all the ingredients and pour into crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool and cut.

title: salmon party log
directions: Drain and flake salmon. Remove skin and bones.
In small bowl with electric mixer, beat the cream cheese with lemon juice, liquid smoke, horseradish, grated onion, salt and pepper until fluffy.
Stir in salmon. Chill thoroughly and shape into log. Chill several hours before serving.
Sprinkle with paprika and garnish with parsley sprigs.
Serve with crackers. Makes 1 log.

title: melda's easy sweet pickles
directions: Drain vinegar juice off
of pickles and discard.
Slice pickles back into empty jar.
Mix the following thoroughly and pour over pickles:	sugar,	vinegar
and
pickling spice.
Let stand a day or two before
eating.	Pickles
will be crisp and delicious.

title: chili bake(great for snack)
directions: Grate Monterey Jack cheese; set aside.
In 9 x 13-inch pan, spread softened cheese.
Top with chili; spread.
Sprinkle onion and olives on top.
Cover all with grated cheese.
Bake or microwave until cheese melts and hot.
Dip with tortilla chips.

title: paul lynde's chicken for dieters
directions: Place the chicken in a pan (Dutch oven); cover with 1/2 cup of tomato juice and 1/2 cup water.
Simmer 1/2 hour.
Add 4 or 5 green peppers (cut into pieces) and 1 whole bunch of celery (chopped).
Simmer 1/2 hour more.

title: oahu frappe
directions: Boil together sugar and water.
Cook over medium heat 5 minutes.
Cool slightly.
Add both juices and freeze until hard.

title: glazed cheesecake puffs
directions: Place the cream cheese, sugar, eggs and vanilla in a large bowl and beat with electric mixer until smooth.
Line muffin tin with paper liners and place one vanilla wafer in bottom of each liner.
Fill liners 3/4 full with cream cheese mixture.
Bake at 375° for 10 minutes and cool.
Cover with pie filling and chill. Yields 2 dozen.

title: cranberry lemon punch
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve over a creative ice ring in a punch bowl.
Float additional cherries, orange wedges and lemon slices.
Serve immediately.

title: tomato aspic
directions: In saucepan, sprinkle gelatin over 1 cup cold juice to soften. Place over low heat, stirring until gelatin is dissolved.
Remove from heat; add remaining juice, vinegar and seasonings.
Pour into 4-cup mold.
Chill 4 hours or until firm; unmold on salad greens. Makes 3 cups.

title: seafoam salad
directions: Heat pear juice and add to jello.
When cool, add mashed pears and cream cheese which has been softened with top milk.
Add whipped cream to the above mixture.
Chill.
Makes 16 servings.

title: shrimp and pea salad
directions: Add shrimp to boiling water.
Return to a boil, reduce heat and simmer for 3 to 4 minutes.
Shrimp should be opaque throughout.
Drain and cool immediately.

title: chicken livers if you like them(this is a cheap dish.)
directions: Heat the butter in a skillet.
Add the livers and saute until well browned, turning them frequently until cooked (who likes raw liver?).
Remove from the pan.

title: mushrooms(side-dish)
directions: Wash mushrooms; cut in thin slices.
Soak 1/2 hour in salt water.
Cover with water and cook until tender.
Add shortening to skillet brown lightly chopped onion, simmer a few minutes.
Add mushrooms and sour cream, salt and pepper.
Stir.
Serve with meat.

title: dive in potato dippers
directions: Scrub potatoes, peel if desired.
Cut in half lengthwise.
Cut each half into 3 wedges.
Arrange wedges in circle on microwavable plate.
Brush with combined butter and seasoning salt.
Cover with waxed paper.
Microwave on High for 6 minutes.
Turn plate halfway around and microwave 7 more minutes.
Remove waxed paper and sprinkle Cheddar cheese on potatoes.
Serve with dip.

title: supreme pasta salad
directions: Cook linguine per package directions.
Drain and set aside in a large bowl to cool.
When cool, add entire bottle of Italian dressing and all vegetables.
Mix well.
Add 1/3 bottle of Salad Supreme; mix well.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Serve chilled.
This is a great take-a-long for picnics or potluck dinners.

title: cream soup base
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Makes equivalent to 9 cans of soup.

title: pepperoni pinwheels
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Separate dough into 4 rectangles.
Firmly press perforations to seal.
Place 8 pepperoni slices on each rectangle.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons of cheese.
Starting at shortest side, tightly roll up each rectangle; pinch to seal. Slice each roll into 4 equal slices.
Place sealed side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake for 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve pinwheels with warm pizza sauce.
Makes 16 pinwheels.

title: coconut cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions.
Cool and split layers.
Combine sugar, sour cream and coconut; blending well. Reserve 1 cup sour cream mixture.
Spread remainder between layers of cake.

title: amish dessert
directions: Cut margarine into flour like pie crust.
Add nuts.
Pat evenly into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Cool. Beat cream cheese, powdered sugar and Cool Whip.
Spread over crust.
Mix pudding mix and milk.
Spread over cream cheese mixture.
Top with Cool Whip.
Add chopped nuts, if desired.

title: roast pork and sauerkraut
directions: Cook drippings in a 2-quart casserole oven until boiling.
Add sauerkraut and water.
Cover.
Cook in microwave oven for 7 minutes.
Place servings of roast on top.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Cover.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes or until meat is heated through.
Total cooking time: 10 to 12 minutes.

title: hearty cabbage soup
directions: Heat butter in large saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion, celery and cabbage; season well.
Partly cover and cook 10 minutes over low heat.
Add potatoes, chicken stock and dill; correct seasoning.
Stir and bring to boil and continue cooking, partly covered, 20 minutes over low heat.
Mix flour with sour cream in small bowl.
Add 1/2 cup of soup stock to bowl and incorporate, then pour into soup.
Mix well and serve.

title: spaghetti primavera
directions: Saute tomatoes in oil, garlic, parsley, salt and pepper.
In another pan, lightly saute mushrooms in oil.
Blanche remaining vegetables in boiling water until tender-crisp, 3 to 4 minutes. Drain and add to mushrooms; keep hot.
Cook spaghetti according to package directions.
Drain.
Lightly mix cheese, butter and cream into noodles.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Serve noodles on large platter, top with vegetables.
Garnish with tomatoes and 1/3 cup pinenuts or slivered almonds, toasted.

title: saucepan brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt shortening and chocolate in saucepan over low heat, stirring occasionally.
Remove from heat. Add sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Beat until blended.
Combine flour, salt and soda; then beat into chocolate mixture until smooth. Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake 30 minutes.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Saute onion in butter.
Add hamburger; cook until brown.
Add flour and soup.
Just before serving, add sour cream.
Serve over hot cooked noodles.

title: low calorie snack dip
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.
Will keep until expiration of cottage cheese.
Dip is especially good with cucumbers, celery, cauliflower and carrots.

title: rose's meat balls
directions: Simmer 30 to 45 minutes.

title: white chili
directions: Soak beans overnight.
Drain beans and put beans and chicken in a 4 to 6-quart stockpot.
Cover with water and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and let simmer, removing chicken to cool when it is done.
When beans are near done, combine chiles, soup, sour cream and 1 cup of the bean juice in a mixing bowl.
Stir until well blended.
Add green chile mixture to beans and mix well.

title: perfect pie crust
directions: Mix egg in cold water and vinegar.
With a fork, mix first 4 ingredients until they are mealy.
Add the rest and mix.
Mold with hands into a ball.
Chill at least 15 minutes before using. Makes crust for 2 pies.

title: dirty rice
directions: Saute mushrooms, onion, pepper and garlic in butter until tender.
Add remaining ingredients and heat to boiling.
Reduce heat to low and cover.
Cook 8 minutes or until livers are cooked, stirring occasionally.

title: yellow squash relish
directions: Chop squash, onions, peppers and mix with salt in large pan. In another container, mix vinegar, sugar, dry mustard, turmeric, celery seed and black pepper.
Add to squash mixture.
Cook slowly for 20 minutes. Put in sterilized jars and seal.
Put screw bands on hand tight only.
Put jars in a large canning pot and cover with hot water.
Boil for 10 minutes.
Take out jars and place on counter out of a draft until cooled completely.
Do not retighten screw bands on lids.
Then pack in storage boxes or in pantry.

title: spinach and chicken devine
directions: Line casserole with spinach, then chicken pieces.
Mix together mayonnaise, soup, broth and curry powder.
Pour on top of chicken. Top with cheese.
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes or until cheese is hot and bubbly.
May be topped with buttered bread crumbs.

title: quick yeast rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil, sugar and salt.
Mix into flour.
Knead until smooth.
Shape into rolls; let stand 1 hour or until double in size.
Bake at 425° for 12 minutes.

title: date candy
directions: Boil sugar and milk to the soft ball stage.
Add dates as mixture is removed from fire.
Beat and pour into buttered pan.

title: rainbow stew(nonedible!)
directions: Mix sugar and cornstarch in pan.
Add cold water.
Heat until it begins to thicken.
Cool.
Divide into 3 containers, coloring one red, one yellow and one blue.
Place 3 tablespoons of each color in a plastic resealable bag.
Express air, seal and tape shut.
Gently knead the bag to mix colors and observe the effects.

title: 3 minute clam sauce
directions: In 8 to 9-inch frying pan, lightly cover bottom with olive oil.
Saute garlic until heated.
Add clams, juice and all. Cover with a light coating of oregano.
For red clam sauce, add 1/2 cup spaghetti sauce now.
Bring to boil, stirring often. Serve over pasta.
Makes 2 servings.

title: aunt mimi's sugar cookies
directions: Mix all ingredients. Drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet. Flatten with glass dipped in sugar. Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes. Yields 4 dozen.

title: cherry tart
directions: Blend together.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool.

title: noodles and cabbage
directions: Dice onion and bacon in small pieces and brown in large pot while stirring now and then.
Cut up cabbage in medium pieces. Drain grease and all cabbage; stir now and then.
Let simmer until tender.
Boil noodles.
Drain and add to pot.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: apple cranberry casserole
directions: Mix first three ingredients and place in buttered casserole. Mix remaining ingredients and spread on top of apple mixture. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Good with chicken and turkey.

title: brandied cherry coffeecake
directions: Combine cream cheese, sugar and margarine.
Beat until well blended.
Add eggs and vanilla; blend well.
Combine dry ingredients, add to mixture alternately with milk, mixing well after each addition.
Pour into greased and floured 19 x 9-inch pan.
Mix brandy with cherries and spoon over batter.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
When cool, dust with powdered sugar.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Melt butter; mix sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: casserole
directions: Dice 4 slices of bread into buttered dish.
Mix crab, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper and celery.
Spread on top of bread.
Dice 4 more slices of bread and put on top.
Mix 4 eggs and 3 cups milk and pour over top.
Keep in refrigerator overnight.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Pour over the mushroom soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake for 60 minutes longer at 325° or 30 minutes at 350°.

title: nacho chicken
directions: Boil and debone chicken.
Mix 1 or 2 cans Ro-Tel tomatoes, mushroom soup and onion.
Layer chicken mixture and chips in pan. Repeat process.
Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marinated vegetable salad
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a medium saucepan; bring to a boil and simmer to dissolve sugar. Cool. Combine vegetables and stir in cooled vinegar mixture. Cover and chill at least 8 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: salmon dip
directions: Cream first 3 ingredients.
Add onions and remaining ingredients to taste.
Be careful with artificial smoke flavoring. Don't add too much.
Add garlic if you like.
Make into a ball.

title: island connection
directions: Blend all ingredients in blender for 20 seconds.
Add ice to fill 1/2 blender.
Blend again until ice is finely mixed with other ingredients.
Serve immediately in tall glass.
Garnish as desired (strawberry slices, pineapple slices).

title: rice krispy mix
directions: God bless my little kitchen, I love its every nook.
And bless me as I do my work, wash pots and pans and cook.
And may the meals that I prepare be seasoned from above with thy great blessing and thy grace.
But most of all thy love.
So bless my little kitchen God and those who enter in.
May they find naught, but joy and peace and happiness therein.

title: peanut butter squares
directions: Beat peanut butter, margarine, brown sugar and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs and vanilla and mix.
Add dry ingredients and mix.
Grease brownie pan and pour mixture in pan.
Bake at 325° until done, not firm.
Cool and frost.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Blend well; spread on bread. Cut in party style. Slice small cucumbers thin and place on top of bread.

title: black walnut pound cake
directions: Cream butter and Crisco until soft and creamy.
Gradually add sugar, beating at medium speed 5 to 7 minutes.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating just until yellow disappears.
Combine flour and baking powder; add to creamed mixture alternately with milk, beginning and ending with flour mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Stir in vanilla and walnuts.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.
Use 10-inch tube pan.
Cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: sour cream coconut cake
directions: Beat all together until mixed.
Bake in three layers or in flat pan.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Remove and drain.
In same pan cook vegetables until tender.
Add sausage and nuts.
Cook 2 minutes until warm.
Serve over rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: western corn
directions: In a small pot, mix pimientos, corn, bell pepper, salt, pepper and margarine.
Bring to a low boil.
Serve with your favorite meat.

title: pizza bread
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly; knead.
Let rise until doubled.
Knead.
Put in loaf pan.
Rise to double.
Bake in a 375° oven for 45 to 50 minutes.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: orange sliced brownies
directions: Dredge candy in flour and combine with other ingredients. Spread thinly in a greased baking pan, 9 x 13-inch, and bake at 375° until golden brown, about 12 minutes or more.
Cool slightly. Cut and roll in powdered sugar.

title: pave
directions: Peel plantains and grill until tender or place in glass bowl with lid.
Microwave for approximately 4 minutes for each one.
Or peel and slice, then deep fry.

title: venison enchiladas
directions: Brown meat and drain well.
Steam tortillas.
Spread 1 to 2 tablespoons sour cream on each tortilla.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons onion each and add 3 to 4 tablespoons meat before topping with 1 to 2 tablespoons chili salsa and 1 tablespoon shredded cheese.
Roll each tortilla and hold with a toothpick.

title: meat loaf on a stick
directions: Crush the cornflakes and then mix in a large bowl with the other ingredients.
Wrap a small quantity of the mixture around the end of a stick, making it long instead of into a round ball.
Wrap foil around the meat and part of the stick to prevent the meat from falling into the coals.
Place it over a bed of coals, turning it slowly to cook it evenly.
Makes about 7 drumsticks.
Serves 3 to 4.

title: fantasy fudge
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and milk into heavy 2 1/2-quart pan. Bring to a full rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat.
Continue stirring constantly to prevent scorching.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat until well blended.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cool at room temperature.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Makes 3 pounds.

title: bourbon franks
directions: Mix all ingredients except franks.
Cover and simmer 2 hours, stirring occasionally.
Add franks and simmer until heated through.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Mix together the flour, soda, sugar and cocoa. Add water, vanilla and mayonnaise.
Mix well.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch cake pan. Bake at 350° until tests done. Cool and frost with Peanut Butter Frosting.

title: german chocolate cheesecake
directions: Combine all.
Press mixture into bottom and sides of 9-inch spring-form pan.
Chill.

title: cranberry apple bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease 8 1/2 x 4 1/2-inch loaf pan. Combine apples, sugar and oil in medium mixing bowl.
Add eggs; mix well.
Combine dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add to apple mixture, mixing just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cranberries and walnuts.
Spread batter evenly in pan.
Bake 1 hour or until a toothpick comes out clean.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: spoon bread
directions: Mix corn meal, 1 cup milk and water in a 2-quart saucepan. Cook, stirring, constantly over medium heat until very thick. Remove from heat.
Stir in slightly beaten egg yolks, 2/3 cup milk, shortening, baking powder and salt until smooth.
Beat egg whites in small bowl until whites hold soft peaks.
Fold into corn mixture.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 55 minutes.
Serve immediately as potato or rice substitute.

title: ginger cookies
directions: Bring molasses and Crisco to boil.
When cool, add remaining ingredients.
Mix and refrigerate about 1 hour, roll out.
Cut, then bake.
The less you handle the dough and less flour, the nicer they are.
Sprinkle sugar over before baking.

title: impossible pie
directions: Grease and flour 10-inch pie dish. Pour all ingredients into blender and blend well. Pour into pie dish. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: rum cake
directions: Mix together.
Bake for 1 hour at 325°.

title: barbecue chicken - oven style
directions: Blend
all
sauce
ingredients	in a bowl.
Dip chicken pieces in	sauce;	place in baking pan.
Pour 1/2 of remaining sauce over chicken; cover pan with foil.
Bake in a 400° oven for 45 minutes.
Remove
foil, pour on rest of sauce and bake for 15 minutes, uncovered, or until chicken is tender.

title: queso
directions: Brown and drain ground beef.
Add all ingredients to a crock-pot.
Cook on low until cheese is melted, stirring occasionally.
Serve with tortilla chips.
This dip is always a hit at parties.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken, then debone.
Place chicken in bottom of large casserole dish.
Spread cream of chicken soup over chicken.
Mix stuffing mix according to package directions, except substitute the chicken broth for water.
Spread over chicken soup in casserole dish.
Pour 1/2 cup milk over dressing.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes, covered, then uncover and bake 15 minutes longer.

title: applesauce cookies
directions: Cream sugar, Crisco and egg.
Add dry ingredients into creamed mixture alternately with applesauce.
Fold in 1 cup raisins.
Drop by teaspoon, onto greased cookie sheets, about 2 inches apart. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar and corn syrup together until sugar is dissolved. Add peanuts and cook until mixture turns a gold brown color.
Add butter, salt and baking soda.
Stir and pour onto buttered cookie sheet, spreading quickly to cover surfaces.
Break into pieces when cool and eat, eat and eat.
Delicious to the taste.

title: easy cream cheese bars
directions: Pat 1 cookie roll in bottom of a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix sugar, cream cheese, eggs and vanilla until creamy. Spread over cookie batter. Slice second cookie roll over top.
Pat to blend edges. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Refrigerate.

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Brown bacon and onion.
Add ketchup, brown sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Simmer for 2 minutes.
Place beans in casserole.
Pour mix over beans.
Do not stir.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: vive empress chez marie's roast
directions: Place roast, fat side up, on rack in shallow roasting pan. Sprinkle salt and pepper.
Rub with garlic and insert garlic cloves in small gashes in surface of lamb.
Insert meat thermometer through fat side into center of roast.
Place in slow oven (325°) and roast about 25 minutes per pound for medium or to a temperature of 165°, about 28 minutes per pound for medium or to a temperature of 175° or to 180° for well done.
About 2 hours before roast is done, take from oven; remove rack.
Set meat in pan.
Combine mushrooms including liquid with onions and add to drippings in pan.
Continue roasting, basting with onion-mushroom sauce several times.
Serves 10 to 12.
Let roast sit about 20 minutes before serving to allow for easier slicing.
Keep warm until serving time.

title: black forest brownies
directions: Combine ingredients, mixing these by hand. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased and floured pan.
Bake in a preheated 350° oven for 25 minutes.

title: lois's rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Cream shortening and sugar, adding 2 cups warm water, yeast and salt.
Mix well and add flour.
Mix well.
Put in large greased bowl, greasing top of dough.
Cover and put in icebox.
(Will keep 1 week.)
Pinch to size wanted.
Put on greased cookie sheet or muffin tins.
Let rise 2 hours.
Cook at 400° for 12 to 14 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: instant hot chocolate mix
directions: Makes about 5 quarts of chocolate mix.
Use 3 to 4 spoonfuls per cup hot water.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: In a large bowl, cream softened margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Beat in eggs until light.
Beat in applesauce.
Stir in flour, soda and salt.
Stir to moisten.
Spoon into muffin tins.

title: mexican pinto beans
directions: Put cooked pinto beans into small bowl.
Add salsa; top with cheese.
Put in microwave until cheese melts.
This puts some umph in an ordinary dish.

title: chicken 'n ham roll-ups
directions: Place chicken between 2 sheets of waxed paper; flatten with side of knife.
Top each with slice of ham.
Roll up; secure with toothpicks.
In skillet, brown roll-ups in butter.
Stir in soup; cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes, or until tender. Stir occasionally.
Serve with asparagus if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: tuna chili (low calorie)
directions: Put the tomato juice,
onion and seasoning in a pot and bring to a boil; simmer
on
low	while
you open the tuna and drain well.
Add tuna
to
the
liquid
and mix real well; let simmer 2 or 3 minutes.
Put into refrigerator. Wait at least 4 hours before reheating and serving.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: cranberry almond muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease a 12-cup muffin tin.
Combine flour, both sugars, baking powder and salt in a medium mixing bowl.
Combine milk, oil, egg and almond extract in a separate mixing bowl. Add liquid ingredients to dry, stirring just until dry ingredients are moist.
Stir in cranberries.
Fill muffin cups 3/4 of the way full with batter.
Sprinkle tops with sugar and almonds.

title: raw vegetable dip
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand in refrigerator for at least 8 hours.

title: kahlua
directions: Melt the sugar in the coffee until its all dissolved into a syrup.
Cool, then add 1/5 of Brandy or Rum.
Cut a vanilla bean into snips and put some in each jar.
Let sit 3 weeks. Serve with family and friends.

title: betty's green grape pie
directions: Place berries in uncooked pie shell.
Mix sugar and flour. Add juice and beaten eggs and mix well.
Pour over the green grapes.
Put a little pie dough on top, crisscrossing, lattice, etc.
Sprinkle with sugar and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.
Makes 1 (9-inch) pie.
To make cobbler, just double the recipe.

title: sweet and saucy meatballs
directions: Mix ground meat, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce together.
Make bite size meatballs and bake at 350° for about 35 to 40 minutes.
Mix together chili sauce, barbecue sauce, mustard and brown sugar.
Pour over meatballs in crock-pot.
Let simmer for about 1 hour.

title: breakfast puffs
directions: Mix thoroughly the butter, egg and sugar. Mix dry ingredients. Combine dry ingredients with egg mix alternately with 1/2 cup milk. Fill greased muffin tins 2/3 full. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Immediately roll in 6 tablespoons melted butter, then in sugar/cinnamon mix.

title: cathedral window cookies
directions: Melt chocolate and butter.
Add sugar and egg.
Put marshmallows in large bowl; pour chocolate mixture over them. Stir until marshmallows are well coated.
Roll into logs.
Roll in coconut.
Refrigerate.
May be frozen.

title: french coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Place in unbaked pie shells.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: christmas punch
directions: Mix all together.
Chill before serving or serve over ice.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook rice and broccoli and set aside.
In a skillet saute vegetables with margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
When vegetables are done, add soup and milk and cook about 5 minutes. In a large bowl mix broccoli and rice and add the sauteed vegetables; stir well.
Put everything else in a casserole (leave room for bubbling while cooking).
Spread Cheez Whiz over the top.
If desired, slice mushrooms over the top.
Bake at 325° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: french silk pie
directions: Mix butter, sugar, chocolate and vanilla.
Beat in eggs at high speed for 6 to 8 minutes.
Pour into cooled, baked pie shell. Refrigerate.
Serve with whipped cream.
This is a delicious summertime dessert!

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 8 or 9-inch baking dish while oven is preheating to 350°.
Set aside.
Combine flour, sugar and about 1/2 of milk. Stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Add remaining milk and stir until smooth.
Pour batter over melted butter.
Do not mix. Place drained fruit over top.
Do not mix.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until lightly browned and center springs back when touched. Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: zesty tomato soup
directions: Mix soup, sauce and milk together until well blended.
Cube cheese slices and add to soup mixture.
Heat until the cheese is melted.
Serve with sandwiches and crackers.
Serves 4.

title: garden puree soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine all ingredients and cook on medium heat for 9 to 11 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
Before serving, garnish with seasoned croutons or small pretzel rings, if desired.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix together.
Chill.
Form into a ball and roll in finely chopped nuts.

title: easy noodles
directions: Heat butter in Dutch oven over medium heat until melted.
Add celery and onion; cook until tender.
Add broth; bring to boil. Stir in noodles, salt and pepper.
Simmer 35 minutes or until noodles are tender.
Stir in meat and sage.

title: quick and easy diabetic salad dressing
directions: In a pint jar, combine olive oil, vinegar, parsley, lemon juice and sweetener; close tightly and shake. Makes 4 servings.

title: earthquake cake
directions: Spray oblong pan with Pam.
Add coconut and pecans.
Mix cake mix as directed and pour over nut mixture.
Mix the sugar, butter and cream cheese.
Pour over cake mix.
Cook at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut beef into 3 x 1-inch strips; brown in oil in skillet. Transfer to a slow cooker.
Combine the next 7 ingredients; pour over beef.
Cover; cook on low for 5 to 6 hours, or until meat is tender.
Add tomatoes and green peppers; cook on low 1 hour longer.
Combine the cold water and cornstarch to make a paste; stir into liquid in slow cooker and cook on high until thickened. Serve over noodles or rice.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: japanese fruit pie(2 pies)
directions: Beat eggs slightly.
Add other ingredients and pour into pie shell.
Bake on 300° for 50 to 55 minutes.

title: green tomato jam
directions: Mix tomatoes and sugar; boil 15 minutes.
Turn off heat and add jello.
Stir until dissolved.
Put in jars and seal.
Tastes just like raspberry jam.
Delicious!

title: cheddar cheese casserole
directions: Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes, uncovered.
Stir a few times while cooking.
Serve with small pumpernickel bread.

title: apple torte
directions: Combine all ingredients until well mixed (it is hard to mix). Bake in a 9 x 13-inch greased pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: zucchini squash soup(delicious)
directions: Saute onion and garlic in oil and butter in large saucepan. Add zukes, salt and pepper.
Cook until tender.
Stir in flour and broth; bring to boil.
Cook 5 minutes; cool.
Puree in blender part at a time.
Serve hot or cold.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare pasta according to package.
Rinse, drain and cool. Pour dressing, seasoning and other ingredients; mix well. Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: reese's cups
directions: Mix together 1 stick melted margarine, sugar, vanilla, peanut butter and brown sugar and spread in pan about 1/2 inch thick. Melt chocolate chips and 1 stick of margarine.
Mix together and spread over peanut butter mixture.
Let cool.

title: kool-aid play dough
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients in a bowl.
Boil 2 cups water.
Add water and 3 tablespoons oil to dry ingredients.
Knead together until well mixed.
Let cool.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Mix chicken, soups, milk and vegetables together. Cook in oven until vegetables are tender. Remove and place biscuits on top of mixture. Put back in oven and let biscuits rise and brown.

title: stuffed rolls
directions: Hard-boil the eggs (run through grinder).
Chop the green onions.
Grate the cheese.
Add other ingredients and mix well. Stuff hot dog buns with mixture. Wrap in foil and heat in a 350° oven for about 1/2 hour until cheese is melted.
Leftover unheated rolls may be frozen.

title: tony's ricotta cheese cake
directions: Blend Ricotta and cream cheese well.
Blend in sugar.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, lemon juice, cornstarch, flour and butter.
Fold in sour cream and blend well.
Pour into a 10-inch buttered spring-form pan that has been dusted liberally with graham cracker crumbs.
Place in cold oven and turn heat to 325°.
Bake 1 hour.
Do not open oven door.
Turn off oven and leave until cool, at least 2 more hours.
(Serve plain or with cherry pie filling or other fruit topping, if desired.)

title: gazpacho
directions: In a saucepan, bring water to a boil.
Stir in the soup mix until dissolved.
Cool slightly.
In a blender, add 1/2 of soup mixture and half of the other ingredients.
Top off with tomato juice; blend for a few seconds to assure the vegetables are chopped finely, but not pureed.
Pour mixture in a plastic container.
Prepare the remaining ingredients the same way.
Top with a tablespoon of sour cream and Croutons.
Makes 1 gallon.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs until thick and lemony.
Add next 6 ingredients. Beat well and pour into ungreased jelly roll pan.
Spread peanut butter on top while hot.

title: kahlua
directions: Boil water, put in coffee.
Remove from fire.
Add sugar, cool until cold.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Makes 2 liters.

title: baked chicken
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt butter in a large skillet over medium heat.
Brown chicken slowly.
Place in shallow baking dish.
Add onion and mushrooms; cook until limp.
Mix remaining ingredients, pouring over chicken.
Bake 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Mix yeast in 5 Tbsp. lukewarm water. Mix and keep in refrigerator until needed: Spoon out on greased pan with a tablespoon and let set 10-15 minutes to rise before baking. Bake at 450 degrees about 15 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 350°.

title: dockside casserole(microwave)
directions: In 2-cup glass measure, mix soup, sour cream, sherry dill and pepper.
In medium bowl, mix cooked rice, broccoli and 1/2 cup of the soup mixture.
In buttered 9 x 9-inch microwave dish, arrange rice mixture.
Top with fish and onion, putting thickest part of fish toward outside of dish.
Cover with waxed paper and microwave on High for 10 minutes or until fish flakes easily, rotating twice during baking.
Remove from microwave and keep covered.
Microwave remaining soup mixture on High for 4 minutes and serve as a sauce.

title: rice and mushrooms
directions: Melt oleo and brown onion and rice lightly.
Mix with soup; pour into casserole dish and bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: monkey bread
directions: Cut buttermilk rolls into small pieces.
Roll pieces in cinnamon and granulated sugar.
Drop into a Bundt pan.
Melt 1 cup brown sugar and 1/2 cup margarine in saucepan.
Pour this over biscuits in Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes. Invert onto serving plate.

title: calico beans
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and pepper; drain.
Add to other ingredients.
May use more or less of seasoning to taste.
Mix well.
Place in 9 inch or larger baking dish.
Bake at 350 degree for 1 hour.

title: cheesy oven fries
directions: Cut potatoes in 8 wedges.
Set aside.
Combine Parmesan and next
ingredients, stirring well.
Dip potato wedges in melted oleo
and
arrange single layer in lightly greased 15 x 10 x 1-inch
dish.
Sprinkle cheese mix on potatoes.
Bake 40 minutes at 375°, uncovered, or until tender.

title: sweet and sour chicken
directions: Place chicken in baking dish.
Mix dressing, jam, dry soup mix and water together.
Pour over chicken.
Cover with foil.
Bake for 1/2 hour in a 350° oven.
Uncover.
Place pepper rings on top of chicken.
Bake another 1/2 hour.

title: cinnamon apple rings
directions: Make a syrup of the sugar and water; add the red candy and food coloring.
Core and peel the apples, slicing into 3 to 4 rings each.
Cook the rings in the syrup until tender.

title: lemon sherbet
directions: Milk may seem to curdle, but it will work out.
Mix sugar, lemon juice and salt together. Add to milk slowly.
Mix in cream last.
Place in freezer pan and freeze until firm.
Mix together again and allow to freeze solid, 3 to 4 hours.

title: easy apple cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Combine milk, flour and 1/2 cup of sugar in bowl; mix thoroughly.
Pour into pan over melted margarine.
Do not stir.
Combine remaining ingredients.
Do not stir.
Cook at 350° until apples are cooked. Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean salad
directions: Mix green beans, onion, green pepper and salad dressing; refrigerate.
Serve cold.

title: lemon fruit dressing
directions: Cook first 3 ingredients in double boiler until thickened. Cool.
When ready to serve, add whipped cream.
Use over pineapple chunks and sliced bananas.
Will keep a week or more.

title: peach bars
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir in oats and sugar.
Cut in butter until mixture is crumbly.
Pat 2/3 of the mixture into an 11 x 7-inch pan.
Spread with preserves.
Cover evenly with remaining crumb mixture and pat down gently.
Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes or until it just begins to turn golden brown. Cool completely and cut into squares.

title: lemon chicken
directions: Place each chicken breast on a 12-inch square of aluminum foil. Sprinkle 1 Tablespoon of lemon juice on each breast, then sprinkle with the tarragon and garlic powder.
Carefully fold the foil so that the lemon juice can't run out.
Bake at 350 for 20-25 minutes.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix cool whip with pudding thoroughly.
Add all other ingredients.
Mix and chill for 1 hour.

title: hanky panky
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Melt cheese.
Combine sausage and cheese.
Place bread on cookie sheet, sides touching.
Spoon cheese and sausage mixture onto bread.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: chocolate covered pecans(turtles)
directions: Combine caramels and milk in top of double boiler.
Heat over water until melted.
Stir occasionally.
Stir in pecans.
Drop onto buttered wax paper.
Cool at least 15 minutes.
Combine chocolate and paraffin in top of double boiler.
Heat until melted. Using toothpick, dip each cluster in chocolate.
Cool on wax paper.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Cook sugar, water, cornstarch and salt, stirring constantly until mixture thickens and becomes opaque.
Remove from heat, add Jell-O, mixing well.
Let cool 5 to 7 minutes.
Add strawberries, pour into two already baked pie crusts and refrigerate.
Top with Cool Whip when served.

title: apple, carrot muffins
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients in a large bowl.
Stir in carrots, apple, raisins, almonds and coconut.
Make a well in the center of mixture.
Combine eggs, oil and vanilla; add to dry ingredients, stirring just until moistened.
Spoon into greased muffin tins or pan until 2/3 full.
Bake at 350° for 20 or 25 minutes.
Remove from pan immediately.
Yields 24 muffins.

title: grape gelatin mold
directions: Mix grape juice concentrate with water.
Dissolve gelatine in 1 cup of juice.
Add sugar, salt and two cups grape juice, heated. Stir until sugar is dissolved; add lemon juice and chill until partially set.
Add remaining ingredients. Pour into mold and chill until firm.

title: german chocolate brownies
directions: Mix dry cake mix with melted butter and 1/4 cup of evaporated milk.
Spread 1/2 of this mixture on bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cook for 6 minutes at 350°.
Cook all caramels and rest of milk until creamy (double boiler or glass bowl in microwave).
Sprinkle chocolate chips on cooled cake.
Spread caramel mixture on top.
Crumble rest of cake mix mixture on top and bake 15 to 18 minutes longer.
Cool before serving.

title: baked chicken reuben
directions: Arrange chicken in greased baking pan.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Drain sauerkraut; squeeze dry.
Spread over chicken.
Top with Swiss cheese.
Pour salad dressing evenly over cheese.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 325° for about 1 1/2 hours.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Yields 4 servings.

title: cole slaw
directions: Shred cabbage finely.
Combine all ingredients in a bowl. Pour dressing over cabbage.
Toss lightly.
Let salad stand a short time for flavors to blend.

title: trifle
directions: Prepare yellow cake mix and leave to cool. In large glass bowl, prepare pack of Jell-O. Before the Jell-O sets, add 1/4 of the cake (cubed) and fruit. After the Jell-O is set, place 1/4 of the cake (cubed) on top of the set Jell-O. Prepare vanilla pudding and pour over cake and set Jell-O. Chill and top with
Cool Whip.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Spread one side of bread slices with butter.
Stack and cut in 1-inch cubes.
Place in greased 12 x 8-inch baking dish.
Add ham, cheese and sauerkraut; toss to mix.
With fork beat the eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over bread mixture.
Bake in preheated oven for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°, until top is lightly browned and egg mixture is set.
Makes 4 main dish servings.

title: dirt pie
directions: Cream sugar and cream cheese.
Mix pudding with milk.
Fold in whipped cream.
Mix all together.
Crush cookies in blender.
In a large clear bowl, begin layering cookies, pudding, cookies and so on, ending with cookies on top.

title: heart healthy luscious cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Spray two 9-inch round cake pans with nonstick cooking spray.
Mix cake mix, water, applesauce and egg whites in a large bowl with electric beater at low speed until moistened.
Beat 2 minutes at high speed or beat 2 minutes by hand.
Pour half of the batter into each prepared pan.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes or until done.
Cool in pan on rack and remove.
When completely cool, layer and frost cake with your favorite frosting. Very moist and delicious.

title: pat's diet cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients well.
Drop by teaspoonful onto ungreased cookie sheet and bake 10 to 15 minutes or until golden brown.

title: salmon loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Then put into a greased loaf pan. Bake 20 minutes at 425°.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit (except cherries).
Measure drained juice and add enough water to make four cups.
Put in saucepan and bring to a boil.
Add pudding mix; cook for one minute, stirring often. Arrange fruit in a bowl and pour sauce over fruit.
Mash bananas under sauce to keep them from turning brown.
Refrigerate 6 to 8 hours.

title: overnight salad
directions: Add the ingredients in layers in order.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Toss just before serving.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients. Mix together to form a loaf. Cook in oblong Pyrex dish at 350° for 45 minutes. Remove from oven. Drain off excess grease. Cover with catsup and cook 15 more minutes. Serve hot.

title: salmon patties
directions: Drain salmon; remove bones and skin.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into patties and fry in 4 tablespoons oil until brown.
Drain.

title: microwave almond crunch
directions: Combine
sugar,
water,
corn
syrup
and butter in a 2 quart glass
mixing bowl.
Microwave, uncovered, for 18 to 20 minutes on
Full
power
or until candy thermometer registers 290°, stirring every 5 minutes.
Using the cold water method, it
should form
a
soft crack consistency.
Stir in almonds. Pour at
once onto a buttered cookie sheet.
Cool.
Break into pieces.
Makes 1 1/2 pounds.

title: banana cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening together.
Add eggs and milk; mix well, then add sifted flour, salt and soda.
Mix well.
Fold in bananas and nuts.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: breakfast gravy
directions: Use a whisk to stir flour into grease.
(Grease should cover bottom of skillet.)
Wait until it bubbles, then add milk.
Stir constantly.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low.

title: onion ring batter
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt into medium size bowl.
Stir in egg, water, lemon juice and Wesson oil until blended.
Dip onion rings in batter a few at a time and cook in hot oil, heated to 375°.
Keep hot in oven until all are cooked.

title: migajan("kids can have fun")
directions: Crumble white bread until fine with no large lumps.
Add glue. It will be sticky!
Knead until it has the consistency of play dough.
Add desired food coloring.
Use a cookie cutter to make desired shapes.
Lay out on a flat dry surface for several days. Turn these over every so often in order for them to dry evenly. When dry, spray with polyurethane to preserve.
These make excellent ornaments, jewelry or refrigerator magnets.

title: candied yams
directions: Boil potatoes until done, but not soggy.
Cool and take jacket off.
Cut in pieces and put in pan or glass dish.
Cook next 4 items together, until melted well.
Pour over sweet potatoes.

title: easy sausage and beans
directions: Cook sliced sausage in approximately 6 cups of water for 1 hour, covered.
Add beans and mix well.
Sprinkle with basil and cook approximately 15 minutes on low heat, uncovered.
In a cup or bowl, serve over cooked rice and top with raw chopped onion.
Serve with cornbread.

title: corned beef casserole
directions: In heavy skillet, cook onion in butter until tender and transparent.
Place potatoes in bottom of buttered 2-quart casserole and season to taste.
Add corned beef and eggs over potatoes; add cooked onion.
Combine cream of mushroom soup, milk and grated cheese.
Pour mixture over casserole.
Blend any remaining butter in skillet with dry bread crumbs.
Sprinkle crumbs on top of casserole.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes. Sprinkle with paprika and serve with ketchup.
Yield: 4 to 6 servings.

title: pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Prepare cake mix according to directions on package.
Melt butter in ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle brown sugar evenly in pan.
Arrange pineapple slices on brown sugar.
Place cherry halves in center of pineapple slices.
Pour cake batter over pineapple slices.
Bake according to directions on cake package.
Cool 5 minutes in pan.
Remove from pan by turning onto platter.

title: millionaire pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into 2 graham cracker crust pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
Chill 24 hours.

title: coquilles jacques
directions: Wash scallops.
Drain.
Slice in half and set aside.
Saute onion or chopped shallots in frying pan.
Add canned mushrooms and juice.
Saute with shallots or onions.
Add parsley, white wine and then cream.
Saute.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Layer cucumbers
and salt.
Chill 2 hours.
Drain and rinse. Add onions and lemon and toss.
Combine vinegar and next four ingredients and shake in a tightly covered container.
Pour over cucumbers and toss.
Serve.

title: seven layer salad
directions: Put torn lettuce into dish for bottom layer.
Add green pepper for second layer and the onion for the third layer.
For the fourth layer, add celery.
Add peas for fifth layer and shredded Cheddar for sixth layer.

title: low calorie fruit salad
directions: Add Tang to pineapple juice.
Pour over fruit.
Sprinkle 1 package diet instant vanilla pudding over fruit and mix well. Refrigerate.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots, then mix with green pepper and red onion.
Mix together the remaining ingredients.
Pour over carrots.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator for 24 hours.
Drain all the sauce before serving.

title: jello rings
directions: Pour off liquid from can of pineapple; replace with Jell-O made with boiling water.
Chill until set.

title: rock and roll raisin mix
directions: Heat butter with Worcestershire sauce, chili powder and seasoned salt in large pan.
Add peanuts, pretzels, wheat and rice squares.
Spread out on baking sheet and bake at 250° for 45 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add raisins and bake 15 minutes longer.
Cool and store in Tupperware container.
Makes
8 cups.

title: arnold flecher cake
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into 3 layer cake pans.
Bake at 350°.

title: venison bake
directions: Slowly cook venison until tender (2 hours in oven).
When done, mix in electric skillet the venison, flour, salt, pepper, tomatoes, mushrooms, onions, soy sauce and beer and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serve hot over buttered egg noodles.

title: tahitian punch
directions: In large punch bowl, stir together juices and carbonated beverage.
Spoon sherbet into bowl.
Serve immediately.
Makes 38 servings (about 1/2 cup each).

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In a skillet, heat the oil and brown the onion. Add the ground beef, garlic, 2 tablespoons parsley, 1/4 teaspoon pepper and 1/4 cup Parmesan cheese. Cook until the beef is browned and transfer to a dish.

title: jewish apple cake
directions: Place first 3 ingredients in mixing bowl.
Make a hole in the center of the mixture and put in the vanilla, eggs, oil and orange juice.
Beat until smooth.
Combine 2/3 cup sugar and 1/3 cup cinnamon and mix.
If you wish to use more of this mixture than is called for in the recipe, use twice as much additional sugar than cinnamon.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Pour 1/3 of the batter into the bottom of the pan.
Place a layer of apple slices on top and sprinkle with 1/3 of the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Add 1/3 more of the batter topped with apple layer and 1/3 more of the cinnamon sugar mixture.
Top with rest of the batter and sprinkle with the rest of cinnamon and sugar.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: baked red snapper with crab stuffing
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Heat butter.
Add onion and saute until tender.

title: chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken until tender.
Take meat off bones.
Spread chicken pieces in large baking pan.
Chop two boiled eggs; spread over chicken.
Bring to boil one can of chicken soup and two cups of broth.
Pour over chicken in pan.
Mix flour, buttermilk and margarine.
Pour over chicken in pan (do not stir).
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes or until brown.

title: peppermint stick crisps
directions: Thoroughly cream sugar and shortening; sift dry ingredients together.
Combine egg and milk.
Add sifted dry ingredients to shortening mixture alternately with egg and milk mixture.
Drop from teaspoon on greased cookie sheet.
Flatten cookies by pressing lightly with glass (dipped in flour).
Sprinkle each with 1/4 teaspoon candy.
Bake in 350° oven for 12 minutes.
Makes 3 1/2 dozen.

title: swedish nuts
directions: Toast nuts on a flat pan with sides at 325° until slightly browned.
Fold sugar and salt into beaten egg whites.
Beat until mixture forms stiff peaks.
Fold nuts into mixture.
Melt butter in oven in same pan used for browning nuts.
Spread nuts and egg mixture over butter.
Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.
Stir every 10 minutes.
Be careful they don't burn.

title: 5 flavor pound cake
directions: *I change about on my flavors.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Mix well.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cool.

title: minnie morse's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix.
Drop
by teaspoons for drop cookies and bake in a 350° oven about 15 minutes.

title: smoked oyster log
directions: Combine softened cream cheese and mayonnaise; blend well. Stir in next 4 ingredients.
Spread 1/4 inch thick on waxed paper. Chill at least 30 minutes.
Spread oysters on cream cheese mixture and roll up jellyroll fashion.
Roll log in dried green onion.
Chill overnight.
Cut in 1/2 inch slices.
Serve with crackers.
Yield:
about 2 dozen slices.

title: crab mold
directions: Dissolve gelatine in hot water; microwave and pour in soup. Cool for 15 minutes.
Beat cream cheese; add onions, celery, pimento, crab and mayonnaise.
Pour into mold.
Chill overnight.

title: christmas cookies
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugars.
Beat in eggs; add remaining ingredients.
Add dates, cherries and pecans.
Dough will be stiff. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes.
Makes 7 dozen.
May be frozen for later.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Mix lukewarm water, sugar, salt and shortening together, then add yeast and egg.
Next, add flour, saving 1 cup for kneading. After kneading for a few minutes, put in greased bowl.
Cover and let rise until double.
Punch down and let rise again, then make out into rolls.
Let rise.
Bake in greased pans at 400° for 16 to 20 minutes or until nice and brown.
This dough can be made and put in refrigerator the day before you need it.

title: chicken stuffed crescent rolls
directions: Cream butter and cream cheese together.
Add lemon pepper, mushrooms and chicken.
Place spoonful of mixture at large end of crescent roll and roll towards small end.
Brush with melted butter and sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla with mixer until well blended.
Add eggs; mix again until well blended.
Pour into crust.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set. Cool; refrigerate for 3 hours or overnight.
Top with fruit. Serves 8 to 10.

title: quick fudge pie
directions: Cream margarine, sugar and eggs.
Add cocoa.
Mix well.
Add flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in an 8-inch pie plate at 325° for 25 minutes.
Let cool before serving.
(Creates its own crust.)
Great with whipped cream or ice cream.

title: bacon pinwheels
directions: Mix crumbled bacon, mushrooms, mayo and garlic powder; set aside.
Unroll crescent rolls and press together.
Spread with softened cream cheese and spread bacon mixture on top.
Roll up the rolls and slice thin as you would cinnamon rolls.
Bake for 9 minutes at 350°.

title: my favorite snack:  bologna and cheese
directions: Lay down the bologna.
Put the cheese on top.
Roll up the bologna.

title: cheesy mashed potatoes
directions: Melt butter in saucepan over medium heat.
Add onion.
Cook until transparent.
Remove from heat.
Mash potatoes.
Add milk until consistency of mashed potatoes.
Stir in cheese and onions. Transfer potatoes to a buttered 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes, covered in foil.
Uncover and bake an additional 20 minutes.

title: creamy cabbage
directions: Cover the cabbage with cold water and let stand for about 1 hour; drain and put in large saucepan.
Cover with boiling water. Simmer uncovered for 7 minutes.
Do not overcook.
Combine the remaining ingredients and fold in the cabbage.
Turn into buttered baking dish.
Bake 30 minutes at 375°.

title: humdingers
directions: Cook oleo, sugar and dates on low heat for 8 minutes; stir constantly.
Add vanilla, nuts and rice crispies; mix well. Butter hands and roll the mixture into "fingers" and dip into powdered sugar.

title: radish dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Serve with breadsticks, tortilla chips or raw vegetables.

title: old-fashioned sugar cookies
directions: Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
In a large mixer bowl, beat butter and shortening.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add egg, milk and vanilla and beat well.
Add flour mixture and beat until well mixed.
Divide dough in half.
Cover and chill at least 3 hours.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Mix the sugar, water and cornstarch. Cook until thick and clear. Add the Jell-O and vanilla. Add cake coloring, if needed. Cook until thickness desired. Cool.
Pour strawberries in your favorite pastry shell.
Pour filling over berries.
Add more berries and then more filling until all is used.
Use about 1 quart berries. Chill.

title: frozen pineapple salad
directions: Mix and spoon into muffin tin lined with baking cups.

title: fresh corn salad
directions: In large pan, cover corn with water and boil 5 to 7 minutes, or until tender.
Drain.
Set aside to cool.

title: broccoli crunch
directions: Combine the above ingredients.

title: divinity
directions: Combine corn syrup, water and sugar; boil to hard ball stage (265°).
Beat egg whites stiff and gradually beat in boiling syrup.
Whip until it begins to stiffen.
Add vanilla and nuts. Drop onto waxed paper.
Makes about 150 pieces.
This is a real old recipe, one that was used when my Mom was a little girl.

title: raisin drop cookies
directions: Boil water and raisins together 5 minutes and cool.
Blend together shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla.
Add raisin mixture. Add dry ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop on greased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes at 400°.

title: supper in the oven
directions: You will also need aluminum foil.

title: apple strudel
directions: Peel and slice apples.
Place in a buttered pan.
Mix sugar and cinnamon and sprinkle over apples.
Cream butter, brown sugar and add flour and nuts.
Pour over apples.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: balkan supper
directions: Cook noodles in 6 cups of water; drain.
Brown sausage in oil, cooking about 5 minutes on each side.
Remove from skillet.
Saute cabbage, onions, salt, pepper and caraway seed about 20 minutes. Add noodles, brown sugar and vinegar.
Mix together.
Arrange noodles and cabbage on dish and top with sausage.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Spoon into lightly greased 1-quart casserole or souffle dish.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Serve hot with crackers.
Yield: about 5 cups.
One-half of the recipe will serve 4 people and fit into a 9-inch pie dish.

title: spinach-cheese pie
directions: Mix croutons and oleo well.
Press into bottom of a 9-inch pie plate.
Combine rest of ingredients except Parmesan cheese and spoon over crust.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until set. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: flonnie's biscuit-style-chicken pie
directions: Mix thoroughly to form batter. Spoon batter (biscuit-style) over chicken in pan. (This leaves space for gravy cracks.)
Bake at 425° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: lutheran punch
directions: Mix in a glass jar.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt oleo in a baking dish.
Mix and blend flour, sugar, baking powder, salt and milk.
Pour into buttered dish.
Do not stir after pouring into butter.
Open 1 large can sliced peaches.
Pour peaches and juice over batter in the dish.
Do not stir.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Other fruit can be used in place of peaches.

title: barbecued salmon steaks
directions: Make marinade by mixing butter, soy sauce, Worcestershire sauce, lemon juice, garlic, hot pepper sauce and liquid smoke. Brush marinade over salmon steaks generously; place on grill over hot coals, grill, allowing 20 minutes per inch of thickness or until fish flakes easily.
Turn over halfway through cooking time. Baste frequently with marinade during cooking and once after taking off grill.

title: meat loaf
directions: Combine all ingredients with 1/2 cup catsup.
Pack firmly into shape of loaf in an ungreased loaf pan.
Make a crease in middle of loaf.
Mix remaining 1/2 cup catsup and honey.
Fill the valley and brush top of loaf.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: prize winning lemonade pie
directions: Preheat oven to 450°.
Grease one cookie sheet.
In a heavy saucepan, combine water, butter, sugar and salt.
Bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add flour all at once.
Stir hard until mixture forms a ball in the middle of the saucepan. Cool slightly.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Place soup, water and chicken in pot to boil.
Add rice and other ingredients.
Place in greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake, covered, at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: vegetable beef soup
directions: Cut beef in small pieces; brown well in shortening.
Place meat and all other ingredients in crock pot.
Cook on high for 6 hours.

title: pineapple nut bread
directions: Mix flour, sugar, salt, baking powder and baking soda.
Beat egg in large bowl.
Stir in oil and pineapple.
Add flour mixture and partially blend.
Add Bran cereal and nuts.
Stir until ingredients are just moistened.
Pour into a greased loaf tin. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground beef and onion.
Add vegetables and both soups (do not dilute).
Place mixture in casserole dish; top with Tater Tots.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: strawberry cream salad
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add strawberries and stir occasionally until thawed.
Add pineapple, bananas and pecans and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of mixture into long dish and chill until firm.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over top.
Pour remaining jello mixture over sour cream and chill until firm.

title: waldorf salad
directions: Core apples.
Pare if desired, or leave red-skinned apples unpeeled.
Dice them and sprinkle with lemon juice.
Combine apples with celery and salt.
Blend together mayonnaise, sugar and sour cream.
Pour over apple mixture, tossing lightly with a fork until apple pieces are well coated.
Arrange salad in lettuce cups.
Sprinkle with walnuts.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: beef stew
directions: Heat fat in Dutch oven.
Add beef chuck; brown on all sides. Add sliced onion and garlic, boiling water, salt, lemon juice, sugar, Worcestershire sauce, pepper, paprika, bay leaf and allspice or cloves.
Cover and gently simmer (not boil) for 2 hours, stirring now and then.
When meat is almost done, add vegetables.
Simmer stew about 30 minutes longer or until everything is done.
Pour cold water into shaker, then add flour. Shake hard to blend.
Remove from heat.
Push meat and vegetables to one side of the pan; stir in flour mixture.
Cook, stirring constantly, until the gravy thickens and boils.
Cook gently about 5 minutes more.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: orange sherbet
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Pour into freezer can.
If it does not completely fill can, add a little milk.
Put in electric freezer with ice and salt.
Freeze as usual.

title: parmesan chicken
directions: Mix eggs and pepper.
Roll chicken in egg mixture and then in the bread crumbs.
Cook in oil until brown on both sides.
Set aside.
Mix tomato sauce, seasonings, Parmesan cheese and butter in saucepan.
Heat on stove.
Put chicken in casserole dish and pour sauce over top.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes, covered. Uncover and sprinkle Mozzarella cheese on top.
Return to oven and heat until cheese is melted.

title: grandma's banana salad dressing
directions: Combine ingredients except the lemon, butter and bananas. Cook until thick; remove from heat and add the lemon and butter. Put over sliced bananas and add crushed peanuts.

title: cereal sundae
directions: Fill your bowl 1/2 way with cereal.
Add ice cream on top. Add more cereal.
Stir together and eat.

title: justin-mannings' southern chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken and cut up into small pieces.
Blend chicken, soup and sour cream into casserole dish (ovenproof).
Crush up Ritz crackers; spread on top of mixture.
Melt butter and pour on top of crackers.
Bake in oven heated to 350° for 1 hour.
Serve with colorful vegetables.

title: asparagus-potato toss
directions: Heat oven to 400. In a large bowl, combine first seven ingredients; reserve 1 Tbsp. In a large bowl, toss potatoes with remaining mixture to coat.
Spread potatoes on baking sheet. Roast 25 minutes.

title: goulash
directions: Brown hamburger meat, onion and green pepper until well done. Add tomatoes and seasonings and simmer for 10 to 15 minutes.
Cook macaroni as directed on package and add to meat mixture.

title: party potatoes
directions: Boil potatoes until done. Mash with other ingredients, except butter and paprika.
Put in a buttered casserole. Dot with butter and sprinkle with paprika.

title: corn salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together using Ranch dressing to desired consistency and taste. Refrigerate. Serve cold.

title: festive rice
directions: Combine all ingredients except whipped cream.
Fold in whipped cream.
Chill.

title: tuna supreme
directions: In saucepan, cook celery and onions in butter until tender. Blend in soup.
Gradually stir in milk.
Add tuna and pimento; heat and stir occasionally.
Garnish with parsley; serve on toasts.
Makes approximately 4 servings.

title: rumaki
directions: Cut each liver into 3 pieces; fold each piece around a water chestnut.
Wrap a piece of bacon around the liver and chestnut and fasten in place with a toothpick.
Marinate in soy sauce mixed with ginger for 1 hour.
Place on a rack in a shallow pan and bake at 425° for 10 minutes, or until bacon is browned and crisp.
Makes 18.

title: sausage and cabbage stew
directions: In a large skillet or Dutch oven, layer ingredients in order listed.
Add enough water to steam.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook, covered, for approximately 30 minutes.
Continue to cook until desired tenderness.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Cook about 1/2 hour, until onions are tender.
Then add leftover roast beef or pork and simmer.
This sauce may be used for Sloppy Joes or to baste pork chops.

title: frozen cheese cream
directions: In covered blender container at low speed, blend cottage cheese with sugar, vanilla and egg until smooth.
In large bowl with mixer at low speed, beat ice cream with cheese mixture until blended.
Pour into 10 x 5-inch loaf pan; cover with foil or plastic wrap and freeze until firm.

title: spicy hot beans
directions: Sort and wash beans.
Put in large Dutch oven and cover with water.
Add 1/2 teaspoon baking soda.
Bring to a boil and boil for 5 minutes.
Drain.
Return to Dutch oven, adding about 6 cups of water.

title: pork chop and rice casserole
directions: Layer pork chops in greased casserole dish.
Spread rice over chops and add water.
Empty can of soup and dry soup over rice. Bake uncovered for 45 to 50 minutes at 375°.

title: spritz
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
In large bowl, blend all ingredients with mixer at low speed.
Roll dough into strips 1-inch apart for the length of ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 8 minutes or until golden brown.
Immediately cut each strip crossways into 2 1/2-inch cookies.
Repeat with remaining dough.

title: lemon pie
directions: Mix together well the first 3 ingredients.
Lay in pie shell starting with lemon filling then the mixture ending with mixture. Chill.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Gather into a ball and chill in freezer awhile.
Form into 3/4 to 1-inch balls.
Place on cookie sheet with sides, as grease will drip during baking.
Bake 25 minutes at 350° or 35 minutes at 325°.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Cut the butter into the first 3 ingredients.
Add sugar, seed and raisins; set aside.
Mix buttermilk, egg and baking soda in separate bowl.
Add to first ingredients.
On a floured board and with floured hands, knead well.
Shape into circular loaf and put in baking pan.
Cook for 1 hour at 350°.

title: alabama biscuits
directions: Heat together milk, oil, sugar and salt until lukewarm. Remove from heat and add yeast until dissolved.
Add baking powder; stir good.
Add flour; stir good.
Knead dough.
Make into biscuits.
Let rise for about 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° for about 20 minutes.

title: quick barbecue sauce
directions: Mix together in small saucepan.
Heat until boiling, stirring as it cooks.

title: vanishing oatmeal cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Beat together butter and sugars until creamy. Add eggs and vanilla. Beat well. Add combined flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt. Mix well. Stir in oats, raisins and nuts. Mix well. Drop by rounded tablespoons onto ungreased cookie sheet. Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until golden brown. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: larry's verification of beauty(cheese cake)
directions: Grease a 9-inch spring-form pan; set aside.
Mix flour, sugar and lemon peel together.
Cut butter or margarine into mixture until it resembles coarse crumbs.
Add egg and stir until mixture forms a ball.
If sticky, add a little flour.
Press dough into pan.
Start at middle and work (fingers of course) up sides until it's covered and smooth all around.
The bottom and sides should be covered.
Use fork to prick sides and bottom.
Easy does it. Freeze until ready to use.

title: banana salad sauce
directions: Heat sugar and vinegar.
Pour over well beaten egg.
While hot, add peanut butter and salt.
Makes about 1 pint.
Serve over sliced bananas.
Sauce may be kept in icebox for a good while.

title: easy pound cake
directions: Cream eggs, butter and vanilla.
Add flour.
Pour into greased and floured tube or Bundt cake pan.
Bake at 300° to 350° for about 1 hour.

title: pumpkin squares
directions: Combine pumpkin, sugar, salt, ginger, cinnamon and nutmeg. Add chopped pecans.
In a chilled bowl, fold pumpkin mixture into softened ice cream.
Line bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan with half of the gingersnaps.

Top with half the ice cream mixture. Cover with another layer of gingersnaps and add remaining ice cream mixture. Freeze until firm, about 5 hours. Cut into squares. Garnish with whipped cream and pecan halves.
Makes 18 servings.

title: dreamy pineapple upside-down cake
directions: Preheat oven to 250°. Melt butter in a large cast-iron skillet or 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Sprinkle brown sugar evenly over melted butter. Arrange pineapple slices over brown sugar to almost cover pan. Place cherry halves in pineapple slices and any other desired pattern. Prepare cake mix as directed on package. Pour over fruit. Bake for 43 to 48 minutes or until done. Cool 5 minutes in pan. Invert onto serving plate.

title: olive balls
directions: Drain juice from olives, reserving 2 tablespoons.
Combine cheese, flour, margarine and hot sauce.
Mix well.
Add enough olive juice to moisten.
Wrap small piece of cheese around each olive.
Bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Do not overbake or cheese will dry out.

title: hot stuffing mix
directions: Combine dry ingredients and all broth; toss to mix.
Makes 4 cups or enough for a 6 pound turkey.

title: brownies
directions: Stir together beaten eggs and sugar.
Add next 4 ingredients and nuts, if desired.
Melt margarine and chocolate over hot water or in microwave. Add to other ingredients. Bake at 350° in a 9 x 13-inch pan (greased) about 35 minutes. Frost with favorite frosting, if desired.

title: onion rings
directions: Beat egg.
Add water, lemon juice and oil.
Beat until frothy. Add flour, baking powder and salt.
Beat until blended.
Divide onions into rings and dip in batter.
Cook in 1-inch oil at 375° to 400°.
Drain on paper.

title: german potato salad
directions: Cook, cool and slice potatoes.
Fry bacon.
Mix sugar, vinegar, water and beaten egg yolks.
Add to bacon and cook until thickens.
Pour over sliced potatoes.
