Let set a few hours before using.

title: eggplant salad
directions: Salt eggplant; place on paper towel, in glass pie plate. Cover tightly; microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Rinse eggplant; dry thoroughly and chop fine.
Mix with tomatoes, onions and parsley.
Add dressing and toss.
Add salt and pepper, if desired. Serve on crisp romaine.
Makes 8 to 12 servings.

title: egg drop soup
directions: Bring soup stock to a boil.
Slowly pour in the cornstarch mixture while stirring the stock until the stock thickens.
Reduce heat so stock just simmers.
Pour in the eggs, slowly while stirring the soup. As soon as the last bit of egg is in, shut off heat at once.
Serve with chopped scallions on top.

title: creamy cucumber salad
directions: Stir jello, boiling water, vinegar and salt until jello is dissolved.
Refrigerate until mixture mounds slightly (approximately 20 to 30 minutes).
Stir in sour cream, cucumber and mayo, then refrigerate until set (approximately 1 1/2 hours).

title: molasses cake
directions: Now follow directions exactly as written:
heat molasses and remove from heat.
Beat soda into molasses.
Add shortening, then buttermilk; stir well.
Add self-rising flour, beating well.
Add spices or vanilla or both (I use both).
Add eggs last then beat hard and well.
Makes 3 layers.
Bake at 350° until done.
Test with toothpick or finger pressure in center.
No matter what you think, add the eggs last!
Ice with Brown Sugar Icing.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix eggs and oil; stir in remaining ingredients, folding in zucchini last.
Spread in greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Cut in squares and serve warm or cold.

title: cracked corn and cheese squares
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees. Grease an 8-inch square baking dish with butter. Stir cheese, corn and scallions into package mixed corn muffin batter.

title: saturday's breakfast
directions: Fry potatoes and onions in margarine until golden brown. Place in greased 8 or 9-inch glass baking dish.
Top with cheese. Crumble sausage and spread over cheese; top with mushrooms. Combine eggs, milk, salt and pepper; pour over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix half of crumb mix to cover bottom of casserole dish. Spread layer of chicken or chicken breast, cut in bite sizes. Cover chicken with sour cream mixed with mushroom soup.
Add remaining half of dressing mix over top of casserole.
Pour 3 cups chicken broth over this.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until firm. Sliced water chestnuts can be added over soup mix if desired.

title: red wine vinegar  chicken
directions: Lightly salt and generously pepper the chicken pieces.
Heat the oil in a skillet large enough to hold all the meat.
Over medium heat, saute the chicken until golden brown, about 6 minutes per side.
Remove the chicken and set it aside.
Keep warm.

title: apricot nectar cake
directions: Mix all in pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour in a 9 x 13-inch pan. Do not open oven while baking.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In large saucepan, combine onions, carrot, celery, garlic and chicken broth.
Bring to boil; add rice.
Cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until rice is tender.
Add broccoli; cover and simmer until broccoli is tender, about 5 minutes.
Puree in processor.
Return to saucepan; add milk, salt and cayenne pepper. Serve hot.
Makes 8 (3/4 cup) servings.

title: strawberry dessert
directions: Break up angel food cake in a large bowl.
Mix pudding mix according to instructions on box and pour over cake.
Spread Cool Whip over pudding.
Mix strawberries and glaze and spread over Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: potatoes
directions: Peel and thinly slice potatoes.
Arrange a layer of potatoes in a large dish (sprayed with Pam).
Dot with margarine.
Spread shredded cheese on potatoes.
Also, sprinkle cut up onions. Repeat and on second layer, spread 1/2 can of mushroom soup.
On third layer, leave off onions.
Cover top of potatoes with 6 slices of cheese and rest of soup.
Lightly sprinkle salt and pepper on each layer of potatoes.

title: baked pinto beans
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Saut onion in bacon drippings (or oil) until golden brown.
Combine with beans, brown sugar, chili powder, oregano, salt and pepper and tomato sauce.	Mix lightly and place in 2-quart dish.
Arrange bacon on top.
Cover.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove cover and bake 10 minutes to brown bacon.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix well and put in a greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: In medium bowl, beat together cream cheese, one cup powdered sugar, vanilla and grated lemon zest until light and fluffy. Gradually beat in remaining powdered sugar.

title: graham cracker pralines
directions: Put graham crackers on cookie sheet.
Melt butter; mix with brown sugar.
Boil 2 minutes.
Take off heat; stir in nuts. Spread on crackers.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes.
Put on waxed paper while still warm.

title: creamy corn
directions: In a slow-cooker combine all ingredients. cover and cook on low for 4 hours or until heated through and cheese is melted.

title: german sweet chocolate cream pie
directions: Heat chocolate and 2 tablespoons of the milk in a saucepan over low heat, stirring until chocolate is melted.
Beat sugar into cream cheese; add remaining milk and chocolate mixture.
Beat until smooth.
Fold chocolate mixture into whipped topping; beat until smooth.
Spoon into prepared crust and freeze until firm (approximately 4 hours).
Garnish with chocolate curls, if desired.
Store leftovers in freezer.

title: pizza sub
directions: Put on Pillsbury crust in long pan.
Add ham, then pepperoni. Top with sliced onion rings, sliced tomatoes and cut up lettuce. On top, spread grated Mozzarella cheese, then put the other pizza crust on top.
Cut a hole in the middle of crust.
Bake at 425° until crust is done and brown.
Eat it with spaghetti sauce on the side.

title: applesauce-raisin bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix applesauce, oil and sugar.
Mix in flour, baking soda, salt and spices, mixing well after each addition.
Add egg and raisins.

title: brownies
directions: In saucepan, put water, Crisco and butter.
Melt over heat until melted.
Remove from heat.
Add other ingredients except sour cream and nuts.
Fold in last.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes in large cookie sheet.

title: rye bread
directions: Combine 1 cup all-purpose flour, rye flour, yeast, rind, anise and salt in a large bowl.
Stir well.
Combine water, molasses and oil in a saucepan; heat to 130°, stirring occasionally.
Gradually add warm liquid to dry ingredients, beating for about 30 seconds at low speed and an additional 3 minutes at high speed.
Gradually add enough flour to form a moderately stiff dough.
Turn dough out on a lightly floured surface and knead until smooth, about 8 minutes. Shape into a ball and place in a well buttered bowl; turn to butter top.
Cover and let rise in a warm place (85°) free from drafts, 1 1/2 hours or until doubled in bulk.

title: strawberry rhubarb pie
directions: Line a 9-inch pan with pastry. Combine the berries and rhubarb; mix the sugar and cornstarch. Add the egg; fold in the fruit and spoon mixture into the pie shell. Top with a lattice crust. Bake in a 400° oven for 35 minutes.

title: cucumber salad
directions: Peel cucumber, slice thinly.
Peel onion, slice thinly.
Add vinegar, oil, sugar, salt and pepper.
If desired add sour cream before serving.

title: cherries in the snow
directions: Mix wafers and oleo.
Press into two 9 x 13-inch pans. Prepare Dream Whip according to package instructions.
(Might try adding butter flavoring to this recipe.)
Set aside.
Beat the cream cheese, sugar and vanilla together.
Add marshmallows and Dream Whip.
Spread over crust.
Spoon cherry pie filling over top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pralines
directions: Boil sugar and water to a temperature of 238° (or until a soft ball forms in cold water).
Remove cooked syrup from fire.

Add pecans. Return mixture to the fire until it again comes to a boil. Remove from fire and stir until syrup becomes slightly cloudy. Pour a large spoonful of the nut and syrup mixture on waxed paper to form a praline.
Makes about 35.

title: goose liver dip or braunschweiger
directions: Allow cream cheese to soften and then mix with onion and goose liver.
Form a ball or log and decorate with slices of olives. Eat on Wheat Thins or your favorite cracker.

title: millionaire's pie
directions: Beat egg and brush on pie crust.
Bake for 5 minutes at 325°. Cool
Mix by hand the rest of ingredients and spoon into crusts. Refrigerate before serving.

title: crabmeat muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Spread mix on the English muffins.
Cut into wedges while frozen.
Bake until hot at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: chicken broccoli rice casserole
directions: Saute onions and pepper in margarine.
Combine remaining ingredients, except crackers, 4 tablespoons margarine and grated cheese.
Place in a 9 x 11-inch casserole dish.
Top with grated cheese and crackers mixed with melted margarine.
Bake at 350° until bubbly.

title: grandma's casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 450°. Bring water to a boil and melt margarine or butter. Pour over turkey that has been salted and peppered in covered roasting pan. Put on lid. Place in oven. Let cook for 1 hour, then turn off oven, but DO NOT OPEN DOOR UNTIL THE NEXT MORNING. It will be done and brown. There will be plenty of broth. IF TURKEY IS LESS THAN 14 POUNDS, COOK ONLY 45 MINUTES.

title: tasty black-eyed peas
directions: Cook black-eyed peas according to package directions. Drain and set aside. Saute green pepper and onion in bacon drippings until tender. Add peas, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook over low heat until thoroughly heated, stirring often.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler.
Crumble sausage over Bisquick. Add melted cheese and mix with hands.
Shape into walnut-size balls.
Bake on cookie sheet for 30 minutes at 400°.

title: broccoli soup
directions: Steam or simmer broccoli for 15 minutes.
Drain.
Melt butter and saute onion.
Add flour, blend.
Stir in salt, pepper and milk. Cook on low heat until blended.
Add chicken broth, broccoli, carrots, sherry, garlic salt and celery soup.
Stir gently until bubbling and hot.

title: sweet potato spoon bread
directions: Combine sweet potatoes and oleo with dry ingredients.
Blend in milk and eggs.
Pour into square baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: butterscotch crunches
directions: Mix butterscotch morsels with peanut butter.
Mix all ingredients well; spoon onto wax paper and let cool.

title: zucchini bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine flour, cinnamon, baking soda, salt, baking powder and nutmeg.
In another mixing bowl, combine sugar, shredded zucchini, cooking oil, egg and lemon peel; mix well.
Add flour mixture; stir just until combined.
Stir in walnuts.
Pour batter into a greased 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan.
Bake in a 350° oven for 55 to 60 minutes or until a toothpick inserted near the center comes out clean.
Cool for 10 minutes on a wire rack.

title: world's best playdough!
directions: Mix flour, salt, cream of tartar in medium saucepan.
Add water and oil.
Cook for 3 minutes, or until mixture pulls away from sides of pan.
Knead slightly when cooled.
To color, divide playdough into sections when cooled.
Add several drops of food coloring to each sections, working in with hands (do on wax paper instead of counter top.)
Store in airtight plastic container.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Bring to a boil, then turn down to a simmer for 5 minutes. Brush on thick before turning each time.

title: skillet potato salad
directions: Broil or fry bacon until crisp; drain on paper towels and crumble.
Reserve 1/4 cup drippings.
Add celery to reserved bacon drippings in skillet; cook and stir until tender-crisp.
Add onion and cook 1 or 2 minutes longer.
Combine sugar, flour, salt, celery seed and pepper; stir into celery-onion mixture.
Add water and vinegar, stirring until smooth.
Bring to a bubbling boil; add potatoes and bacon.
Mix thoroughly.
Serve as soon as heated through.
Makes six servings.
Can also be made with hot dog slices instead of bacon or leave meat out all together and serve on top of raw spinach!

title: chocolate mint cookies
directions: Mix together cake mix, shortening, water and eggs well.
Form into 1 inch balls.
Roll in powdered sugar.
Put on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake in 375° oven for 7 to 10 minutes.
When done baking immediately push Junior Mint in middle.
Remove from cookie sheet.
Let cool.

title: raspberry pie
directions: Put 1 1/4 cups sugar, 1/3 cup cornstarch and 1/4 teaspoon salt in a bowl and mix.
Add berries and melted butter; mix together. Pour into a baking dish; let stand while you fix pastry.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, celery, eggs, pickles and salt.
Add enough mayonnaise to moisten.
Yields 6 to 8 servings.

title: 3-hole chocolate cake - no eggs!
directions: Mix together dry
ingredients,
put in an ungreased pan and make 3
holes.
Add
liquid
as follows, keeping separate: 1st hole - 5
tablespoons
oil,
2nd hole - 1 teaspoon vanilla and 3rd hole - 1 tablespoon vinegar.
Add 1 cup water.
Stir a little. Bake in an ungreased pan at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes (25 minutes for cupcakes).

title: barbecue green beans
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Bake for 1 hour in covered casserole dish at 275°.

title: double boiler bread pudding
directions: Place brown sugar on top of double boiler and the bread on top of it.
Mix eggs, salt, vanilla and milk.
Pour over bread.
Do not stir!
Steam over boiling water until knife comes out clean. Serve warm with ice cream.

title: cinnamon toast
directions: Spread softened butter on bread and sprinkle cinnamon mix on bread.
Place under broiler and let cook until toast is brown.

title: chicken and rice casserole
directions: Boil chicken breasts until done.
Debone and cut into bite-size pieces.
Cook rice.
Mix broth, mushrooms, flour and butter.
Cook over low heat until thickened.
Add milk and salt. Cook over low heat for 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Mix with rice.
Add chicken pieces and mix.
Pour into buttered casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 375°.

title: bethany's macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni in boiling salted water until tender; drain. In saucepan melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Add milk; cook and stir until thick and bubbly.
Add cheese; stir until melted.
Mix cheese sauce with macaroni.
Turn into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: goldwater beans
directions: Soak beans over night.
Cook until tender - about 2 hours. Brown meat in back fat.
Add meat to beans; add all other ingredients and cook until flavors blend.
Serve with cornbread pancakes.

title: white chocolate icing
directions: Beat cream cheese and butter on medium speed until blended. Add melted chocolate and vanilla. Add sugar gradually, beating until light and fluffy after each addition.

title: cabbage ham and cheese salad
directions: Mix all of the dressing ingredients, adding oil last, slowly. Can put dressing on an hour or two before serving.
Serve on a bed of Boston lettuce and radicchio.
Garnish with 6 tablespoons fresh parsley, chopped and put on the top and sprinkle with fresh ground pepper.

title: cheddary scalloped potatoes
directions: In skillet over medium heat in hot margarine or butter, cook onion until tender.
Stir in soup, milk and pepper.
Heat to boiling.

Add potatoes. Reduce heat to low. Cover and simmer 5 minutes or until hot and bubbling, stirring occasionally. Garnish with sage if desired. For cheesier flavor, add 1/4 cup shredded Cheddar cheese to soup.

title: easy beef stroganoff
directions: Mix all the ingredients together.
Bake at 300° for 3 hours. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: cashew chicken(oriental)
directions: Heat wok over high heat.
Add oil and swirl around until wok is coated.
Sprinkle in salt.
Add chicken and stir-fry for 2 minutes. Add pea pods, bamboo shoots, mushrooms and chicken broth.
Cover and cook for 2 minutes.
Carefully stir in nuts and sugar.
Mix cornstarch with water to form paste.
Add cornstarch mixture to chicken and cook, stirring constantly, until sauce thickens. Remove from heat and serve.
Serves 4.

title: peaches and cream
directions: Sprinkle peaches with sugar; set aside.
In medium bowl, beat milk with lemon juice until thick.
Fold in whipped cream and sweetened peaches.
Fill cooked crepes; fold over.
Serve with whipped cream, if desired.
Makes 8 to 10 crepes.

title: sweet potato pone
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Place in a buttered casserole dish. Top with butter.
Bake at 350° until golden brown, about 45 minutes.
Yields 6 servings.

title: zucchini sweet relish
directions: Grind squash, onions, peppers and carrots.
Soak in salt for at least 3 hours or overnight.
Drain through a sieve and wash through 2 clear waters.
Drain well.

title: lemon bisque
directions: Chill milk in freezer.
Cream Jell-O, sugar and cream cheese. Slowly add boiling water and vanilla.
Let stand in refrigerator until thickened.
Whip Pet milk, lemon juice and zest until it stands in peaks.
Fold into Jell-O mixture.
Sprinkle 1/2 of crumbs into bottom of 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish; pour mixture over crumbs.
Top with remaining crumbs.
Freeze.
Take out 10 minutes before serving.
May be served with sauce (pureed strawberries or raspberries with a little sugar).

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Make pie shell with high-fluted edge.
Place cherry pie filling in shell and bake at 425° for 15 minutes.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Mix dry ingredients together.
Add oil, egg and sour cream.
Roll into balls and drop onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Place maraschino cherry in center while warm.

title: melting apples
directions: Coat a 10 x 6 x 2-inch baking dish with cooking spray. Arrange apple slices in baking dish.
Sprinkle with allspice and flavoring.
Top with marshmallow halves. Cover and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Serve warm.
Yields 6 servings.

title: amish vanilla pie
directions: Combine 1/2 cup brown sugar, 1 tablespoon flour, corn syrup, vanilla and egg in 2-quart saucepan.
Slowly stir in water.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly until mixture comes to a boil.
Let cool.
Combine 1 cup flour, 1/2 cup brown sugar, cream of tartar, baking soda, salt and butter.
Mix until crumbly.
Pour cooled mixture into pie shell; top with crumbs.
Bake in 350° oven 40 minutes or until golden brown.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: yellow squash casserole
directions: Cook squash in small amount of oil, together with onion and bell pepper.
Mix all remaining ingredients, except eggs.
Let cook about 15 to 20 minutes.
Add eggs and season to taste.
Top with bread crumbs and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: christmas fruit pie
directions: Make crust of crushed wafers and margarine.
Mix the remaining ingredients, except whipped cream.
Combine fruit mixture; pour over crust.
Top with whipped cream.
Chill and serve.

title: corn casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients including 8 ounces grated Cheddar cheese thoroughly.
Bake in large baking dish for 35 to 40 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: easy fantasy fudge
directions: Lightly grease 13 x 9-inch or 9-inch square pan.

title: death by chocolate
directions: Let brownies cool and break up into chunks.
Place 1/2 of the chunks into a deep, flat-bottomed dish.
Spread 1/2 of the pudding on top of the brownies.
Sprinkle 1/2 of the chocolate chips over the pudding.
Spread 1/2 of the Cool Whip over the chips.
Crush 3 of the candy bars with a hammer before unwrapping them.
Sprinkle this across the top of the Cool Whip.
Repeat the layers of brownies, pudding, chips, Cool Whip and candy.
Garnish with the chocolate syrup.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: garden medley
directions: Dump everything into a pot.
Cook over medium heat until squash is tender.

title: tortellini ala panna
directions: In a deep saute pan, melt 1/2 butter.
Add onion and garlic; saute 3 to 4 minutes.
Add mushrooms and tomatoes.
Saute another 3 to 4 minutes.
Add remainder of butter and thyme.
Add cream. If using dry basil, add now.
Reduce mixture in half.
If using fresh basil, add after cream is reduced.

title: apple tray
directions: Fill a bowl 3/4 full with pineapple juice.
Quarter, then core each apple.
Cut each apple slice in half (each apple will make 8 apple slices).
Drop apple slices in pineapple juice and let soak while slicing the next apple.
Swish juice over apples, then let drain on paper towels.
Arrange a tray, alternating rows of red and green apples.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix cake mix, oil and eggs in one at a time.
Add poppy seed and nutmeats.
Add the crushed bananas.
Pour into a greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about an hour or until done.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Note:
May top with toasted bread crumbs at dinner.

title: spaghetti pizza
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti.
Beat egg with milk and stir into spaghetti until moistened.
Pour into greased 9 x 12-inch metal pan.
Pour large jar Ragu sauce over spaghetti.
Sprinkle shredded Mozzarella cheese over this.
Top with pepperoni slices.
Cover tight.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: green rice and broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in melted margarine.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Pour into an 8-inch square glass baking dish.
Cover with foil and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Recipe may be doubled and baked in a 9 x 13-inch pan for about 15 minutes longer.
When doubling, broccoli cuts may be used instead of chopped broccoli.

title: fruit tra-a-la
directions: Cook flour, sugar, pineapple juice, salt and egg.
Boil slowly, stirring until thick.
Cool.
When cool, fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over the jello mixture.
Let chill for 2 hours.
Serve as salad or dessert.

title: 7-up cake
directions: Mix together the cake mix, pudding mix, cooking oil and 7-Up. Add eggs, one at a time. Bake in a greased and floured tube pan or 3 round cake pans at 350° for about 25 minutes.
Mix together sugar, coconut, flour, water and pineapple and cook in double boiler until icing turns white looking and kind of thick.
Then pour over cake.

title: sonora casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with onion in large skillet.
Add chilies, evaporated milk and soups to ground beef.
Tear tortillas into small pieces.
Layer in a 9 x 13-inch pan as follows:
layer of meat followed by layer of tortillas followed by cheese.
Do this twice, ending with cheese.
Casserole may be refrigerated or frozen at this point for later use.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.
If casserole is frozen, thaw in refrigerator before baking or increase baking time if starting from frozen state.
Serves 12.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown meat and onion together. Add remaining ingredients except lasagna noodles and simmer 45 minutes to 1 hour until rather thick.

title: tena's cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and brown sugar.
Add beaten eggs and vanilla; beat well.
Add the remaining ingredients in order, stirring well after each ingredient.
Roll into balls.
Place 2 inches apart on a cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes in a 375° oven. Makes 9 dozen.

title: glazed fruit
directions: Drain fruit well, reserving pineapple juice.
Mix pudding with pineapple juice and 1 teaspoon almond flavor.
Pour over fruit.

title: carrot cake
directions: Mix together sugar and oil; stir together dry ingredients. Add to oil mixture.
Blend in carrots, pineapple, nuts, eggs and vanilla.

title: date pudding
directions: Pour soda over dates and pour boiling water over; blend and let stand.
Mix sugar, salt, butter and eggs; blend well.
Stir into dates, then add flour, baking powder and nut meats.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: egg custard pie
directions: Beat eggs and add remaining liquid ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients together and add to first mixture.
Put in two large unbaked pie shells.
Bake for 30 minutes at 400°.
Yield:
2 pies.

title: roast beef and yorkshire puddingengland
directions: Heat oven to 350°f. 180°c. gas mark 4. In a 13 x 9-inch baking pan, brush the beef with the melted butter, pour any remaining butter into the pan.
Place in the center of the oven and roast for 20 minutes per pound + 20 minutes extra.
Baste occassionally.
In the meantime, using a whisk, mix together the water, milk and egg then add the flour and salt, whisk well until smooth.
Set aside until beef is cooked.
Remove beef from oven and use drippings to grease 12 muffin tins, turn heat up to 425°f. 215°c. gas mark 7 and place muffin tins on center rack.
When muffin tins are smoking, quickly divide the batter between them.
Bake for approximately 30-40 minutes or until the yorkshire puddings are well risen and golden brown.
Makes 1 dozen puddings.
Serve with brown gravy, potatoes (roasted in the pan with the beef for the last hour of cooking) and fresh veggies.

title: shrimp sandwiches(new to me)
directions: In a large bowl, beat eggs. Add the shrimp, haddock, pancake mix, cornmeal, parsley, celery salt, mustard and paprika; mix well. Shape into 8 patties. Coat with bread crumbs.

title: beef and macaroni(quick and easy  dinner)
directions: Cook ground chuck until done; drain. Cook macaroni; drain. Mix together with Ro-Tel tomatoes. Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 375°.

title: potato salad dressing
directions: Mix together the sugar and flour, then add the milk, vinegar and egg. Stir until smooth and cook until thick. Add mayonnaise and mustard.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil butter, shortening, cocoa and water.
Pour over sugar and flour.
Beat soda in buttermilk.
Add eggs and vanilla. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: lithuanian sour kraut
directions: Fry bacon until crisp and set aside. Save 2 Tbsp. of bacon grease.

title: congealed asparagus salad
directions: Mix all ingredients. Chill.

title: cool whip caramel pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan or skillet. Add pecans and cook until done- drain. Set aside.

title: pineapple dish
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Melt butter; add beaten egg and sugar. Mix pineapple and cubed bread.
Stir and pour into baking pan. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix the applesauce, oleo and vanilla. Add the flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt.
Add the chocolate bits, pecans and raisins.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a greased and floured angel food pan.
Serves 18.

title: breakfast muffins
directions: Combine flour, baking powder and sugar. Mix bran, oats and corn meal together; stir in egg and oil. Add to dry ingredients. Pour into greased muffin pans, filling each cup 2/3 full. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. Serve warm or split and toast.

title: spicy hot beans
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven. Cover with water 2-inches above beans; let soak 8 hours.
Drain beans and return to Dutch oven.
Add all 6 cups water.
Combine bacon and next 4 ingredients in a skillet and cook over medium heat until bacon is browned and vegetables are tender.
Drain and add to beans.

Add Worcestershire sauce and remaining ingredients, except tomatoes, and bring mixture to a boil. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 2 hours or until beans are tender, stirring occasionally. Add tomatoes and cook an additional 30 minutes. Remove bay leaf. Yields 10 servings.

title: peanut butter sticks
directions: Cut each slice of bread in 6 strips or more.
Cut off crust. Dry out on cookie sheet in a 200° oven for 3 hours.
Melt peanut butter and oil in a double boiler.
Coat each bread stick in the peanut mixture.
Dry and roll in corn flakes.
These are better rolled in 4x powdered sugar.

title: crab dip
directions: Use equal portions of cream cheese and marshmallow cream. Beat/blend together.
Use as dip for any kind of fruit.

title: hush puppies
directions: Combine all ingredients and drop by spoonful into hot oil and deep fry until golden brown.

title: butter pecan ice cream
directions: Mix and freeze in a a 4 quart ice cream churn.

title: donna's steak marinade
directions: Cover and refrigerate for 2 hours or overnight.
Grill or Broil. Dispose of marinade.

title: peach cream pie
directions: Slice peaches into crust.

title: bourbon balls(no bake)
directions: In a large bowl, mix all ingredients except 1/2 cup granulated sugar.
Shape mixture into 1-inch balls.
Roll balls in granulated sugar.
Store in tightly covered container for at least 3 days before serving for flavors to mellow.
Keeps up to 2 weeks in tightly covered container.
Makes about 3 1/2 dozen balls, about 85 calories each.

title: grandma miller's pancakes
directions: Batter should resemble a crepe batter in thickness.
Fry pancakes in a generous amount of Crisco shortening.
This recipe makes a thin, moist pancake approximately 3 inches in diameter.

title: krispy treats
directions: Bring to boil sugar and syrup. Boil
till clear, on medium- medium high heat. Remove from heat stir in peanut butter and rice krispies. Press into buttered pan.

title: czechoslovakian cookies
directions: Mix by hand with long wooden spoon.
Cream butter and add sugar.
Cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs yolks and blend well.
Add flour, mix thoroughly.
Fold in nuts, salt and vanilla. Spoon 1/2 batter into pan.
Spread evenly.
Spread strawberry jam on dough.
Cover with remaining dough.
Bake 1 hour at 325° or until lightly browned.
Remove from oven.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on top.
Cut into squares.

title: hamburger hash(serves four)
directions: Crumble ground beef into a heavy skillet.
Brown over medium heat until rich brown in color.
Add the minced onion and continue to brown until the onion is transparent.
Add the diced potatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.
Add just enough water to barely cover the ingredients.
Simmer gently until the potatoes are tender (about 15 minutes).
Don't hurry the simmering for the slow cooking is what gives it a delicious flavor.
Make a paste of two tablespoons of flour and 1/2 cup of water.
When the potatoes are tender, add the flour and water mixture.
Stir until the mixture thickens and starts to bubble again.
Serve with hot buttered toast or biscuits.

title: cheese ball
directions: Soften ingredients and mix until smooth.
Refrigerate 2 or more hours.
Shape into any size ball.
Slice green olives and place slices 2-inches apart on
outside of cheeseballs.
Roll cheeseball in chopped pecans or walnuts.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: marinade beef kabobs
directions: Pour over meat and refrigerate for at least 4 hours; beat if marinated overnight.

title: conch chowder
directions: Dice salt pork and fry out.
Add diced garlic, green pepper and onions.
Cook until well done.
Add mashed whole tomatoes, tomato paste, poultry seasoning, oregano, bay leaves, salt, pepper and barbecue sauce.
Cook over low heat.
Bring water to a boil in large saucepan.
Add vinegar and ground conch.
Add other ingredients and cook 2 hours.
Add diced potatoes and cook until tender.

title: pork and noodle casserole
directions: Brown meat in butter.
Add broth.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Add rest of ingredients and bring to boil.
Place in buttered casserole.
Top with buttered bread crumbs.
Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes in 300° oven.

title: shipwreck casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown ground beef with onion and celery.
Drain.
Add beans, salt and pepper.
Place layers of potatoes and meat in casserole dish.
Spoon soup evenly over all. Cover and bake 1 hour or until done.

title: casserole stuffing
directions: Cook celery, onions and poultry seasoning in butter until tender.
Add soup and mix lightly with bread crumbs.
Bake in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: tuna macaroni salad
directions: Combine macaroni, tuna, artichoke hearts and tomatoes.
Toss lightly.
Mix together salt, pepper, garlic, paprika, oil and vinegar.
Pour dressing over tuna and macaroni mixture and toss thoroughly.
Chill until ready to serve.
Serve on well washed spinach leaves.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: apple pie
directions: Blend together the sugar, 1 tablespoon of flour, cinnamon and salt.
Toss lightly with apples.
Spoon into pastry lined pan.

title: rum or bourbon balls
directions: Mix together in a large bowl and roll into small balls.
If too dry when rolling, add another spoon of bourbon or rum.
Roll in sugar and keep in sealed container.
The longer they sit in container, the better.

title: cereal cookies
directions: Bake 375° for 15-17 minutes.

title: pumpkin dream bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 13 x 9-inch pan.
Beat margarine and sugar until fluffy.
Add combined oats and flour; mix well. Spread evenly onto bottom of pan.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly.
Beat cream cheese and sugar at medium speed until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix until smooth.
Pour over crust.
Bake 45 to 50 minutes.
Cool completely.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix all until creamy.
Spread on muffins.
Freeze.
Cut in fourths.
Broil 3 to 4 minutes until bubbly.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix together ingredients in order given.
Pour into 2 medium greased loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: brown sugar bars
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar. Add egg yolk, vanilla and flour; blend. Spread evenly in a lightly greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes (until lightly brown). Remove from oven. Immediately sprinkle chocolate chips on top and set back in oven for 2 minutes. Remove and spread chocolate over bars immediately. Sprinkle with chopped nuts. Cool and cut.

title: pie crust
directions: Sift flour with salt; blend oil and water.
(Shake in jar until foamy.)
Pour over flour; blend.
Roll out pie crust between two sheets of wax paper.
Makes 2 flakey pie crusts.

title: hot clam dip
directions: In mixing bowl pour the 2 cans of clams with juice.
Add breadcrumbs and spices.
Melt margarine in small saucepan and mix with the clams and breadcrumbs mixture.
Pour batter into a 9-inch pie pan. Cover entire top with Mozzarella cheese (won't need all 8 ounces).
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake in a 375° oven for 15 minutes or until cheese is melted. Serve hot with crackers on the side. Use teaspoon to scoop onto crackers.

title: peanut butter gems
directions: Combine.
Shape in small balls and roll in shredded coconut. Store in tight container in refrigerator.

title: swedish soft spice cake(swedish "mjuk pepperkaka")
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Add milk with egg and beat together. Last, add the melted butter.
Bake in moderate oven about 1 hour. Loaf pan is good for this recipe.

title: divinity fudge
directions: Combine Karo syrup, water, salt and sugar; boil to 265° or hard ball stage.
Beat egg whites until stiff and gradually beat in the boiling syrup mixture.
Beat until it begins to stiffen, then add vanilla and nuts.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper to cool.

title: apricot ham steak
directions: Trim fat around ham; place in shallow dish and sprinkle with sugar and stud sides with cloves.
Drain apricot juice.
Pour 1/3 cup of juice over ham.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour, basting often with juice in pan.
Arrange apricots on top of ham; bake 15 minutes longer.
Approximately 270 calories per serving.

title: cream cheese cherry tarts(makes 24)
directions: Mix.
Pour on top of cream cheese mixture.
Bake 5 more minutes at 450°.
Cool.
(Can be frozen.)
Top with a 30 ounce can of cherry pie filling two hours before serving.
Chill.

title: apple turnovers
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine flour, granulated sugar, salt and cinnamon.
Cut in Crisco with pastry blender or two knives until mixture is uniform.
Sprinkle dough with water, a tablespoon at a time, stirring it with a fork until just enough has been added so that dough can be patted into a ball.
Divide pastry in half. On a lightly floured surface, roll 1/2 of the dough into a 10 x 15-inch rectangle.
Cut into six 5-inch squares.
Repeat with other half of dough.
Place about 2 measuring tablespoons of fruit filling in center of each square.
Moisten pastry edges with water. Fold over one half of pastry to form a triangle.
Seal edges firmly with a fork.
Prick top with fork for steam to escape.
Bake on ungreased baking sheets 12 to 15 minutes or until lightly browned. Cool slightly.
Sprinkle with confectioners sugar.
Makes 12.
Out of this world!

title: broccoli and cheese
directions: Mix together and bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: veggie sandwich
directions: Spread bread with fat-free mayonnaise and mustard.
Layer the tomatoes, zucchini, onion, cucumbers and leaf lettuce.
Top with second slice of bread.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender, 20 to 25 minutes.
Drain in colander.
Put in bowl.
Add margarine while hot.
Add other ingredients; mix well.
Place in Pyrex dish; sprinkle top with stuffing mix.
Dot with margarine.
Bake at 350° for about 25 minutes until bubbly and brown.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken breasts for 1 hour.
After cooking, cut chicken up into pieces.
Set chicken aside and then cook spaghetti noodles for 10 minutes.
Chop onion and bell pepper up and saute in butter until tender, then add onion and bell pepper to chicken.
Add cream of mushroom soup and cooked spaghetti noodles to the chicken mixture.
Mix well; put Mozzarella cheese in bottom of casserole dish, then add spaghetti and chicken mixture.
Then put Cheddar cheese on top.
Cook for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: toffee treasure cake
directions: Mix cake according to
recipe on box.
Grease and flour 1 Bundt pan or two layer cake pans and pour batter into pans.

title: pimento and cheese casserole
directions: Prepare the macaroni and cheese as on the box. Add to it all the other ingredients.
Pour into baking dish.
Top with bread crumbs. Bake in oven at 350° until bubbles.

title: stuffed artichokes
directions: Drain and arrange artichokes on baking sheet, open center. Melt 1/2 stick butter, garlic and bread crumbs until slightly moistened with oregano, parsley and black pepper.
Stuff each artichoke and dot each one with oil.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: two-crust lemon pie
directions: Beat all ingredients together, then add 1 1/2 cups of hot water.
Cook over medium heat until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour thickened mixture into a 9-inch pie crust. Cover with second crust and seal edges.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 hour or until crust is golden brown.

title: sour cream cashew drops
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda and salt together into mixing bowl.
Put egg, butter, sugar, vanilla and sour cream in blender.
Cover and cream on speed 6 until smooth.
Stop blender and add nuts.
Cover and chop on high until nuts are chopped fine.
Pour into flour mixture and stir to mix. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto greased cookie sheets.
Bake about 10 minutes.
Cool and frost with white powdered sugar frosting.

title: ultimate scalloped potatoes
directions: Grease a shallow 1 1/2-quart baking dish with butter. Set aside. In a saucepan, combine cream, milk, salt, pepper and garlic. Cook just until bubbles begin to form around sides of pan. Remove from the heat; cool for 10 minutes. Peel and thinly slice the potatoes; pat dry with paper towels. Layer half of the potatoes in prepared baking dish. Top with half of the cream mixture and half of the cheeses. Repeat layers. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 55 to 65 minutes or until potatoes are tender. Let stand for 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate covered marshmallows
directions: Place chocolate chips and shortening in 2 Cup measuring bowl. Microwave at medium 1 to 3 minutes or until chips are shiny and soft.
Stir until smooth.

title: french onion soup
directions: In covered large saucepan, cook onion in butter over low heat, about 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add beef broth, water and Worcestershire sauce; heat to boiling.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer about 30 minutes.
Place 1/2 slice toasted bread in each of 4 soup bowls.
Pour hot soup over bread and sprinkle with cheese. Makes 4 servings (1 cup each).

title: italian "lite" potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes and cut into large chunks.
Place in pan and cover with water.
Add a little salt and bring to a boil.
Cook until tender.
Drain.
While hot, cover with dressing to taste. Serve hot.

title: liz's congealed salad
directions: Drain fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Heat fruit juices until simmering and mix with jello.
Mix cream cheese with jello and other ingredients.
If fruit settles to bottom, stir once after beginning to chill.

title: coconut ice cream pie(make day ahead.)
directions: Mix cracker and margarine and line a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix pudding with milk.
Add vanilla ice cream.
Mix well with mixer. Pour over crackers.
Ice with Cool Whip and top with coconut. Store in refrigerator.

title: 3 step cheesecake
directions: Mix cheese, sugar and vanilla with electric mixer on medium speed; blend well. Add eggs and mix until well blended. Pour into crust. Bake at 350° for 40 minutes until center is almost set; cool. Refrigerate 3 hours to overnight. Top with fruit. Serves 8 to 10.
